1
00:00:58,260 --> 00:01:02,480
古巴 关达那摩湾 美国海军基地

2
00:02:47,990 --> 00:02:51,240
<i><b><font color=#FFFF80>义海雄风</b></i>

3
00:02:55,870 --> 00:02:58,460
齐步走！
Forward march!

4
00:04:30,380 --> 00:04:32,970
我请求
I'm requesting...

5
00:04:32,970 --> 00:04:37,180
上校，我想请求由我担任律师
Captain, I'd like to request that it be me who's the attorney...

6
00:04:37,180 --> 00:04:40,020
这是我自己决定的
That it be myself who's assigned.

7
00:04:40,020 --> 00:04:42,940
不行，我想请求指任我作
No, I'd like to request that it be I who am assigned...

8
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:46,650
“这是我的决定”？
"That it be I who am assigned"?

9
00:04:46,650 --> 00:04:50,070
这样不错，显得信心十足
That's good. That's confidence-inspiring.

10
00:04:50,070 --> 00:04:52,030
措辞也很得体
Good grammar there.

11
00:04:52,070 --> 00:04:53,280
上校，我想请求指任我为律师
Captain, I'd like to request...

12
00:04:53,280 --> 00:04:57,950
上校，我想请求指任我为律师
<font size=18 color=#9B9BFF>华盛顿哥伦比亚特区  法务总监办事处
that I be the attorney assigned.

13
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:02,580
嗨，我是盖洛维少校，来这见威斯特上校
I'm Lieutenant Commander Galloway here to see Captain West.

14
00:05:02,580 --> 00:05:04,540
快进去吧，少校，他们正等着你
Go right in, Commander. They're expecting you.

15
00:05:04,580 --> 00:05:06,040
谢谢
Thank you.

16
00:05:09,590 --> 00:05:11,550
乔，快进来 谢谢，长官
Jo, come on in. Thank you, sir.

17
00:05:12,630 --> 00:05:15,640
威斯特上校，这就是盖洛维少校
Captain West, this is Lieutenant Commander Galloway.

18
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:18,060
乔，你认识劳伦斯少校吧？ 是的，长官
Jo, you know Commander Lawrence. Yes, sir.

19
00:05:18,060 --> 00:05:20,270
上校，很感谢你这么快就接见我
Captain, I appreciate you seeing me on such short notice.

20
00:05:20,310 --> 00:05:22,940
干嘛不坐下？ 不用，长官
Would you like to sit down? I'm fine, sir.

21
00:05:22,940 --> 00:05:25,480
坐吧 好的
Have a seat. Okay.

22
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:27,730
我听说上周末在古巴出了麻烦是吧？
I understand we had some trouble over the weekend down in Cuba?

23
00:05:27,730 --> 00:05:31,110
是的，长官，上周五有两名海军陆战队员
Yes, sir. This past Friday, two Marines...

24
00:05:31,110 --> 00:05:35,160
准下士哈罗德・道森 和一等兵劳登・多尼
a Lance Corporal Harold Dawson and a Private Louden Downey...

25
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:39,410
进入一等兵威廉・圣地亚哥的营房 并殴打了他
entered the barracks room of a P.F.C. William Santiago and assaulted him.

26
00:05:39,410 --> 00:05:43,000
大约一小时后圣地亚哥在基地医院身亡
Santiago died at the base hospital approximately an hour later.

27
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:46,580
负责给道森和多尼录取口供 的海军调查处官员…
The N.I.S. Agent who took Dawson and Downey's statements...

28
00:05:46,580 --> 00:05:48,960
认定他们是想试图阻止圣地亚哥…
maintains they were trying to prevent Santiago...

29
00:05:48,960 --> 00:05:51,880
举报道森在界线上的开枪事件
from naming Dawson in a fenceline shooting incident.

30
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:55,720
已安排今天下午四点 在基地举行一次听证会
They're scheduled to have a hearing down in Cuba this afternoon at 16:00.

31
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:57,680
问题在哪？ 道森和多尼…
What's the problem? Dawson and Downey...

32
00:05:57,720 --> 00:06:02,100
都是模范海军陆战队员 而圣地亚哥是有名的落后分子
are both recruiting poster Marines, and Santiago was known to be a screwup.

33
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:04,980
我猜这多半是一次“红色条规”
I was thinking it sounded an awful lot like a Code Red.

34
00:06:05,690 --> 00:06:07,270
老天
Christ.

35
00:06:07,310 --> 00:06:11,070
长官，我希望将他们移交华盛顿 并为他们指派一名
Sir, I'd like to have them moved up to Washington and assigned counsel...

36
00:06:11,070 --> 00:06:13,400
能认真调查此事
someone who can really look into this...

37
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:15,860
不仅精通法律技巧…
someone who possesses not only the legal skill...

38
00:06:15,860 --> 00:06:18,870
而且熟知军队内部运作方式的律师
but a familiarity with the inner workings of the military.

39
00:06:18,870 --> 00:06:21,450
简而言之，上校，我提议…
In short, Captain, I'd like to suggest that...

40
00:06:21,450 --> 00:06:23,450
由我来担任
I be the one who that...

41
00:06:23,450 --> 00:06:28,670
指派我作他们的辩护律师
that it be me who is assigned to represent them... myself.

42
00:06:30,710 --> 00:06:33,300
盖洛维少校，你要不要来杯咖啡？
Commander Galloway, why don'tyou get yourself a cup of coffee?

43
00:06:33,300 --> 00:06:35,380
谢谢，长官，不用
Thank you, sir. I'm fine.

44
00:06:35,380 --> 00:06:38,640
我希望你能回避一下好让我们私下谈谈
I'd like you to leave the room so we can talk about you behind your back.

45
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:40,640
没问题，长官
Certainly, sir.

46
00:06:47,350 --> 00:06:50,480
我还以为再也不会有什么“红色条规”了
I thought this Code Red shit wasn't going on anymore.

47
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:53,650
海军远在关达那摩 谁知道在那有些什么鬼事？
With the Marines at Gitmo, who knows what the hell goes on down there?

48
00:06:53,650 --> 00:06:55,690
我们最好在其他人知道之前查清楚
We better find out before the rest of the world does.

49
00:06:55,690 --> 00:06:57,780
这种鬼事有可能弄得无法收拾
Damn thing could get messy.

50
00:06:57,820 --> 00:07:00,410
好吧，这个盖洛维少校怎么样？
All right, what about this Commander Galloway?

51
00:07:00,410 --> 00:07:03,620
她在内政部担任文职人员…
She's been working a desk in Internal Affairs...

52
00:07:03,620 --> 00:07:05,580
有一年多了
for a little over a year now.

53
00:07:05,620 --> 00:07:08,670
之前呢？ 两年内办过三个案子
Before that? Disposed of three cases in two years.

54
00:07:08,670 --> 00:07:11,580
两年三件案子？罗森博格叛国案吗？
Three cases in two years? Who's she handling, the Rosenbergs?

55
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:14,170
她不适合做首席律师 但绝对是个好调查员
She's not cut out for litigation. She's a hell of an investigator.

56
00:07:14,210 --> 00:07:17,760
她在内政部协助律师工作非常尽力
In Internal Affairs she can crawl up a lawyer's ass with the best of them.

57
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:21,680
但到了庭讯的时候 我知道，心有余而力不足
But when it comes to trial work... I know. All passion, no street smarts.

58
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:23,640
叫她进来吧
Bring her back in.

59
00:07:34,070 --> 00:07:37,110
少校，我们明早就将被告转到这里来
Commander, we're gonna have the defendants moved up here in the morning.

60
00:07:37,110 --> 00:07:40,360
谢谢，长官 师部会给他们指派律师
Thankyou, sir. Division will assign them counsel.

61
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:45,790
但…不是我 根据你的同事对你的评价…
But not me. From what I get from your colleagues...

62
00:07:45,790 --> 00:07:48,200
由你担任此事太过大材小用…
you're much too valuable in your present assignment to be wasted...

63
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:50,330
我相信此案无非是几分钟的庭辩…
in what I'm sure will boil down to a five-minute plea bargain...

64
00:07:50,370 --> 00:07:52,330
以及一个礼拜的文书工作
and a week's worth of paperwork.

65
00:07:52,370 --> 00:07:54,540
长官，我想恐怕没这么简单
Sir, I think there might be more involved than that.

66
00:07:54,590 --> 00:07:56,050
别担心
Don't worry about it.

67
00:07:56,090 --> 00:07:59,050
我保证师部会为此指派合适的人选
I promise you Division will assign the right man for the job.

68
00:07:59,420 --> 00:08:01,430
好了，来吧，拿下二垒
All right. Let's go. Let's get two.

69
00:08:02,930 --> 00:08:05,220
抱歉 用不着抱歉，切比
Sorry. Nothing to be sorry about, Sherby.

70
00:08:05,220 --> 00:08:07,470
你只要把球接住就行
You just look the ball into your glove.

71
00:08:07,470 --> 00:08:08,930
第二投
Shooting two.

72
00:08:10,730 --> 00:08:12,730
对不起 你得相信我，切比
Sorry. You gotta trust me, Sherby.

73
00:08:12,770 --> 00:08:16,570
你只要集中精神就能提高接住的成功率
Keep your eyes open, your chances of catching it increase by a factor often.

74
00:08:16,570 --> 00:08:18,480
凯菲 我们再试试
Kaffee. Let's try it again.

75
00:08:19,610 --> 00:08:21,650
戴维，你精神失常吗？
Dave, you seem distraught.

76
00:08:21,650 --> 00:08:24,490
麦德摩的案子 我们约好在十五分钟前会面的
We were supposed to meet 15 minutes ago about the McDermott case.

77
00:08:24,490 --> 00:08:27,280
你是在拖延时间，现在我们马上着手…
You're stalling on this thing. Now we either do it now...

78
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:30,950
不然我就把你的当事人送上他妈的绞架
or, no kidding, Kaffee, I'm gonna hang your boy from a fucking yardarm!

79
00:08:30,950 --> 00:08:35,000
绞架？切比，海军还在用绞架行刑吗？
Yardarm? Sherby, does the Navy still hang people from yardarms?

80
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,460
我看不会
I don't think so.

81
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:39,920
戴维，切比认为海军不会再采用绞刑
Dave, Sherby doesn't think the Navy hangs people from yardarms anymore.

82
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:43,340
我要指控他藏毒并在值勤期间吸毒
I'm gonna charge him with possession and being under the influence on duty.

83
00:08:43,340 --> 00:08:47,600
你劝他认罪的话 我可以建议判他三十天监禁
You plead guilty, I'll recommend 30 days in the brig with loss of rank and pay.

84
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:50,640
那是“牛至”，戴维 只值十美元的调味品
It was oregano, Dave. It was $10 worth of oregano.

85
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:52,600
可他认为是大麻
Yeah, well, your client thought it was marijuana.

86
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:55,440
我的当事人是个傻瓜，但傻并不违法
My client's a moron. That's not against the law.

87
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:58,900
凯菲，我同样得给上面一个交代 我必须起诉他
Kaffee, I got people to answer to just like you do. I'm gonna charge him.

88
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:01,150
告他私藏调味品吗？
With what, possession of a condiment?

89
00:09:01,190 --> 00:09:03,820
凯菲 我很想帮你了结此事…
Kaffee. I tried to help you out of this...

90
00:09:03,820 --> 00:09:06,620
但说到监禁时间，我会申请撤诉
but if you ask for jail time, I'm gonna file a motion to dismiss.

91
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:08,530
你办不到 我会办到的
You won't get it. I will get it.

92
00:09:08,580 --> 00:09:10,540
如果法官拒绝，我会申请…
And if the M.T.D. Is denied, I'll file a motion...

93
00:09:10,580 --> 00:09:13,460
要求作一次预先取证
seeking to obtain an evidentiary ruling in advance.

94
00:09:13,460 --> 00:09:15,870
然后反对审前监禁
And after that, I'm gonna file against pretrial confinement.

95
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:18,500
而你得花上三个月来做书面材料…
And you're gonna spend the next three months going blind on paperwork...

96
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:22,210
就因为一名二等通信兵购买并吸食调味品
because a signalman second-class bought and smoked a dime bag of oregano.

97
00:09:22,210 --> 00:09:24,800
再来，拿下二垒
Let's go! Let's get two!

98
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:28,300
Ｂ级轻罪，二十天监禁
B misdemeanor, 20 days in the brig.

99
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:30,640
Ｃ级轻罪，十五天受限处罚
C misdemeanor, 15 days restricted duty.

100
00:09:32,060 --> 00:09:34,140
不知道我凭什么要接受
I don't know why I'm agreeing to this.

101
00:09:34,140 --> 00:09:36,480
因为你比一般人要明智
'Cause you have wisdom beyond your years.

102
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:42,030
早
Morning.

103
00:09:42,070 --> 00:09:43,780
早，上校
Morning, Captain.

104
00:09:43,820 --> 00:09:45,400
孩子怎么样，山姆？
How's the baby, Sam?

105
00:09:45,450 --> 00:09:48,700
她大概随时在准备说出她的第一句话
I think she's getting ready to say her first word any day now.

106
00:09:48,700 --> 00:09:50,330
你怎么知道？
How can you tell?

107
00:09:50,370 --> 00:09:54,080
她看起来象有什么话要说
She just looks like she has something to say.

108
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:56,750
不好意思，抱歉我来晚了
Excuse me. I'm sorry I'm late.

109
00:09:56,750 --> 00:09:58,790
我知道你没什么好借口…
It's all right, Danny. I know you don't have a good excuse...

110
00:09:58,830 --> 00:10:00,920
所以不会强迫你找个坏借口
so I won't force you to come up with a bad one.

111
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:03,960
谢谢，长官 第一件事与你有关
Thank you, sir. This first one's for you.

112
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:07,380
看来你要飞黄腾达了
Seems you're moving up in the world.

113
00:10:07,380 --> 00:10:09,390
是师部要人
Been requested by Division.

114
00:10:10,220 --> 00:10:12,220
要我去哪？
Requested to do what?

115
00:10:12,220 --> 00:10:14,640
古巴，关达那摩湾
Guantanamo Bay, Cuba.

116
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:18,810
一名叫道森的海军准下士 非法使用所持武器…
A Marine corporal named Dawson illegally fires a round from his weapon...

117
00:10:18,810 --> 00:10:21,730
向界线另一边的古巴境内开枪
over the fenceline and into Cuban territory.

118
00:10:21,730 --> 00:10:23,690
什么“界线”？ 山姆
What's a fenceline? Sam.

119
00:10:23,690 --> 00:10:27,990
是一堵把好人和坏人分隔开来的高墙
A big wall separating the good guys from the bad guys.

120
00:10:27,990 --> 00:10:31,320
好学生 一等兵威廉・圣地亚哥…
Teacher's pet. P.F.C. William Santiago...

121
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:34,700
威胁要向海军调查部门举报道森
threatens to rat on Dawson to Naval Investigative Service.

122
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:36,790
道森和他的另一名队友…
Dawson and another member of his squad...

123
00:10:36,830 --> 00:10:40,880
一等兵劳登・多尼 进入圣地亚哥的房间…
P.F.C. Louden Downey, go into Santiago's room...

124
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:44,340
把他捆了起来，在他喉咙里塞了块抹布…
tie him up, stuff a rag down his throat...

125
00:10:44,340 --> 00:10:46,460
一小时后，圣地亚哥死了
and an hour later, Santiago's dead.

126
00:10:46,510 --> 00:10:50,260
主治医师说那块抹布经过了某种毒药处理
Attending physician says the rag was treated with some kind of toxin.

127
00:10:50,260 --> 00:10:51,510
他们下的毒？
They poisoned it?

128
00:10:51,590 --> 00:10:54,600
他们矢口否认 都说了些什么？
Not according to them. What did they say?

129
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:57,270
没说太多，他们明天会乘飞机过来…
Not much. They're being flown up here tomorrow...

130
00:10:57,270 --> 00:11:00,810
周三凌晨六点，你要去古巴呆一天…
and on Wednesday at 0600, you'll catch a transport down to Cuba for the day...

131
00:11:00,810 --> 00:11:02,810
看能找到些什么
to find out what you can.

132
00:11:02,810 --> 00:11:09,740
同时，去见见隶属内政部的 乔安妮・盖洛维少校
Meantime, go and see Lieutenant Commander Joanne Galloway... with Internal Affairs.

133
00:11:09,780 --> 00:11:11,360
有问题吗？
Any questions?

134
00:11:11,410 --> 00:11:15,580
去古巴的飞机…是在早上六点吗，长官？
Uh, the flight to Cuba... Was that 0600 in the morning, sir?

135
00:11:16,580 --> 00:11:19,040
看来重点在于师部要依条例行事
Seems important to Division that this one be handled by the book.

136
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:23,210
所以要我指派辩护律师，有没有志愿者？
So I'm assigning co-counsel. Any volunteers?

137
00:11:24,710 --> 00:11:27,800
不，我手头的案子太多了
I got a stack of papers on my desk about a mile high.

138
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:29,800
去帮帮凯菲吧 去干什么？
Work with Kaffee on this. Doing what?

139
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:32,090
凯菲只要四天就能摆平
Kaffee will have this done in about four days.

140
00:11:32,130 --> 00:11:35,470
做些管理方面的事
Doing various administrative things.

141
00:11:35,470 --> 00:11:37,430
备份什么的
Backup, whatever.

142
00:11:37,470 --> 00:11:40,100
换句话说，就是我没有任何责任了
In other words, I have no responsibilities here whatsoever.

143
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:41,640
没错
Right.

144
00:11:41,690 --> 00:11:43,810
正合我意
My kind of case.

145
00:11:44,860 --> 00:11:46,900
对
Right.

146
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:49,480
好的，但我要周三才能拿到报告
Okay, but I've got to have that report by Wednesday.

147
00:11:55,780 --> 00:11:58,580
嗨 稍等一下，嗨
Hi. Hold on. Hi.

148
00:11:58,580 --> 00:12:01,000
丹尼・凯菲，我是来见
Daniel Kaffee. I was told to me with, uh...

149
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:11,380
盖洛维少校的
Lieutenant Commander Galloway.

150
00:12:13,550 --> 00:12:14,800
来了解一下情况
About a briefing?

151
00:12:14,890 --> 00:12:16,850
我回头打给你
I'll call you back.

152
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:21,520
你是师部指定的律师？
You're the attorney Division assigned?

153
00:12:22,390 --> 00:12:24,350
我是首席律师，这是山姆
I'm lead counsel. This is Sam Weinberg.

154
00:12:24,390 --> 00:12:26,610
我对此事不负任何责任
I have no responsibilities here whatsoever.

155
00:12:26,610 --> 00:12:28,820
进来吧，请坐
Come in, please. Have a seat.

156
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:41,450
中尉，你在海军服役多久了？
Lieutenant, how long have you been in the Navy?

157
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:45,040
快九个月了
Going on nine months now.

158
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:47,750
你从律师学校毕业多久了？
And how long have you been out of law school?

159
00:12:48,880 --> 00:12:50,380
一年多一点
A little over a year.

160
00:12:50,420 --> 00:12:52,550
明白了
I see.

161
00:12:53,260 --> 00:12:54,880
我做错什么了吗？
Have I done something wrong?

162
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:57,640
不，只是我请求师部指派律师时…
It's just that when I petition Division to have counsel assigned...

163
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:59,720
还指望会被认真对待
I was hoping I'd be taken seriously.

164
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:02,470
恕我冒昧，实际上确实如此
No offense taken, in case you were wondering.

165
00:13:02,470 --> 00:13:06,850
凯菲中尉被公认是 我们部门最会打官司的人
Commander, Lieutenant Kaffee is generally... considered the best litigator in our office.

166
00:13:06,850 --> 00:13:10,150
九个月内他成功地处理过四十四起案件
He's successfully plea-bargained 44 cases in nine months.

167
00:13:10,150 --> 00:13:12,230
再多一件就能奖一套牛排刀
One more, I get a set of steak knives.

168
00:13:12,230 --> 00:13:14,070
你上过庭吗？
Have you ever been in a courtroom?

169
00:13:14,110 --> 00:13:16,700
驾照被吊销时上过一次
I once had my driver's license suspended.

170
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:18,740
以我的看法，如果闹上法庭…
Commander, from what I understand, if this thing goes to court...

171
00:13:18,740 --> 00:13:20,950
他们需要的就不是律师而是牧师
they won't need a lawyer, they'll need a priest.

172
00:13:21,530 --> 00:13:23,540
不，他们需要的是律师
No, they'll need a lawyer.

173
00:13:24,540 --> 00:13:26,660
已经联系过道森的家人
Dawson's family's been contacted.

174
00:13:26,660 --> 00:13:30,290
多尼最亲近的人是他姨妈詹妮・米勒
Downey's closest living relative is Ginny Miller, his aunt.

175
00:13:30,290 --> 00:13:33,250
还没和她联系过，需要我来处理吗？
She hasn't been contacted yet. Would you like me to take care of that?

176
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:34,800
如果你愿意的话
If you feel like it.

177
00:13:36,550 --> 00:13:38,510
你到那要见的人…
One of the people you'll be seeing down there...

178
00:13:38,550 --> 00:13:40,640
是基地指挥官内森・杰赛普上校
is the barracks C.O., Colonel Nathan Jessup.

179
00:13:40,680 --> 00:13:42,850
我猜你也听说过他
I assume you've heard of him.

180
00:13:42,890 --> 00:13:44,350
谁没听说过呢？
Who hasn't?

181
00:13:45,390 --> 00:13:48,060
他最近上了报，可能被任命为…
He's been in the papers lately. He's expected to be appointed...

182
00:13:48,060 --> 00:13:50,940
国家安全委员会的执行主管
director of operations of National Security Council.

183
00:13:50,940 --> 00:13:52,270
是吗？ 这些信…
Really? These are the letters...

184
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:54,690
是圣地亚哥在关达那摩写的
that Santiago wrote in his eight months at Gitmo.

185
00:13:54,690 --> 00:13:57,240
就是关达那摩湾 我知道
That's Guantanamo Bay. I knew that one.

186
00:13:57,240 --> 00:14:00,820
他曾写给舰队司令 写给海军指挥部的指挥官…
He wrote to the fleet commander to the commandant of the Marine Corps.

187
00:14:00,820 --> 00:14:03,830
甚至议员，他希望能调离基地
Even his senator. He wanted to be transferred off the base.

188
00:14:03,830 --> 00:14:07,790
但没人理会，你在听吗？
No one was listening. Are you with me? Yeah.

189
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:11,000
最后，他写给海军调查处…
Finally, he wrote to the Naval Investigative Service...

190
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:14,130
以提供道森准下士非法开枪的资料…
where he offered information about Corporal Dawson's fenceline shooting...

191
00:14:14,130 --> 00:14:16,840
作为调动的交换条件
in exchange for a transfer.

192
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:19,550
很好，就这些吗？
Right. Is that all?

193
00:14:19,550 --> 00:14:21,510
中尉，这些信似乎提供了…
Lieutenant, this letter makes it look like...

194
00:14:21,550 --> 00:14:24,050
你当事人杀害圣地亚哥的动机
your client had a motive to kill Santiago.

195
00:14:24,050 --> 00:14:27,390
明白了，圣地亚哥是谁？
Got you. And Santiago is who?

196
00:14:27,390 --> 00:14:29,020
被害人
The victim.

197
00:14:29,060 --> 00:14:31,770
写下来，可否假设这些信…
Write that down. Am I correct to assume these letters...

198
00:14:31,770 --> 00:14:34,730
描述的并非关达那摩的光彩之处呢？
don't paint a flattering picture of Marine Corps life at Guantanamo Bay?

199
00:14:34,730 --> 00:14:36,230
对，在 进一步地假设…
Yes, among... Am I further right in assuming...

200
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:40,150
调查此事有没有可能 令安全委员会的人难堪呢？
investigation of this incident might embarrass the Security Council guy?

201
00:14:40,150 --> 00:14:42,240
杰赛普上校 十二年
Colonel Jessup. Twelve years.

202
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:44,160
什么？
Sorry?

203
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:46,490
争取判为共谋及行为不当
I'll get them to drop the conspiracy and conduct unbecoming.

204
00:14:46,490 --> 00:14:48,330
刑期十二年
Twelve years.

205
00:14:48,330 --> 00:14:52,040
你没和证人谈过也没看过一页档案
You haven't talked to a witness or looked at a piece of paper.

206
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:54,170
很意外，对吧？
Pretty impressive, huh?

207
00:14:54,170 --> 00:14:55,920
你应该深入调查
You're gonna have to go deeper than that.

208
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:58,800
你有什么权限是我应该知道的？
Do you have some sort of jurisdiction here that I should know about?

209
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:01,680
我的工作就是确保你干好你的工作
My job is to make sure that you do your job.

210
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:03,680
我是内政部的特别律师…
I'm special counsel for Internal Affairs...

211
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:07,180
所以我的权限可说就是看着你
so my jurisdiction's pretty much in your face.

212
00:15:09,220 --> 00:15:12,350
看看这些信 希望你从古巴回来能向我汇报
Read the letters. I'll expect your report when you return from Cuba.

213
00:15:12,350 --> 00:15:15,110
当然 你可以走了
Sure. You're dismissed.

214
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:19,690
我总是忘了这个部分
I always forget that part.

215
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:24,240
他有点分心
He's a little preoccupied.

216
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:27,490
下周要和贝赛斯塔医院队比赛
Team's playing Bethesda Medical next week.

217
00:15:27,490 --> 00:15:29,450
告诉他在那可别抖机灵
Tell your friend not to get cute down there.

218
00:15:29,490 --> 00:15:31,870
关达那摩的海军可不好惹
The Marines in Guantanamo are fanatical.

219
00:15:31,910 --> 00:15:33,210
哪方面？
About what?

220
00:15:33,920 --> 00:15:35,630
海军方面
About being Marines.

221
00:15:35,670 --> 00:15:36,710
尊敬的长官…
Dear sir...

222
00:15:36,750 --> 00:15:39,590
我是一等兵威廉・Ｔ・圣地亚哥
my name is P.F.C. William T. Santiago.

223
00:15:39,590 --> 00:15:45,260
是隶属海军陆战队Ｗ步兵警卫连二Ｂ排 的一名海军陆战队员
I'm a Marine stationed at Marine barracks... Rifle Security Company Windward, Second Platoon Bravo.

224
00:15:45,260 --> 00:15:49,140
我写信是想告知您 我在古巴单位上遇到的麻烦…
I'm writing to inform you of my problems with my unit here in Cuba...

225
00:15:49,140 --> 00:15:50,810
并请求您的帮助
and to ask for your help.

226
00:15:50,850 --> 00:15:54,270
我之前曾因某种原因在训练时晕倒…
I've fallen out on runs before for several reasons...

227
00:15:54,270 --> 00:15:56,270
感觉象是头晕或恶心
such as feeling dizzy or nauseated.

228
00:15:56,270 --> 00:16:02,690
但在五月十八日，从一座小石山下来时 我落后了大约二到三十码
But on May 18, I'd fallen back about 20 or 30 yards... going down a rocky unstable hill.

229
00:16:02,690 --> 00:16:05,740
我的中士抓住我并把我向山下推
My sergeant grabbed me and pushed me down the hill.

230
00:16:05,740 --> 00:16:09,700
然后我眼前一黑，摔倒在地上
Then I saw all black, and the last thing I remembered was hitting the deck.

231
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:13,160
到医院后我被告知只是中暑而已
I was brought to the hospital where I was told I just had heat exhaustion.

232
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:14,790
我请求您帮助我
I ask you to help me.

233
00:16:14,830 --> 00:16:18,380
求您，长官，我想要调离步兵警卫连
Please, sir. I just need to be transferred out of R.S.C.

234
00:16:18,380 --> 00:16:22,920
美国海军陆战队一等兵 威廉・Ｔ・圣地亚哥 谨启
Sincerely, P.F.C. William T. Santiago... U.S. Marine Corps.

235
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:25,970
另附，作为我调离基地的交换条件…
P.S. In exchange for my transfer off the base...

236
00:16:25,970 --> 00:16:28,010
我可以向您提供有关
I'm willing to provide you with information about...

237
00:16:28,010 --> 00:16:32,430
“八月二日夜间向境外非法开枪事件” 的信息
"The illegal fenceline shooting that occurred the night of August 2."

238
00:16:33,220 --> 00:16:37,690
这个该死的一等兵 威廉・圣地亚哥是什么人？
Who the fuck is P.F.C. William T. Santiago?

239
00:16:37,690 --> 00:16:40,860
是隶属第二Ｂ排的一名一等兵，长官
Private Santiago is a member of Second Platoon Bravo, sir.

240
00:16:40,860 --> 00:16:45,110
是吗，他似乎在“香格里拉” 呆得很不开心啊…
Yeah. Well, apparently he's not very happy down here in Shangri-la...

241
00:16:45,110 --> 00:16:50,240
因为他给圣诞老人之外的所有人写信 请求调离
because he's written letters to everybody but Santa Claus... asking for a transfer.

242
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:53,290
而且还要披露一桩违纪开枪事件
And now he's telling tales about a fenceline shooting.

243
00:16:54,250 --> 00:16:55,870
马修？
Matthew?

244
00:16:55,910 --> 00:16:58,540
我感到震惊，长官
I'm appalled, sir.

245
00:16:59,290 --> 00:17:01,790
你感到震惊
You're appalled.

246
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:06,380
这小子越级上报还出卖自己的队友…
This kid broke the chain of command and ratted on a member of his unit...

247
00:17:06,380 --> 00:17:09,260
谎称他作为一名海军陆战队员…
to say nothing of the fact that he is a U.S. Marine...

248
00:17:09,260 --> 00:17:14,930
就算没有中暑虚脱，似乎也无法参加训练
and it would appear he can't run from here to there... without collapsing from heat exhaustion.

249
00:17:14,930 --> 00:17:18,270
Ｂ排是他妈的怎么回事，马修？
What the fuck is going on in Bravo Company, Matthew?

250
00:17:18,270 --> 00:17:21,360
上校，我想这事最好还是等私下再谈
Colonel, I think it would be better to hold this discussion in private.

251
00:17:21,360 --> 00:17:25,570
没必要，上校，我可以处理好这事，长官
That won't be necessary, Colonel. I can handle the situation, sir.

252
00:17:25,570 --> 00:17:29,360
象你处理柯蒂斯・贝尔那样吗？ 别打断我，上尉
The same way you handled Curtis Bell? Don't interrupt me, Lieutenant!

253
00:17:29,360 --> 00:17:32,990
我还是你的上级 而我是你的上级，马修
I'm still your superior officer. And I'm yours, Matthew.

254
00:17:35,080 --> 00:17:38,210
我想知道我们该如何处理这事
I wanna know what we're going to do about this.

255
00:17:38,210 --> 00:17:41,210
我认为圣地亚哥应该马上调离基地
I think Santiago should be transferred off the base immediately.

256
00:17:41,210 --> 00:17:42,880
他那样差劲吗？
He's that bad, huh?

257
00:17:42,920 --> 00:17:45,090
除此之外，信的内容一传出去…
Not only that. But word of this letter is bound to get out.

258
00:17:45,130 --> 00:17:47,090
他可就有得受了
He's gonna get his ass whipped.

259
00:17:47,130 --> 00:17:51,220
调走圣地亚哥
Hmm. Transfer Santiago.

260
00:17:51,220 --> 00:17:54,810
好吧，我相信你是对的
Yes. I'm sure you're right.

261
00:17:54,810 --> 00:17:57,390
我相信就该这么办
I'm sure that's the thing to do.

262
00:17:59,020 --> 00:18:02,980
等等，我有个更好的主意
Wait. I've got a better idea.

263
00:18:02,980 --> 00:18:06,020
我们把整个班都调离基地
Let's transfer the whole squad off the base.

264
00:18:06,020 --> 00:18:09,190
我们…接下来考虑，Ｗ
Let's... On second thought, Windward...

265
00:18:09,190 --> 00:18:13,490
我们将整个Ｗ连都调离基地
Let's transfer the whole Windward Division off the base.

266
00:18:13,490 --> 00:18:17,200
约翰，到外边去把弟兄们都从边境带走
John, go on out there and get those boys down off the fence.

267
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:19,750
他们正在收拾行李，汤姆
They're packing their bags. Tom.

268
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:23,420
长官 给我接总统
Sir. Get me the president on the phone.

269
00:18:23,420 --> 00:18:26,590
我们要放弃古巴的军事基地
We're surrendering our position in Cuba.

270
00:18:26,590 --> 00:18:29,090
是，长官 等等，汤姆
Yes, sir. Wait a minute, Tom.

271
00:18:29,090 --> 00:18:31,090
先不要接总统
Don't get the president just yet.

272
00:18:31,090 --> 00:18:34,800
也许我们该考虑一下
Maybe we should consider this for a second.

273
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:37,140
出去吧，汤姆 是，长官
Dismissed, Tom. Yes, sir.

274
00:18:38,180 --> 00:18:42,100
也许…我刚才是胡说八道
Maybe... and I'm just spit-balling here...

275
00:18:42,100 --> 00:18:47,230
也许作为长官我们有责任训练圣地亚哥
Maybe we have a responsibility as officers to train Santiago.

276
00:18:47,230 --> 00:18:51,440
也许作为长官我们有责任为国家…
Maybe we as officers have a responsibility to this country...

277
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:54,820
看着那些肩负国家安全重任的人…
to see that the men and women charged with its security...

278
00:18:54,820 --> 00:18:56,950
受到专业的训练
are trained professionals.

279
00:18:56,950 --> 00:19:00,950
没错，我确信在什么地方看到过这些话
Yes, I'm certain that I read that somewhere once.

280
00:19:00,950 --> 00:19:03,620
我现在想的是，马金森中校…
And now I'm thinking, Colonel Markinson...

281
00:19:03,620 --> 00:19:08,040
你提议调走圣地亚哥…
that your suggestion of transferring Santiago...

282
00:19:08,040 --> 00:19:11,340
痛快固然是痛快…
while expeditious and certainly painless...

283
00:19:11,340 --> 00:19:16,890
但恐怕不是美国人处理事情的方式
might not be, in a manner of speaking... the American way.

284
00:19:16,890 --> 00:19:19,760
圣地亚哥必须留在这
Santiago stays where he is.

285
00:19:21,390 --> 00:19:23,770
我们要训练这个小伙子
We're gonna train the lad.

286
00:19:23,810 --> 00:19:26,810
约翰，由你负责
John, you're in charge.

287
00:19:26,810 --> 00:19:33,780
如果圣地亚哥下次的训练和实习报告 还达不到四-六-四-六的话
Santiago doesn't make 4-6-4-6... on his next proficiency and conduct report...

288
00:19:33,780 --> 00:19:36,160
我唯你是问
I'm going to blame you.

289
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:38,870
我会毙了你 是，长官
Then I'm going to kill you. Yes, sir.

290
00:19:38,870 --> 00:19:41,540
我认为这是个错误，上校
I think that's a mistake, Colonel.

291
00:19:42,870 --> 00:19:47,080
马修，我想我有些话要和你私下聊聊
Matthew, I think I will have that word in private with you now.

292
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:51,130
约翰，就这样吧 我们午饭时在军官俱乐部碰头…
John, that's all. Why don't we meet at the "O" club and have lunch...

293
00:19:51,130 --> 00:19:53,800
讨论怎样训练小威廉
and we'll talk about the training of young William?

294
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:56,590
我很乐意听听您的建议，长官
I'd be delighted to hear any suggestions that you might have, sir.

295
00:19:56,590 --> 00:19:58,590
出去吧 是，长官
Dismissed. Yes, sir.

296
00:20:02,350 --> 00:20:05,640
马修，请坐下
Matthew, sit down. Please.

297
00:20:10,730 --> 00:20:13,400
你觉得肯德瑞克怎么样？
What doyou think of Kendrick?

298
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:15,280
我对他的看法毫无
My opinion of him has nothing to do...

299
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:18,530
就我个人而言我觉得他不太靠得住…
I think he's pretty much of a weasel myself...

300
00:20:18,530 --> 00:20:20,570
但他是个很不错的军官
but he's an awfully good officer.

301
00:20:20,570 --> 00:20:25,080
我们最终的目的 就是要训练一支最好的海军陆战队
And in the end, we see eye-to-eye on the best way to run a Marine Corps unit.

302
00:20:25,080 --> 00:20:28,710
保家卫国是我们份内的事，马修
We're in the business of saving lives, Matthew.

303
00:20:28,710 --> 00:20:32,460
这是我们该认真对待的职责
That is a responsibility that we have to take pretty seriously.

304
00:20:32,460 --> 00:20:36,880
我相信对于这样一名 不称职的海军陆战队员…
And I believe that taking a Marine who is not quite up to the job...

305
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:39,430
把他送到其他单位…
and shipping him off to another assignment...

306
00:20:39,430 --> 00:20:41,470
是拿生命当儿戏
puts lives in danger.

307
00:20:42,180 --> 00:20:44,520
坐下，马修
Sit down, Matthew.

308
00:20:53,980 --> 00:20:56,070
想想过去吧
We go back a while.

309
00:20:56,110 --> 00:20:59,660
我们一同上军校，一同接受任命
We went to the Academy together. We were commissioned together.

310
00:20:59,660 --> 00:21:02,200
一同经历过越战
We did our tours in Vietnam together.

311
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:04,620
只不过我得到的一系列提升…
But I've been promoted up through the chain...

312
00:21:04,660 --> 00:21:07,620
比起你来要运气好一些
with greater speed and success than you have.

313
00:21:07,620 --> 00:21:10,670
现在，如果是因为这个…
Now, if that's a source of tension...

314
00:21:10,670 --> 00:21:12,670
令你感到难堪…
or embarrassment foryou...

315
00:21:12,670 --> 00:21:14,500
我不会太在意
I don't give a shit.

316
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:19,800
我们的职责性命攸关，马金森中校
We're in the business of saving lives, Lieutenant Colonel Markinson.

317
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:24,010
永远别在其他军官面前质疑我的命令
Don't ever question my orders in front of another officer.

318
00:21:43,910 --> 00:21:45,370
所有材料都准备好了
All the paperwork's in order.

319
00:21:46,410 --> 00:21:48,410
过去吧 是，长官
Step over there. Yes, sir.

320
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:55,880
哈罗德，这就是华盛顿特区？
Hal, is this Washington, D. C?

321
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:57,550
对，我们走吧
All right. Let's move.

322
00:21:57,590 --> 00:21:59,050
是，长官
Yes, sir.

323
00:22:05,890 --> 00:22:08,890
这一击能拿满分 打扰一下
Got all of that one. Excuse me.

324
00:22:08,890 --> 00:22:12,560
我想和你谈谈道森和多尼的事
I wanted to talk to you about Corporal Dawson and Private Downey.

325
00:22:12,560 --> 00:22:15,230
什么？ 道森和多尼
Say again? Dawson and Downey.

326
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:18,480
这些名字听起来和我有点关系
Those names sound like they should mean something to me...

327
00:22:18,530 --> 00:22:21,400
道森，多尼…你的当事人
Dawson, Downey... your clients.

328
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:24,780
古巴的事，对了，道森和多尼，没错
The Cuba thing. Yes! Dawson and Downey. Right.

329
00:22:27,910 --> 00:22:30,040
我又做错了什么吗？
I've done something wrong again, haven't I?

330
00:22:30,040 --> 00:22:34,960
我只是奇怪那两个人一早就被关押的同时 他们的律师却在打球
I was just wondering why two guys have been locked up... since this morning while their lawyer's outside hitting a ball.

331
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:38,630
我们需要训练
We need the practice.

332
00:22:38,630 --> 00:22:40,250
这并不好笑
That wasn't funny.

333
00:22:41,010 --> 00:22:42,380
有一点点好笑
It was a little funny.

334
00:22:42,420 --> 00:22:47,760
如果我向你的上司建议另外指派律师 会不会令你感到羞辱？
Would you be very insulted if I recommended to your supervisor... that he assign different counsel?

335
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:51,310
理由呢？ 我认为你不适合办理此案
Why? I don't think you're fit to handle it.

336
00:22:51,310 --> 00:22:55,140
你根本不了解我 一般来说，总得花些时间…
You don't even know me. Ordinarily, it takes someone hours...

337
00:22:55,140 --> 00:22:57,860
来了解我适不适合作辩护律师
to discover I'm not fit to handle a defense.

338
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:02,990
得了吧，这未免太可笑了
Oh, come on. That was damn funny.

339
00:23:05,860 --> 00:23:07,070
你错了
You're wrong.

340
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:10,160
我了解你
I do know you.

341
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:14,080
丹尼・艾勒斯塔・凯菲 一九六四年六月八日生于…
Daniel Alistair Kaffee, born June 8, 1964...

342
00:23:14,080 --> 00:23:16,080
波士顿仁爱医院
at Boston Mercy Hospital.

343
00:23:16,080 --> 00:23:17,460
你父亲莱昂内尔・凯菲…
Your father's Lionel Kaffee...

344
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:21,050
曾担任海军军法检察官及美国司法部长
former Navy judge advocate and attorney general of the United States.

345
00:23:21,050 --> 00:23:22,670
一九八五年去世
Died 1985.

346
00:23:22,710 --> 00:23:25,510
你上过哈佛法学院，毕业后加入海军…
You went to Harvard law. Then you joined the Navy...

347
00:23:25,510 --> 00:23:28,340
也许这是出于你父亲的要求
probably because that's what your father wanted you to do.

348
00:23:28,340 --> 00:23:31,760
所以现在你只想在海军军法署混上三年
And now you're just treading water for three years in the JAG Corps.

349
00:23:31,760 --> 00:23:35,310
混到退役找一份真正的工作
Just laying low till you can get out and get a real job.

350
00:23:35,310 --> 00:23:38,940
如果是这样的话也无可厚非 我不会告诉任何人
If that's the situation, that's fine. I won't tell anyone.

351
00:23:38,940 --> 00:23:44,280
但我认为如果象求快，耍小聪明的 波斯商贩那样来对待本案…
But it's my feeling that if this case is handled in the same... fast-food, slick-ass, Persian bazaar manner...

352
00:23:44,280 --> 00:23:46,240
用你应付其他案子的那一套…
with which you seem to handle everything else...

353
00:23:46,280 --> 00:23:47,950
就会漏掉一些东西
then something's gonna get missed.

354
00:23:47,990 --> 00:23:50,740
如果道森和多尼因为他们的律师…
And I wouldn't be doing my job if I allowed Dawson and Downey...

355
00:23:50,740 --> 00:23:53,370
预先就盘算不尽全力而使他们…
to spend any more time in prison than absolutely necessary...

356
00:23:53,370 --> 00:23:56,540
多受哪怕一天的牢狱之灾，就是我的失职
because their attorney had predetermined the path of least resistance.

357
00:24:01,790 --> 00:24:04,340
真令我兴奋，少校
I'm sexually aroused, Commander.

358
00:24:04,960 --> 00:24:07,300
我不相信他们会杀人
I don't think your clients murdered anyone.

359
00:24:07,300 --> 00:24:08,720
理由根据呢？
What are you basing this on?

360
00:24:08,760 --> 00:24:10,590
没有动机
There was no intent.

361
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:13,510
医检报告说圣地亚哥死于窒息…
The doctor's report says Santiago died of asphyxiation...

362
00:24:13,510 --> 00:24:15,520
是因为急性乳酸中毒…
brought on by acute lactic acidosis...

363
00:24:15,520 --> 00:24:19,440
而这种症状很容易让人联想到是人为的
and that the nature of the acidosis strongly suggests poison.

364
00:24:19,440 --> 00:24:22,270
我不知道这表示什么，但听起来相当不妙
I don't know what any of that means, but it sounds pretty bad.

365
00:24:22,270 --> 00:24:24,230
圣地亚哥是死于凌晨一点
Santiago died at 1:00 a.m.

366
00:24:24,270 --> 00:24:27,150
三点时医生还无法确定死因
At 3:00, the doctor wasn't able to determine the cause of death.

367
00:24:27,150 --> 00:24:29,450
两小时后，他说是死于中毒
Two hours later, he said it was poison.

368
00:24:29,450 --> 00:24:32,030
哦，我现在懂你的意思了
Oh, now I see what you're saying.

369
00:24:32,030 --> 00:24:35,410
肯定是图书馆的普拉姆教授 用烛台打死了他
It had to be Professor Plum in the library with a candlestick.

370
00:24:35,410 --> 00:24:37,950
我去和你的上司谈好了 行啊
I'm gonna talk to your supervisor. Okay.

371
00:24:37,950 --> 00:24:40,170
直接去宾州林荫大道
Go straight up Pennsylvania Avenue.

372
00:24:40,210 --> 00:24:42,750
找一幢有柱子的白色宫殿
It's the big white house with the pillars in front.

373
00:24:42,750 --> 00:24:46,050
谢了 我觉得你的运气不会太好
Thank you. I don't think you'll have much luck.

374
00:24:46,050 --> 00:24:47,510
我是由师部任命的
I was assigned by Division.

375
00:24:47,550 --> 00:24:50,680
那儿有人认为我是个很不错的律师
Somebody over there thinks I'm a pretty good lawyer.

376
00:24:50,680 --> 00:24:54,220
我对你的专注和热情表示敬佩…
So while I appreciate your interest and admire your enthusiasm...

377
00:24:54,220 --> 00:24:56,770
但我认为我自己能处理好这事
I think I can handle things myself.

378
00:24:56,770 --> 00:24:58,930
知道什么是“红色条规”吗？
You know what a Code Red is?

379
00:25:02,730 --> 00:25:04,940
真遗憾
What a pity.

380
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:17,620
早，长官 早
Morning, sir. Morning.

381
00:25:18,500 --> 00:25:20,210
长官到，立正
Officer on deck!

382
00:25:20,250 --> 00:25:22,460
长官，哈罗德・道森准下士，长官
Sir, Lance Corporal Harold W. Dawson, sir!

383
00:25:22,460 --> 00:25:24,710
隶属Ｗ步兵警卫连二Ｂ排
Rifle Security Company Windward, Second Platoon Bravo.

384
00:25:24,750 --> 00:25:28,090
曾经违纪并且 不能和队友好好相处的哈罗德？
Someone hasn't been working and playing well with others, Harold.

385
00:25:28,090 --> 00:25:30,050
长官，是的，长官
Sir, yes, sir!

386
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:34,180
长官，一等兵劳登・多尼，长官
Sir, P.F.C. Louden Downey, sir!

387
00:25:35,640 --> 00:25:38,310
我是丹尼・凯菲，这是山姆・温伯格
I'm Daniel Kaffee. This is Sam Weinberg.

388
00:25:38,310 --> 00:25:39,470
坐吧
Sit down.

389
00:25:46,770 --> 00:25:49,650
这是你的签名？ 是的，长官
This your signature? Yes, sir.

390
00:25:49,650 --> 00:25:51,490
用不着叫我长官，这是你的签名吗？
You don't have to call me "sir." Is this your signature?

391
00:25:51,490 --> 00:25:52,700
长官，是的，长官
Sir, yes, sir.

392
00:25:52,780 --> 00:25:55,700
完全没必要一句话叫两次长官
You certainly don't need to do it twice in one sentence.

393
00:25:55,700 --> 00:25:59,370
什么是“红色条规”？ 是一种训诫条规
What's a Code Red? It is a disciplinary engagement.

394
00:25:59,370 --> 00:26:00,830
表示什么？
What's that mean?

395
00:26:00,870 --> 00:26:04,830
如果有陆战队员掉队 就可以用来帮助这个队员跟上队伍
A Marine falls out of line, it's up to the men in his unit to get him on track.

396
00:26:04,830 --> 00:26:08,380
“红色条规”具体是什么花样？ 长官？
What's a garden variety Code Red? Sir?

397
00:26:08,380 --> 00:26:12,380
哈罗德，你这么叫会让我 忍不住回头看是不是我爸爸来了
Harold, you say, "sir," and I turn around and look for my father.

398
00:26:12,380 --> 00:26:15,010
叫我丹尼，凯菲都行
Danny, Daniel, Kaffee.

399
00:26:15,050 --> 00:26:18,180
说明白点 “红色条规”大概是什么意思？
Garden variety. Typical. What's basic Code Red?

400
00:26:18,180 --> 00:26:20,890
长官，比如有队员拒绝按规定洗澡…
Sir, a Marine refuses to bathe on a regular basis...

401
00:26:20,890 --> 00:26:23,560
队友就会给他洗个“军用澡”
the men in his squad will give him a G.I. Shower.

402
00:26:23,560 --> 00:26:24,810
怎么个洗法？
What's that?

403
00:26:24,890 --> 00:26:27,480
用刷子，钢丝刷
Scrub brushes, Brillo pads, steel wool.

404
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:28,810
太妙了
Beautiful.

405
00:26:28,900 --> 00:26:31,480
圣地亚哥接受的也是“红色条规”吗？
Was the attack on Santiago a Code Red?

406
00:26:31,480 --> 00:26:33,190
是的，长官
Yes, sir.

407
00:26:38,410 --> 00:26:41,660
他从不说话吗？
Does he ever talk?

408
00:26:41,660 --> 00:26:45,040
长官，一等兵多尼会回答你的所有问题
Sir, P.F.C. Downey will answer any direct questions you ask him.

409
00:26:45,040 --> 00:26:46,620
非？
Swell.

410
00:26:48,210 --> 00:26:51,050
多尼，你塞进圣地亚哥嘴里的抹布
Private Downey, the rag you stuffed in Santiago's mouth...

411
00:26:51,050 --> 00:26:53,010
有没有毒？ 没有，长官
Was there poison on it? No, sir.

412
00:26:53,050 --> 00:26:55,590
上光剂，松节油，防冻剂之类？
Silver polish, turpentine, antifreeze?

413
00:26:55,590 --> 00:26:58,050
没有，长官，我们只是想给他剃头
No, sir. We were just gonna shave his head, sir.

414
00:26:58,050 --> 00:27:00,930
突然之间
When all of the sudden...

415
00:27:00,930 --> 00:27:03,430
我们看到他的嘴在流血…
We saw blood dripping down his mouth...

416
00:27:03,430 --> 00:27:07,690
我们撕掉胶布，他满脸都是血，长官
and we pulled the tape off and there was blood all down his face, sir.

417
00:27:07,690 --> 00:27:11,020
接着道森准下士就打电话叫了救护车
That's when Lance Corporal Dawson called the ambulance.

418
00:27:11,020 --> 00:27:12,770
有人看到你打电话吗？
Did anyone see you call the ambulance?

419
00:27:14,740 --> 00:27:15,900
没有，长官
No, sir.

420
00:27:18,410 --> 00:27:20,160
救护车来时你在那吗？
Were you there when the ambulance got there?

421
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:22,620
是的，长官，这时我们已经被拘捕
Yes, sir. That's when we were taken under arrest.

422
00:27:22,660 --> 00:27:27,620
八月二日夜间 你是否在边界向古巴境内开过枪？
The night of August 2, did you fire a shot across the fenceline into Cuba?

423
00:27:29,370 --> 00:27:30,830
是的，长官 为什么？
Yes, sir. Why?

424
00:27:30,880 --> 00:27:33,750
我的对象在动手，长官 对象？
My mirror engaged, sir. His mirror?

425
00:27:33,750 --> 00:27:37,670
每个美军岗哨都有一个对应的古巴岗哨 称为“对象”
Every American sentry post has a Cuban counterpart, called "mirrors."

426
00:27:37,670 --> 00:27:41,220
下士的意思是他的对象想向他开枪
Lance Corporal's claiming that his mirror was about to fire at him.

427
00:27:41,220 --> 00:27:43,760
圣地亚哥写信给海军调查处…
Santiago's letter to the N.I. S...

428
00:27:43,760 --> 00:27:46,310
说你违纪开枪
said you fired illegally.

429
00:27:46,310 --> 00:27:50,310
他说那个人，那个对象
He's saying that the guy, the mirror...

430
00:27:50,310 --> 00:27:51,940
决没有任何行动
He never made a move.

431
00:27:58,360 --> 00:28:00,320
你明白我在说什么吗？
You see what I'm getting at?

432
00:28:01,360 --> 00:28:04,660
既然圣地亚哥和你没有私怨 为何对他执行“红色条规”？
If Santiago didn't have anything on you, then why did you give him a Code Red?

433
00:28:04,660 --> 00:28:06,910
因为他越级上报，长官
'Cause he broke the chain of command, sir.

434
00:28:06,910 --> 00:28:09,960
什么？ 他撇开了自己的单位，长官
He what? He went outside of his unit, sir.

435
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:12,420
如果他有问题，应该先向我报告，长官
If he had a problem, he should have spoken to me, sir.

436
00:28:12,420 --> 00:28:15,550
然后才是中士，指挥官 好了好了
Then his sergeant, then commander... Yeah. All right.

437
00:28:15,550 --> 00:28:18,260
你袭击他时是否意图杀死他？
Did you assault Santiago with the intent of killing him?

438
00:28:18,260 --> 00:28:19,970
没有，长官 意图何在？
No, sir. What was your intent?

439
00:28:20,010 --> 00:28:22,840
教训他，长官 教训他什么？
To train him, sir. Train him to do what?

440
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:27,430
考虑个人之前先考虑集体…要尊重秩序
Train him to think of his unit before himself... to respect the code.

441
00:28:27,430 --> 00:28:29,270
什么秩序？
What's the code?

442
00:28:29,310 --> 00:28:31,350
分队，军团，上帝，国家
Unit, Corps, God, Country.

443
00:28:31,350 --> 00:28:32,650
能再说一次吗？
I beg your pardon?

444
00:28:32,690 --> 00:28:38,230
依次为分队、军团、上帝、国家，长官
Unit, Corps, God, Country, sir.

445
00:28:53,960 --> 00:28:56,920
美国政府…
The government of the United States...

446
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:59,800
要指控你俩谋杀…
wants to charge you two with murder...

447
00:28:59,800 --> 00:29:05,510
你想让我对起诉人说什么 分队，军团，上帝，国家吗？
and you want me to go to the prosecutor... with "Unit, Corps, God, Country"?

448
00:29:05,510 --> 00:29:07,560
这是我们的规矩，长官
That's our code, sir.

449
00:29:11,520 --> 00:29:13,350
你们的规矩
It's your code.

450
00:29:13,390 --> 00:29:16,020
我们还会来
We'll be back.

451
00:29:16,020 --> 00:29:19,980
有什么需要吗？ 书，纸张，香烟，火腿三明治？
You guys need anything... books, papers, cigarettes, ham sandwich?

452
00:29:19,980 --> 00:29:22,320
长官，不用，谢谢，长官
Sir, no, thank you, sir.

453
00:29:22,360 --> 00:29:26,200
哈罗德，我觉得你最好开始明白一件事
Harold, I think there's a concept you better start warming up to.

454
00:29:26,200 --> 00:29:27,490
长官？
Sir?

455
00:29:27,530 --> 00:29:30,200
我是你们唯一的朋友
I'm the only friend you've got.

456
00:29:43,420 --> 00:29:44,510
丹尼・凯菲
Daniel Kaffee

457
00:29:45,300 --> 00:29:46,590
微笑的杰克・罗斯
Smiling Jack Ross.

458
00:29:46,640 --> 00:29:48,930
欢迎你的加入 是吗？
Welcome to the big time. You think so?

459
00:29:48,930 --> 00:29:52,890
为道森和多尼着想 但愿你的专业水平高于垒球水平
Let's hope, for Dawson and Downey, you practice law better than play softball.

460
00:29:52,890 --> 00:29:56,480
真为他俩遗憾 我没有什么能比垒球更擅长
Unfortunately for those two, I don't do anything better than play softball.

461
00:29:56,480 --> 00:29:58,020
我走了，简奈儿 再见
I'm out of here, Janelle. Bye.

462
00:29:58,110 --> 00:30:00,440
等我从古巴回来再见 代我向卡斯特罗问好
See you when I get back from Cuba. Say hi to Castro for me.

463
00:30:00,440 --> 00:30:02,820
没问题，有何见教？
Will do. What are we looking at?

464
00:30:02,820 --> 00:30:06,070
他们认罪 就网开一面只告他们共谋及行为不当
They plead guilty, we drop the conspiracy and conduct unbecoming.

465
00:30:06,070 --> 00:30:08,410
二十年，十年后就能回家 我想要十二年
Twentyyears. They're home in half. I want 12.

466
00:30:08,410 --> 00:30:10,410
办不到 他们叫了救护车
Can't do it. They called the ambulance.

467
00:30:10,450 --> 00:30:13,830
我不在乎他们叫过谁，总之他们杀了人
I don't care if they called the Avon lady. They killed a Marine.

468
00:30:13,830 --> 00:30:18,000
那块抹布化验过了 法医和化验报告都说未必如此
The rag was tested for poison. The autopsy, lab reports. They say the same thing: Maybe, maybe not.

469
00:30:18,040 --> 00:30:21,170
关达那摩湾海军医院的内科主任…
Chief of Internal Medicine at the Guantanamo Bay Naval Hospital...

470
00:30:21,170 --> 00:30:22,710
说他可以肯定
says he's sure.

471
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:24,880
你知道“红色条规”吗？
What do you know about Code Reds?

472
00:30:24,920 --> 00:30:26,380
哦，老天
Oh, man.

473
00:30:28,840 --> 00:30:31,430
这算私人谈话吧？ 说说看
We off the record? Tell me.

474
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:34,600
就依你的，判十二年
I'm gonna give you the 12 years.

475
00:30:34,640 --> 00:30:37,850
不过你在明天给自己惹麻烦之前该知道…
Before you go getting yourself into trouble tomorrow, you should know...

476
00:30:37,850 --> 00:30:40,060
排长乔纳森・肯德瑞克上尉…
the platoon commander, Lieutenant Jonathan Kendrick...

477
00:30:40,060 --> 00:30:43,070
召集手下开过会并且特地…
held a meeting with the men and specifically...

478
00:30:43,070 --> 00:30:45,570
告诉他们别碰圣地亚哥
told them not to touch Santiago.

479
00:30:48,110 --> 00:30:51,030
我们明晚还打篮球吗？ 算是成交了？
We still playing hoops tomorrow night? Do we have a deal?

480
00:30:51,030 --> 00:30:53,790
等我回来再说
I'll talk toyou when I get back.

481
00:30:57,210 --> 00:31:00,040
你好 找到谁替换我了吗？
Hi there. Any luck getting me replaced?

482
00:31:00,040 --> 00:31:03,340
是不是部里所有人都是你的酒友或球友？
Is there anyone in this command you don't either drink or play ball with?

483
00:31:03,340 --> 00:31:05,300
少校 听着，我是来讲和的
Commander... Listen. I came to make peace.

484
00:31:05,340 --> 00:31:09,430
我承认之前对你有误会 怎么样？可以做朋友吗？
Got off on the wrong foot. What do you say? Friends?

485
00:31:09,430 --> 00:31:12,550
我照多尼的要求给他带了些漫画
I brought Downey some comic books he was asking for.

486
00:31:12,550 --> 00:31:15,060
这孩子根本不明白自己的处境
The kid, Kaffee, I swear he doesn't know where he is.

487
00:31:15,060 --> 00:31:17,480
甚至不知为何被捕 少校
Doesn't even know why he's arrested. Commander.

488
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:19,270
可以叫我乔安妮 乔安妮
You can call me Joanne. Joanne.

489
00:31:19,310 --> 00:31:21,600
乔也可以 好的
Or Jo. Yes.

490
00:31:21,600 --> 00:31:24,690
乔，如果你再私自和我的当事人交谈…
Jo, if you ever speak to a client of mine again without my permission...

491
00:31:24,690 --> 00:31:26,280
我就把你排除在外
I'll have you disbarred.

492
00:31:26,320 --> 00:31:29,610
行吗，朋友？ 有人授权给我
Friends? I had authorization.

493
00:31:29,610 --> 00:31:32,450
谁？ 多尼最亲的亲人
From where? Downey's closest living relative.

494
00:31:32,450 --> 00:31:36,080
詹妮・米勒，他的姨妈
Ginny Miller. His aunt on his mother's side.

495
00:31:36,080 --> 00:31:38,500
詹妮・米勒授权给了你？
You got authorization from Aunt Ginny?

496
00:31:38,500 --> 00:31:40,540
我照你的要求给她打了电话
I gave her a call like you asked.

497
00:31:40,580 --> 00:31:43,040
很不错的女人，我们聊了将近一小时
Very nice woman. We spoke for about an hour.

498
00:31:43,040 --> 00:31:45,630
詹妮・米勒授权给了你
You got authorization from Aunt Ginny.

499
00:31:45,630 --> 00:31:48,380
我完全有这个权利
Perfectly within my province.

500
00:31:48,380 --> 00:31:50,880
她有车库吗？我们可以在那庭审
Does Aunt Ginny have a barn? We could hold the trial there.

501
00:31:50,880 --> 00:31:54,100
我懂缝纫，没准能给他叔叔缝件法官制服
I can sew the costumes. Maybe his Uncle Goober can be the judge.

502
00:31:57,470 --> 00:32:00,060
我明天和你一起去古巴
I'm going to Cuba with you tomorrow.

503
00:32:01,980 --> 00:32:04,860
看来好戏还在后头
And the hits just keep on coming.

504
00:32:27,840 --> 00:32:31,470
过得怎么样，卢瑟？ 多活一天算一天，中尉
How's it going, Luther? Another day, another dollar, captain.

505
00:32:31,470 --> 00:32:34,720
看来你是听天由命了 爱怎么着怎么着吧
You gotta play them as they lay. What goes around comes around.

506
00:32:34,720 --> 00:32:38,220
惹不起就投降好了 至少我的身体还行
Can't beatthem, joingem. At least I got my health.

507
00:32:38,220 --> 00:32:42,060
这比什么都实在，明天见，卢瑟
Well, then you got everything. See you tomorrow, Luther.

508
00:32:42,060 --> 00:32:44,060
我可会躲着你
Not if I seeyou first.

509
00:32:46,360 --> 00:32:48,400
别忘了莎莉回来时给我作证
Now don't forget. When Sally gets back, you're my witness.

510
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:50,780
孩子说话了，我女儿说话了
The baby spoke. My daughter said a word.

511
00:32:50,780 --> 00:32:53,150
我可不能肯定她那是在说话
Your daughter made a sound, Sam. I'm not sure it was a word.

512
00:32:53,150 --> 00:32:55,110
得了吧，那肯定是在说话
Come on, now. It was definitely a word.

513
00:32:57,990 --> 00:33:00,740
你明明听到她在指着我说“爸爸”
You heard her. The girl sat here, pointed and said, "Pa."

514
00:33:00,740 --> 00:33:02,870
没错，她就是说“爸爸”
She did. She said, "Pa."

515
00:33:02,910 --> 00:33:05,170
可她指的是邮筒，山姆
She was pointing at a mailbox, Sam.

516
00:33:05,210 --> 00:33:09,290
没错，等于是说：“爸爸，看，邮筒”
That's right, pointing as if to say, "Pa, look. A mailbox."

517
00:33:16,720 --> 00:33:19,930
杰克・罗斯今天找过我 他同意只判十二年
Jack Ross came to see me today. He offered me the 12 years.

518
00:33:19,930 --> 00:33:22,680
正是你想要的不是吗？ 我知道
Oh, that's what you wanted, right? I know, I know.

519
00:33:23,680 --> 00:33:28,400
我是说，我觉得应该接受，应该接受
I mean, I guess I'll take it. I'll take it.

520
00:33:29,310 --> 00:33:32,530
那么，只用了四十五秒就说定了
So... It took about 45 seconds.

521
00:33:32,530 --> 00:33:34,280
没费多大力气
He barely put up a fight.

522
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:36,950
丹尼，接受吧，这是份大礼
Danny, take the 12 years. It's a gift.

523
00:33:37,950 --> 00:33:39,910
你不相信他们的供词对吧？
You don't believe their story, do you?

524
00:33:39,950 --> 00:33:42,160
你觉得他们该在牢里过下半辈子
You think they ought to go to jail for the rest of their lives.

525
00:33:42,160 --> 00:33:44,410
我相信他们说的每句话…
I believe every word of their story...

526
00:33:44,450 --> 00:33:47,580
也认为他们该在牢里过下半辈子
and I think they ought to go to jail for the rest oftheir lives.

527
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:54,880
明天见 好的
See you tomorrow. Okay.

528
00:33:54,920 --> 00:33:57,630
别忘了穿白色制服，那边很热
Don't forget to wear the whites. Very hot down there.

529
00:33:57,630 --> 00:33:59,550
我不喜欢白色制服
I don't like the whites.

530
00:33:59,550 --> 00:34:01,970
没人喜欢，但我们要去古巴
Nobody likes the whites, but we're going to Cuba.

531
00:34:02,010 --> 00:34:04,770
有没有茶苯海明？ 是用来降温的吗？
You got Dramamine? Dramamine keeps you cool?

532
00:34:04,770 --> 00:34:08,400
不，是用来防止呕吐的 坐飞机会让你感到不舒服
No, Dramamine keeps you from throwing up. You get sick when you fly.

533
00:34:08,400 --> 00:34:11,860
我不舒服是因为担心飞机撞到山上
I get sick when I fly because I'm afraid of crashing into a large mountain.

534
00:34:11,860 --> 00:34:13,440
恐怕茶苯海明没什么用
I don't think Dramaminewill help.

535
00:34:14,400 --> 00:34:16,900
我有些牛至，听说很管用
I got some oregano. I hear that works pretty good.

536
00:34:20,280 --> 00:34:23,580
罗斯提到的一件怪事让我改变了想法
You know, Ross said the strangest thing to me right before I left.

537
00:34:23,580 --> 00:34:27,080
他说排长乔纳森・肯德瑞克上尉…
He said the platoon commander Lieutenant Jonathan Kendrick...

538
00:34:27,080 --> 00:34:30,750
召集手下开会告诉他们别碰圣地亚哥
had a meeting with the men and told them not to touch Santiago.

539
00:34:30,750 --> 00:34:32,170
那么？
So?

540
00:34:33,550 --> 00:34:35,960
我从没提过这人，根本不知道他是谁
I never mentioned Kendrick. I don't even know who he is.

541
00:34:39,550 --> 00:34:43,680
管他怎么回事，明天见
Ah, what the hell. I'll see you tomorrow.

542
00:35:19,130 --> 00:35:21,930
两位中尉，盖洛维少校
Lieutenants Kaffee and Weinberg, Commander Galloway.

543
00:35:21,930 --> 00:35:24,680
我是巴恩斯下士，是来送你们去基地的
I'm Corporal Barnes. I'm to escort you to the windward side of the base.

544
00:35:24,680 --> 00:35:27,930
谢谢 我这有几件迷彩服
Thank you. I got some camouflage jackets here.

545
00:35:27,930 --> 00:35:31,100
我建议你们都穿上 迷彩服？
I suggest you both put them on. Camouflage jackets?

546
00:35:31,100 --> 00:35:34,310
是的，长官，我们一路上离边境相当近
Yes, sir. We'll be riding pretty close to the fenceline.

547
00:35:34,310 --> 00:35:36,520
古巴人看到穿白制服的军官…
The Cubans see an officer wearing white...

548
00:35:36,570 --> 00:35:39,190
有可能认为是重要人物而开枪
they think it might be someone they want to take a shot at.

549
00:35:40,950 --> 00:35:43,490
你出的好主意，山姆
Good call, Sam.

550
00:35:47,990 --> 00:35:50,660
很快就到渡口，要不了多久
We'll just hop on the ferry. We'll be there in no time.

551
00:35:50,660 --> 00:35:53,330
等等，还得坐船吗？ 是的，长官
Wait. We gotta take a boat? Yes, sir.

552
00:35:53,330 --> 00:35:57,040
要到海湾的另一侧 没人提过要坐船
To get to the other side of the bay. Nobody said anything about a boat.

553
00:35:57,040 --> 00:35:59,920
有问题吗，长官？ 不，没问题
Is there a problem, sir? No, no problem.

554
00:35:59,920 --> 00:36:01,720
只是讨厌坐船而已
Just not crazy about boats.

555
00:36:01,760 --> 00:36:06,100
老天，凯菲 你可是海军，却因为坐船而感到害怕
Jesus Christ, Kaffee, you're in the Navy, for crying out loud.

556
00:36:06,100 --> 00:36:09,770
没人会对坐船太感兴趣 是的，长官
Nobody likes her very much. Yes, sir!

557
00:36:22,860 --> 00:36:25,530
我是内森・杰赛普，请进
Nathan Jessup. Come on in.

558
00:36:25,530 --> 00:36:29,620
谢谢，长官，我是丹尼・凯菲 道森和多尼的律师
Thank you, sir. Daniel Kaffee. I'm the attorney for Dawson and Downey.

559
00:36:29,620 --> 00:36:32,040
这是乔安妮・盖洛维少校
This is Lieutenant Commander Joanne Galloway.

560
00:36:32,040 --> 00:36:35,330
幸会，少校 她负责监督评估，长官
Pleasure meeting you, Commander. Observing and evaluating, sir.

561
00:36:35,330 --> 00:36:37,290
山姆・温伯格中尉，我的助手
Lieutenant Sam Weinberg. He'll be assisting.

562
00:36:37,330 --> 00:36:40,130
长官 这是我的助手，马金森中校…
Sir. This is my X.O., Colonel Markinson...

563
00:36:40,130 --> 00:36:42,210
和排长肯德瑞克上尉
and platoon leader Lieutenant Kendrick.

564
00:36:42,210 --> 00:36:44,800
是我让他们来的，请坐
I've asked them to join us. Sit down, please.

565
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:47,340
凯菲中尉 马金森中校
Lieutenant Kaffee. Colonel Markinson.

566
00:36:47,340 --> 00:36:49,930
我曾有幸见过你父亲一面
I had the pleasure of meeting your father once.

567
00:36:49,930 --> 00:36:52,020
我当时才十多岁，他到学校去演讲
I was a teenager. He spoke at my high school.

568
00:36:52,970 --> 00:36:54,180
莱昂纳尔・凯菲？
Lionel Kaffee?

569
00:36:55,020 --> 00:36:57,020
是的，长官 你们知道吗？
Yes, sir. Well, what do you know?

570
00:36:57,060 --> 00:37:01,730
约翰，他父亲曾在你老家得罪过很多人
John, this man's dad once made a lot of enemies down in your neck of the woods.

571
00:37:01,730 --> 00:37:05,570
杰斐逊和麦迪逊地区学校打官司
Jefferson v. Madison County School District.

572
00:37:05,570 --> 00:37:09,950
当地人反对一个黑人女孩到白人学校上学
Folks down there said a black girl couldn't go to an all-white school.

573
00:37:09,950 --> 00:37:13,950
莱昂纳尔・凯菲说 “我们就等着瞧好了”
Lionel Kaffee said, "Well, we'll just see about that."

574
00:37:13,950 --> 00:37:16,620
你父亲怎么样，丹尼？
How the hell is your dad, Danny?

575
00:37:16,620 --> 00:37:19,080
他七年前去世了，长官
He passed away seven years ago, sir.

576
00:37:20,750 --> 00:37:23,670
千万别以为我是故意这么问
Don't I feel like the fucking asshole.

577
00:37:23,670 --> 00:37:25,050
绝对不会
Not at all.

578
00:37:26,260 --> 00:37:28,390
有什么需要我们效劳的，丹尼？
Well, what can we do for you, Danny?

579
00:37:28,430 --> 00:37:30,390
没什么，长官
Uh, not much, sir.

580
00:37:31,850 --> 00:37:35,890
说起来纯粹只是例行公事而已
This is really a formality more than anything else.

581
00:37:36,810 --> 00:37:39,810
军法署署长要求我们面见所有相关证人
JAG Corps insists that we interview all the relevant witnesses.

582
00:37:39,810 --> 00:37:41,820
署长有权这样要求
The JAG Corps can be demanding that way.

583
00:37:43,530 --> 00:37:46,360
约翰会带你们去见想见的人
John will take you out and show you what you want to see.

584
00:37:46,360 --> 00:37:48,490
之后我们可以一起吃午饭
After that we can all hook up for lunch.

585
00:37:48,530 --> 00:37:51,820
怎么样？ 好的，长官
How does that sound? Good. Fine, sir.

586
00:37:59,870 --> 00:38:02,380
那天下午你召集部下开过会是吗？
I understand you had a meeting with your men that afternoon.

587
00:38:02,380 --> 00:38:04,750
是的，没错 都说了些什么？
Yes, I did. What did you guys talk about?

588
00:38:04,750 --> 00:38:07,220
我告诉他们我们中间有个告密者…
I told the men that we had an informer among us...

589
00:38:07,220 --> 00:38:10,260
不管大家有多想惩罚他…
and that despite any desire they might have to seek retribution...

590
00:38:10,260 --> 00:38:13,850
总之不得伤害一等兵圣地亚哥
Private Santiago was not to be harmed in anyway.

591
00:38:13,850 --> 00:38:17,230
什么时候开的会？
16:00 What time was that meeting? 16:00.

592
00:38:17,230 --> 00:38:20,140
就是四点
That's 4:00.

593
00:39:11,450 --> 00:39:14,030
山姆，应该找人把这些送交他的父母
Sam, we should make sure somebody gets this to his parents.

594
00:39:14,030 --> 00:39:17,280
我们不再需要这些了 是啊
We don't need it anymore. Right.

595
00:39:18,490 --> 00:39:20,790
肯德瑞克上尉，能叫你约翰吗？
Lieutenant Kendrick, may I call you John?

596
00:39:20,830 --> 00:39:22,920
不，不行
No, you may not.

597
00:39:22,960 --> 00:39:25,130
我是不是冒犯了你？
Have I done something to offend you?

598
00:39:25,170 --> 00:39:27,290
不，我喜欢你们海军
No, I like all you Navy boys.

599
00:39:27,340 --> 00:39:31,510
每次我们去什么地方打仗 你们总会送我们一程
Every time we gotta go someplace to fight, you fellas always give us a ride.

600
00:39:32,760 --> 00:39:36,260
肯德瑞克上尉 你认为圣地亚哥是死于谋杀吗？
Lieutenant Kendrick, do you think Santiago was murdered?

601
00:39:36,260 --> 00:39:39,220
少校，我信奉主和他的儿子耶稣
Commander, I believe in God and His Son Jesus Christ.

602
00:39:39,220 --> 00:39:41,270
所以我只能说
And because I do, I can say this:

603
00:39:41,270 --> 00:39:45,060
一等兵圣地亚哥死了，这是个悲剧
Private Santiago is dead, and that is a tragedy.

604
00:39:45,060 --> 00:39:47,400
但他的死是因为不守规矩
But he is dead because he had no code.

605
00:39:47,400 --> 00:39:51,860
他的死是因为他对主不敬 而上帝觉察到了
He is dead because he had no honor, and God was watching.

606
00:39:54,200 --> 00:39:55,990
你同意这种观点吗？
How do you feel about that theory?

607
00:39:56,030 --> 00:39:58,330
有道理，我们走吧
Sounds good. Let's move on.

608
00:39:58,330 --> 00:40:00,370
你的计划是来此调查…
Are you planning on doing any investigating...

609
00:40:00,410 --> 00:40:02,370
还是仅仅来旅游？
or are you just gonna take the guided tour?

610
00:40:03,960 --> 00:40:06,830
我有我的处理方式
I'm pacing myself.

611
00:40:07,580 --> 00:40:09,380
他们来来回回跑了三个钟头…
They were running around for three hours...

612
00:40:09,420 --> 00:40:12,420
想找些白色的东西用来当白旗
Iooking for anything white they could wave in the air.

613
00:40:12,420 --> 00:40:15,800
有些人向一个有线新闻网的人投了降
Some of these people surrendered to a crew from CNN.

614
00:40:16,760 --> 00:40:22,220
我总是说，无遮无掩 却战胜了一支装甲部队
Well, walk softly and carry an armored tank division, I always say.

615
00:40:23,520 --> 00:40:26,810
味道很好，谢谢 是我的荣幸，长官
That was delicious. Thank you. My pleasure, sir.

616
00:40:26,810 --> 00:40:31,730
上校，我想问您几个关于九月六日的问题
Colonel, I do have to ask you a couple of questions about September 6.

617
00:40:31,730 --> 00:40:33,360
尽管问
Shoot.

618
00:40:33,400 --> 00:40:36,070
早上六点，您曾接触过 一个海军调查处的官员…
On the morning of the sixth, you were contacted by an N.I.S. Agent...

619
00:40:36,070 --> 00:40:39,570
他说圣地亚哥曾向他透露 一起边界违规开枪事件
who said that Santiago tipped him off to an illegal fenceline shooting.

620
00:40:39,570 --> 00:40:41,830
是的 圣地亚哥是以此…
Yes. Santiago would reveal the person...

621
00:40:41,830 --> 00:40:44,700
作为调动的交换条件 是的
in exchange for a transfer. Yes.

622
00:40:47,750 --> 00:40:50,630
如果您觉得我漏掉了什么细节…
If you feel there are any details that I'm missing...

623
00:40:50,630 --> 00:40:53,960
您可以直接了当地说出来
you should feel free to speak up.

624
00:40:56,420 --> 00:40:57,880
谢谢
Thank you.

625
00:41:01,430 --> 00:41:06,680
然后您将马金森中校 和肯德瑞克上尉叫到了您的办公室
Now, at this point you called Lieutenant Colonel Markinson... and Lieutenant Kendrick into your office.

626
00:41:06,680 --> 00:41:08,440
是这样吗？ 是的
Is that right? Yes.

627
00:41:08,480 --> 00:41:09,650
结果呢？
What happened?

628
00:41:09,690 --> 00:41:15,570
