783
00:50:19,490 --> 00:50:21,740
使他和部队免于难堪
to spare Jessup and the Corps any embarrassment.

784
00:50:21,780 --> 00:50:22,950
多大的余地？
How much?

785
00:50:24,120 --> 00:50:27,750
过失杀人，两年刑期 他们六个月后就能回家
Involuntary manslaughter, two years, they're home in six months.

786
00:50:27,750 --> 00:50:29,250
没得商量，我们要上庭
No deal. We're going to court.

787
00:50:29,290 --> 00:50:31,130
你们不会 为什么？
No, you're not. Why not?

788
00:50:31,170 --> 00:50:34,550
因为你会输，丹尼明白这一点
'Cause you'll lose, and Danny knows it.

789
00:50:34,550 --> 00:50:37,340
如果上了法庭我就要追查到底
If we do go to court, I'm gonna have to go all the way.

790
00:50:37,340 --> 00:50:39,760
他们就得承担所有罪名…
They're gonna be charged with a whole truckload...

791
00:50:39,760 --> 00:50:42,430
谋杀，共谋，行为不当
murder, conspiracy, conduct unbecoming.

792
00:50:42,430 --> 00:50:44,890
在球场上他能赢我，可他知道…
Even though he's got me by the balls out here, Danny knows...

793
00:50:44,890 --> 00:50:47,270
上了法庭他准会输
that in a courtroom, he loses this case.

794
00:50:47,310 --> 00:50:49,270
丹尼是个天才横溢的律师
Danny is an awfully talented lawyer.

795
00:50:49,310 --> 00:50:51,770
既然知道当事人六个月就能回家…
He's not about to see his clients go to jail for life...

796
00:50:51,770 --> 00:50:54,360
就不会让他们蹲一辈子监狱
when he knows they can be home in six months.

797
00:50:54,980 --> 00:50:56,990
协商到此为止
That's the end of this negotiation.

798
00:50:57,820 --> 00:51:00,280
明早传讯时见
I'll see you tomorrow morning at the arraignment.

799
00:51:03,620 --> 00:51:06,580
好了，情况是这样
All right. Here's the story.

800
00:51:06,580 --> 00:51:11,330
政府提出以过失杀人罪判处两年刑期
The government's offering involuntary manslaughter, two years.

801
00:51:11,330 --> 00:51:13,340
六个月后就能回家
Be home in six months.

802
00:51:15,960 --> 00:51:19,630
哇，凯菲，你是世上最了不起的律师
Wow, Kaffee! You're the greatest lawyer in the world!

803
00:51:19,630 --> 00:51:22,760
我们该怎么谢你呢？
Ooh, how can we ever thank you?

804
00:51:22,760 --> 00:51:25,390
伙计们，你们听到我说什么了吧？
Fellas, you hear what I just said?

805
00:51:25,390 --> 00:51:28,730
你们六个月后就能自由
You're going home in six months.

806
00:51:28,730 --> 00:51:31,150
我恐怕不能接受，长官
I'm afraid we can't do that, sir.

807
00:51:31,150 --> 00:51:34,570
接受什么？ 协商解决，长官
Do what? Make a deal, sir.

808
00:51:34,570 --> 00:51:36,030
你说什么？
What are you talking about?

809
00:51:36,070 --> 00:51:38,990
我们没做错什么，长官 我们只是恪守本份…
We did nothing wrong, sir. We did our job...

810
00:51:38,990 --> 00:51:42,240
如果要因此而我会承受的
and if that has consequences, then I'll accept them.

811
00:51:42,240 --> 00:51:44,700
但我不会承认有罪，长官
But I won't say that I'm guilty, sir.

812
00:51:45,950 --> 00:51:49,580
是你…是不是她让你们这么说的？
Did you... Did she put you up to this?

813
00:51:49,580 --> 00:51:53,170
这是我们的准则，长官 哦，令人激动
We have a code, sir. Oh, well, zip-a-dee-doo-dah!

814
00:51:53,170 --> 00:51:56,590
你依你的准则申请无罪 就得在牢里过下半辈子
You and your code plead not guilty. You'll be in jail the rest of your life.

815
00:51:56,590 --> 00:51:59,720
照我说的做六个月后就能回家
Do what I'm telling you, you'll be home in six months.

816
00:52:01,470 --> 00:52:03,510
接受吧，哈罗德，六个月
Do it, Harold. Six months.

817
00:52:03,510 --> 00:52:06,100
算不了什么，一个冰球赛季而已
It's nothing. It's a hockey season.

818
00:52:08,520 --> 00:52:10,270
请允许我… 说吧
Permission to... Speak!

819
00:52:10,310 --> 00:52:12,440
老天
Jesus!

820
00:52:14,770 --> 00:52:17,860
我们以后怎么办，长官？ 什么以后？
What do we do then, sir? When?

821
00:52:17,860 --> 00:52:20,990
六个月后，会被不荣誉解职是吧？长官
After six months, we'll be dishonorably discharged, right, sir?

822
00:52:20,990 --> 00:52:22,320
有可能
Probably.

823
00:52:23,530 --> 00:52:25,570
那时我们怎么办，长官？
Well, what do we do then, sir?

824
00:52:28,240 --> 00:52:32,210
我们入伍是为了按一种明确的法规来生活
We joined the Marines because we wanted to live our lives by a certain code.

825
00:52:32,210 --> 00:52:34,000
我们在部队感受到了
And we found it in the Corps.

826
00:52:34,040 --> 00:52:37,340
现在你却要我们签字承认自己是不光彩的
Now you're asking us to sign a piece of paper that says we have no honor.

827
00:52:37,340 --> 00:52:39,590
要我们承认不是陆战队员
You're asking us to say we're not Marines.

828
00:52:39,630 --> 00:52:41,970
如果法庭判决我们犯了错…
If a court decides that what we did was wrong...

829
00:52:42,010 --> 00:52:44,050
不管什么处罚我都接受
then I'll accept whatever punishment they give.

830
00:52:44,090 --> 00:52:47,640
但我相信没做错，长官 我只是履行了自己的职责…
But I believe I was right, sir. I believe I did my job...

831
00:52:47,640 --> 00:52:51,020
我不会为了六个月后能回家…
and I will not dishonor myself, my unit or the Corps...

832
00:52:51,020 --> 00:52:55,190
而让自己，自己的单位和部队蒙羞…
so that I can go home in six months...

833
00:52:55,190 --> 00:52:56,650
长官
sir.

834
00:53:03,820 --> 00:53:08,780
少校，请让我和道森下士 单独聊一会行吗？
Commander, I'd like to talk to Lance Corporal Dawson alone for a minute.

835
00:53:10,200 --> 00:53:12,120
中士
Sergeant.

836
00:53:12,120 --> 00:53:14,710
我们去其他房间
We're gonna go to another room.

837
00:53:14,750 --> 00:53:17,130
我们要去其他监禁室 好的，夫人
We'd like another holding room. All right, ma'am.

838
00:53:17,130 --> 00:53:19,630
不会有问题 坐吧
It's gonna be okay. Sit down.

839
00:53:31,010 --> 00:53:33,100
你很讨厌我是不是？
You don't like me very much, do you?

840
00:53:34,350 --> 00:53:37,650
算了，不必回答，没关系
Forget it. Don't answer that. It doesn't matter.

841
00:53:43,780 --> 00:53:45,240
知道吗…
You know...

842
00:53:46,570 --> 00:53:48,530
多尼很尊敬你
Downey worships you.

843
00:53:51,240 --> 00:53:53,830
你怎么做他就会怎么做
He's gonna do whatever you do.

844
00:53:54,700 --> 00:53:59,580
你真的愿意因为一条准则 而让他受一辈子牢狱之灾吗，哈罗德？
Are you really gonna let this happen to him because of a code, Harold?

845
00:53:59,580 --> 00:54:02,090
你觉得我们有错吗？ 问题不在这…
Do you think we were right? It doesn't matter...

846
00:54:02,090 --> 00:54:06,300
你觉得我们有没有错？ 我觉得你们会输
Do you think we were right? I think you'd lose.

847
00:54:08,130 --> 00:54:10,090
你是个懦夫
You're such a coward.

848
00:54:10,140 --> 00:54:12,760
真不明白怎么会让你穿上军装
I can't believe they let you wear a uniform.

849
00:54:15,060 --> 00:54:17,770
我的责任到此为止，我已经尽了力
I'm not gonna feel responsible for this. I did everything I could.

850
00:54:17,770 --> 00:54:20,350
你去监狱过你的美好生活好了
You're going to Leavenworth for the better part of your life.

851
00:54:20,350 --> 00:54:22,360
和我没半点关系
And you know what? I don't give a shit.

852
00:54:24,360 --> 00:54:27,450
长官离开房间时你怎么不敬礼？
What happened to saluting an officer when he leaves the room?

853
00:54:36,410 --> 00:54:37,540
开门
Open it up.

854
00:54:40,290 --> 00:54:42,330
真不敢相信，真不敢相信
I don't believe it. I don't believe it.

855
00:54:42,470 --> 00:54:44,930
就因为恨我他宁可去监狱
Dawson's gonna go to jail just to spite me.

856
00:54:44,930 --> 00:54:47,560
没问题，他想自寻死路是他的事
Fine. If he wants to jump off a cliff, that's his business.

857
00:54:47,560 --> 00:54:51,390
我可不想陪他去送死 怎样才能给他另找个律师？
I'm not gonna hold his hand on the way. I wanna get him a new lawyer. How?

858
00:54:51,390 --> 00:54:53,900
明早传讯时提出申请就是
Just make a motion tomorrow morning at the arraignment.

859
00:54:53,900 --> 00:54:55,940
法官会问你是否要提出答辩…
The judge will ask you if you want to enter a plea...

860
00:54:55,980 --> 00:54:58,440
你就说希望另行指派律师
and you tell him that you want to have new counsel assigned.

861
00:54:59,900 --> 00:55:01,360
就这样吧
That's that.

862
00:55:01,400 --> 00:55:04,780
还有，当你要求法官另找律师时…
One thing, though. When you ask the judge for new counsel...

863
00:55:04,780 --> 00:55:06,740
丹尼，记住一定要客气点
Danny, be sure and ask nicely.

864
00:55:07,620 --> 00:55:10,500
你想要我怎么做？ 要你让他们接受庭审
What doyou want from me? I want you to let them be judged.

865
00:55:10,500 --> 00:55:13,460
要你站起来进行辩护
I want you to stand up and make an argument.

866
00:55:13,460 --> 00:55:16,210
辩护对屠杀越南人的战犯没用
An argument that didn't work for Calley at My Lai.

867
00:55:16,210 --> 00:55:18,380
对纽伦堡的纳粹分子也没用
An argument that didn't work for the Nazis at Nuremburg.

868
00:55:18,380 --> 00:55:20,380
看在上帝份上，山姆
Oh, for Christ's sake, Sam.

869
00:55:20,380 --> 00:55:22,880
你真认为这是一码事吗？
Do you really think that's the same as two teenage Marines...

870
00:55:22,880 --> 00:55:25,760
他们从不怀疑执行命令有什么错
executing a routine order they never believed would result in harm?

871
00:55:25,760 --> 00:55:27,510
他们可不是纳粹分子
These guys aren't the Nazis.

872
00:55:27,550 --> 00:55:30,680
现在争没用，丹尼，除非你上庭辩护
Don't look now, Danny, but you're making an argument.

873
00:55:32,230 --> 00:55:35,810
是啊，是啊，明早我就给他们找个新律师
Yeah, yeah. Tomorrow morning I get them a new attorney.

874
00:55:35,810 --> 00:55:37,810
你干嘛这样害怕做律师？
Why are you so afraid to be a lawyer?

875
00:55:37,860 --> 00:55:40,400
是你父亲的期望太高了吗？
Were Daddy's expectations really that high?

876
00:55:40,400 --> 00:55:44,070
得了，别跟我来这套父父子子的激将法
Oh, please. Spare me the psycho-babble father bullshit!

877
00:55:44,070 --> 00:55:47,530
他们会有满意的结果，不过要靠别的律师
Dawson and Downey will have their day in court, but with another lawyer.

878
00:55:47,530 --> 00:55:50,580
别的律师不够好，他们需要你
Another lawyer won't be good enough. They need you.

879
00:55:50,580 --> 00:55:54,210
你知道怎么赢 你知道他们有冤情，你知道怎么才能赢
You know how to win. You know they have a case, and you know how to win.

880
00:55:54,210 --> 00:55:56,710
你一走了之等于决定了他们的命运
If you walk away from this now, you've sealed their fate.

881
00:55:56,710 --> 00:56:00,130
圣地亚哥身亡之时 他们的命运就已经注定了
Their fate was sealed the moment Santiago died.

882
00:56:00,130 --> 00:56:04,970
你相信他们有冤情吗？ 你和道森都活在梦想世界里
Do you believe they have a case? You and Dawson. You both live in the same dream world.

883
00:56:04,970 --> 00:56:06,970
问题不在于我相信什么
It doesn't matter what I believe.

884
00:56:06,970 --> 00:56:09,180
而在于我能证明什么
It only matters what I can prove.

885
00:56:09,180 --> 00:56:12,180
所以别说我知道什么不知道什么
So, please, don't tell me what I know and don't know!

886
00:56:12,180 --> 00:56:13,980
我只知道法律
I know the law!

887
00:56:18,940 --> 00:56:20,900
你对法律一无所知
You know nothing about the law.

888
00:56:20,940 --> 00:56:23,190
你是个二手车推销员，丹尼
You're a used car salesman, Daniel.

889
00:56:23,190 --> 00:56:25,780
你做律师只配处理交通纠纷
You're an ambulance chaser with a rank.

890
00:56:25,780 --> 00:56:28,950
一无是处是你的谋生之道
You're nothing. Live with that.

891
00:56:35,410 --> 00:56:37,370
所以我告诉邓肯…
So I told Duncan...

892
00:56:37,420 --> 00:56:41,670
如果你想上庭，我会申请要求取证…
"If you wanna take this to court I'm gonna file nine discovery motions...

893
00:56:41,670 --> 00:56:48,590
你就得因为一个九旬老翁看错特拉华州 的保险条款花上一年时间来组织书面材料
and you're gonna spend a year going blind on paperwork... because a 90-year-old man misread the Delaware insurance code."

894
00:56:48,590 --> 00:56:50,850
然后呢？ 十五分钟后他回了电话
So what happened? He calls back 15 minutes later.

895
00:56:50,850 --> 00:56:52,850
他说“庭外和解好了”
He says, "Let's make a deal."

896
00:57:39,980 --> 00:57:41,440
全体起立
All rise.

897
00:57:48,940 --> 00:57:50,030
哪个案子？
Where are we?

898
00:57:51,700 --> 00:57:55,330
诉讼号 411275VR-5 一案
Docket number 411275VR-5.

899
00:57:55,330 --> 00:57:58,450
美国政府起诉哈罗德・道森准下士…
The United States v. Lance Corporal Harold W. Dawson...

900
00:57:58,450 --> 00:58:00,500
和一等兵劳登・多尼
and Private First Class Louden Downey.

901
00:58:00,540 --> 00:58:03,750
罪名为谋杀，同谋策划谋杀…
The accused are charged with murder, conspiracy to commit murder...

902
00:58:03,750 --> 00:58:06,380
以及对一名陆战队员行为不当
and conduct unbecoming a United States Marine.

903
00:58:06,380 --> 00:58:08,630
辩方有什么意见吗？
Does the defense wish to enter a plea?

904
00:58:10,340 --> 00:58:11,800
是的
Yeah.

905
00:58:15,510 --> 00:58:16,930
他们没有罪
They're not guilty.

906
00:58:20,060 --> 00:58:22,730
提请进行无罪答辩
Enter a plea of not guilty for the accused.

907
00:58:22,730 --> 00:58:26,060
现在宣布休庭，三周后上午十点…
We'll adjourn until 1000, three weeks from today...

908
00:58:26,060 --> 00:58:29,110
在最高军事法庭重新开庭审理
at which time this general court-martial will reconvene.

909
00:58:45,580 --> 00:58:49,130
为什么一名只有九个月经验 和资历的中尉…
Why does a lieutenant junior grade with ninth months'experience...

910
00:58:49,130 --> 00:58:52,590
会被指派为一起谋杀案作辩护律师？
and a track record for plea bargaining get assigned a murder case?

911
00:58:55,340 --> 00:58:58,430
难道这样就能避免对簿公堂吗？
Would it be so that it never sees the inside of a courtroom?

912
00:59:00,930 --> 00:59:02,930
晚上七点到我家找找答案
We'll work out of my apartment every night, 7:00.

913
00:59:02,930 --> 00:59:07,650
乔，记住带一盒便笺 六盒红笔和六盒黑笔
Jo, pick up a carton of legal pads, half a dozen boxes of red and black pens.

914
00:59:07,650 --> 00:59:10,940
山姆，带几盏台灯来 准备一份初步的验尸报告
Sam, get a couple of desk lamps. I need a preliminary medical profile.

915
00:59:10,940 --> 00:59:15,450
乔，把道森，多尼和圣地亚哥 所有的训练审核报告找来
Jo, we need all proficiency and conduct reports on Dawson, Downey and Santiago.

916
00:59:15,450 --> 00:59:17,700
我只有可可饮料和汽水…
The only thing I have to eat is Yoo-hoo and Cocoa Puffs...

917
00:59:17,740 --> 00:59:19,700
想要其他饮料自己带
so if you want anything else, bring it with you.

918
00:59:19,740 --> 00:59:21,950
行吗？ 好的
Okay? Yeah.

919
00:59:27,960 --> 00:59:30,460
原来法庭就是这个样子
So this is what a courtroom looks like.

920
00:59:40,850 --> 00:59:43,470
你和海军调查处的朋友说过吗？
Were you able to speak to your friend at the N.I. S?

921
00:59:44,480 --> 00:59:47,810
说过，她说如果马金森不想被找到…
Yeah. She said if Markinson doesn't want to be found...

922
00:59:47,810 --> 00:59:49,730
我们就别想找到他
we're not gonna find him.

923
00:59:49,770 --> 00:59:52,780
哪怕马金森就在你面前你也认不出
She said I could be Markinson, and you wouldn't know it.

924
00:59:54,280 --> 00:59:56,400
你是马金森吗？
Are you Markinson?

925
00:59:57,660 --> 01:00:00,570
不是，我也不是马金森
I'm not Markinson.

926
01:00:01,620 --> 01:00:03,830
那你我都排除在外了
That's two down.

927
01:00:05,580 --> 01:00:06,790
怎么了？
What?

928
01:00:08,960 --> 01:00:12,340
我想知道，现在有乔安妮帮忙…
I'm just wondering, now that Joanne's on this...

929
01:00:12,340 --> 01:00:14,920
你是不是还需要我
I'm just wondering if you still need me.

930
01:00:14,920 --> 01:00:17,800
他们只是执行命令 是不合法的命令
They were following orders. An illegal order.

931
01:00:17,800 --> 01:00:20,090
你认为他们知道这命令不合法吗？
Do you think they knew it was an illegal order?

932
01:00:20,090 --> 01:00:23,510
问题在于凡是正直的人都会拒绝…
It doesn't matter what they knew. Any decent person would have refused...

933
01:00:23,510 --> 01:00:25,850
他们无权怀疑上级的命令
They're not permitted to question orders.

934
01:00:25,850 --> 01:00:28,940
那干嘛要偷偷摸摸？干嘛要用代码？
Then what's the secret? Huh? What are the magic words?

935
01:00:28,940 --> 01:00:30,560
我每天都下命令…
I give orders every day...

936
01:00:30,600 --> 01:00:32,610
我们有棒球比赛和军乐队
We have softball games and marching bands.

937
01:00:32,610 --> 01:00:36,940
可他们呆的地方得穿迷彩服 不然就可能被当成靶子
They work at a place where you have to wear camouflage or you might get shot!

938
01:00:44,580 --> 01:00:46,660
我需要你
I need you.

939
01:00:46,700 --> 01:00:51,790
做调查你比我强 而且你知道怎样安排证人
You're better at research than I am, and you know how to prepare a witness.

940
01:00:57,050 --> 01:01:00,260
我带来了验尸报告，还有中餐，先吃点吧
I've got medical reports and Chinese food. I say we eat first.

941
01:01:07,680 --> 01:01:08,770
怎么了？
What?

942
01:01:10,980 --> 01:01:12,940
有没有宫保鸡丁？
You got any kung pao chicken?

943
01:01:16,240 --> 01:01:19,870
我们要强调的是… 没人能证明那块抹布下过毒
This is our defense... intent. No one can prove there was poison on the rag.

944
01:01:19,870 --> 01:01:22,790
“红色条规”在关达那摩湾见怪不怪
Code Red... they're common and accepted in Guantanamo Bay.

945
01:01:22,790 --> 01:01:27,250
而命令…Ａ：是肯德瑞克下的 Ｂ：他们必须服从
The order... A: Kendrick gave it, B: They had to follow it.

946
01:01:27,250 --> 01:01:29,420
就这些 动机呢？
That's it. What about motive?

947
01:01:29,420 --> 01:01:31,500
这一点我们处于下风
We're a little weak on motive. They had one.

948
01:01:31,550 --> 01:01:33,760
这并不表示他们有罪 别激动
That doesn't mean they're guilty. Relax.

949
01:01:33,760 --> 01:01:36,220
我们会应付好开枪事件
We'll deal with the fenceline shooting when it comes up.

950
01:01:36,220 --> 01:01:39,430
开始吧，别管圣地亚哥的具体死因…
Let's start with intent. I don't want to know what made Santiago die.

951
01:01:39,430 --> 01:01:42,430
只需要证明有可能是毒药之外的因素
I just want to show it could've been something other than poison.

952
01:01:42,430 --> 01:01:46,100
乔，找医生了解和乳酸中毒有关的一切
Jo, talk to doctors. Find out everything there is to know about lactic acidosis.

953
01:01:46,100 --> 01:01:49,440
我是华盛顿最高军法处的盖洛维少校
This is Lieutenant Commander Galloway with the JAG Corps in Washington.

954
01:01:49,440 --> 01:01:52,780
我想找出马修・马金森中校的下落
I've been trying to track down a Lieutenant Colonel Matthew Markinson.

955
01:01:52,780 --> 01:01:55,650
医生，有没有任何外伤？
Doctor, was there any sign of external damage?

956
01:01:55,650 --> 01:02:00,240
没有擦伤？没有伤口？淤伤和骨折呢？
No scrapes? No cuts? Bruises? Broken bones?

957
01:02:00,240 --> 01:02:04,660
有没有暴力痕迹？ 难道死亡还不足以证明吗？
Was there any sign of violence? You mean, other than the dead body?

958
01:02:04,660 --> 01:02:07,500
见鬼，我忽略了该死的时间问题
Shit, I walk into that every goddamn time.

959
01:02:07,500 --> 01:02:12,210
他命令我和道森准下士 对威廉执行“红色条规”
He ordered me and Lance Corporal Dawson to give Willie a Code Red.

960
01:02:12,210 --> 01:02:14,510
回答还得更快一些
Answers still have to come much faster.

961
01:02:14,510 --> 01:02:19,140
马马虎虎，但最后一句 听起来感觉象在编造事实
This Iowa farm boy thing will play for a while... but in the end, it sounds like he's searching for the truth.

962
01:02:19,180 --> 01:02:21,470
没错，要说“一等兵圣地亚哥”
He's right. From now on, Willie is Private Santiago.

963
01:02:21,510 --> 01:02:26,180
别说“威廉”，那会让陪审团产生 对我们不利的情绪，懂吗？
You start calling him Willie, and all of a sudden he's a person... who's got a mother who's gonna miss him, okay?

964
01:02:26,180 --> 01:02:28,190
下午已经拟定了陪审团
They drew the court members this afternoon.

965
01:02:28,190 --> 01:02:30,560
七男两女，五个海军，四个陆战队员
Seven men, two women, five Navy, four Marines.

966
01:02:30,560 --> 01:02:33,150
全是资深军官，两个女的都有孩子
All officers with line experience. Neither of the women have children.

967
01:02:33,190 --> 01:02:35,530
不太妙，我们对此无能为力
That's a bad break. There's nothing we can do.

968
01:02:35,530 --> 01:02:38,360
有陪审团就不单纯是法律的问题了
My father always said a jury trial is not just about the law.

969
01:02:38,360 --> 01:02:41,620
而圣地亚哥的无辜身亡会让…
It's about assigning blame. Santiago's dead, and he shouldn't be.

970
01:02:41,620 --> 01:02:44,540
陪审团主张有人得为此承担罪责
These nine people are gonna insist that someone be blamed for that.

971
01:02:44,540 --> 01:02:47,080
是当事人还是肯德瑞克…
Ross is handing them our clients. We're gonna hand them Kendrick.

972
01:02:47,080 --> 01:02:50,710
就得看律师如何“推销”自己的观点了
This is about a sales pitch. It's gonna be won by the lawyers.

973
01:02:50,710 --> 01:02:54,050
记住表情要严肃，在陪审团面前不要畏缩
So remember, poker faces. Don't flinch in front of the court members.

974
01:02:54,050 --> 01:02:57,880
态度要强硬，别低着头如坐针毡
Something doesn't go our way, don't hang your head or shift in your seat.

975
01:02:57,880 --> 01:03:01,720
不管出现什么意外都要让人感觉成竹在胸
Whatever happens, you have to look like it's exactly what you knew would happen.

976
01:03:01,720 --> 01:03:06,390
递文件给我时… 动作要迅速而从容
If you pass me documents... Do it swiftly and don't look eager.

977
01:03:06,390 --> 01:03:09,600
上庭时别打香水，那会分散我的注意力
Don't wear that perfume in court. Wrecks my concentration.

978
01:03:09,600 --> 01:03:11,060
真的吗？
Really?

979
01:03:11,100 --> 01:03:13,520
我是说山姆
I was talking to Sam.

980
01:03:14,820 --> 01:03:16,230
几点了？
What time is it?

981
01:03:16,280 --> 01:03:18,320
该回家了，好好睡一觉
It's time to go home. Try to get some sleep.

982
01:03:18,360 --> 01:03:20,450
能送我一程吗？
Yeah. Give me a ride?

983
01:03:20,450 --> 01:03:21,910
没问题
Sure.

984
01:03:24,870 --> 01:03:27,080
你真是个好人，查理布朗（卡通人物）
You're a good man, Charlie Brown.

985
01:03:27,080 --> 01:03:29,660
法庭上见，大律师
I'll seeyou in court, counselor.

986
01:03:36,340 --> 01:03:38,590
丹尼，我… 不用说了
Danny, I... You don't have to say it.

987
01:03:38,590 --> 01:03:41,050
我们有过分歧，我说过一些无心的话
We've had our differences. I said some things I didn't mean.

988
01:03:41,090 --> 01:03:44,510
你也是，但你很高兴我能接下这个案子
You said some things you didn't mean, but you're happy I stuck with the case.

989
01:03:44,510 --> 01:03:48,980
如果过去三周以来 你对我多了一些敬意…
And if you've gained a certain respect for me over the last three weeks...

990
01:03:48,980 --> 01:03:51,100
我当然会为此而高兴
of course, I'm happy about that.

991
01:03:51,100 --> 01:03:53,270
但用不着太放在心上
But we don't have to make a whole big deal out of it.

992
01:03:53,270 --> 01:03:55,610
你喜欢我我也不会要求你说出来
If you like me, I won't make you say it.

993
01:03:55,610 --> 01:03:59,150
我只是想提醒你明天别穿错袜子
I was just gonna tell you to wear matching socks tomorrow.

994
01:04:00,950 --> 01:04:04,370
好的，很重要提示
Okay. Good tip.

995
01:04:05,120 --> 01:04:06,370
那就万事俱备了
We're ready.

996
01:04:06,410 --> 01:04:08,910
最好相信这一点
Better believe it.

997
01:04:18,760 --> 01:04:20,760
我们要大获全胜
We're gonna get creamed.

998
01:04:50,160 --> 01:04:52,370
凯菲中尉？ 什么事？
Lieutenant Kaffee? Yes?

999
01:04:52,370 --> 01:04:54,790
你会救我们的儿子对吧？
You are gonna save our son, aren't you?

1000
01:04:55,790 --> 01:04:57,170
我会尽力而为
I'll do my best.

1001
01:04:57,920 --> 01:05:02,760
丹尼，我给你介绍一下 劳登的姨妈詹妮・米勒
Danny, I'd like you to meet Ginny Miller, Louden's aunt.

1002
01:05:03,590 --> 01:05:06,640
你就是詹妮姨妈？
You're Aunt Ginny? Uh-huh.

1003
01:05:07,760 --> 01:05:11,020
不好意思，没想到你这么年轻
I'm sorry. I was expecting someone older.

1004
01:05:11,020 --> 01:05:12,770
彼此彼此
So was I.

1005
01:05:16,810 --> 01:05:18,900
给个机会掷硬币定输赢吧
Last chance. I'll flip you for it.

1006
01:05:18,900 --> 01:05:21,400
全体起立 太晚了
All rise. Too late.

1007
01:05:29,830 --> 01:05:33,080
最高军事法庭，请所有在场人员…
All those having business with this general court-martial...

1008
01:05:33,080 --> 01:05:35,710
坐到前面来，主持审判的是…
stand forward and you shall be heard.

1009
01:05:35,710 --> 01:05:39,250
朱利叶斯・亚历山大・伦道夫将军
Colonel Julius Alexander Randolph is presiding.

1010
01:05:39,250 --> 01:05:41,880
控方准备好作公开陈述了吗？
Is the government prepared to make an opening statement?

1011
01:05:41,880 --> 01:05:43,340
是的，大人
Yes, sir.

1012
01:05:46,630 --> 01:05:48,760
本案事实如下：
The facts of the case are these:

1013
01:05:48,760 --> 01:05:51,640
九月六日午夜，被告潜入其队友…
On midnight of September 6, the accused entered the barracks room...

1014
01:05:51,640 --> 01:05:54,680
一等兵威廉・圣地亚哥的房间
of their platoon mate, P.F.C. William Santiago.

1015
01:05:54,680 --> 01:05:57,850
将其弄醒后捆住其手脚…
They woke him up, tied his arms and legs with tape...

1016
01:05:57,850 --> 01:06:00,150
并强行将一块抹布塞进他的喉咙
and forced a rag into his throat.

1017
01:06:00,190 --> 01:06:03,860
几分钟后 一种名为“乳酸中毒”的化学反应…
A few minutes later, a chemical reaction called lactic acidosis...

1018
01:06:03,860 --> 01:06:06,030
导致其肺部出血…
caused his lungs to begin bleeding.

1019
01:06:06,030 --> 01:06:08,030
因此而窒息…
He drowned in his own blood...

1020
01:06:08,030 --> 01:06:11,740
至午夜十二点三十七分被确认死亡
and was pronounced dead at 37 minutes past midnight.

1021
01:06:11,740 --> 01:06:16,870
以上为本案事实经过，绝无虚假
These are the facts of the case, and they are undisputed.

1022
01:06:16,870 --> 01:06:20,540
各位将会听到被告道森准下士…
That's right. The story I've just told you...

1023
01:06:20,540 --> 01:06:24,210
以及一等兵多尼的陈述…
is the exact same story you're gonna hear from Lance Corporal Dawson...

1024
01:06:24,210 --> 01:06:27,010
与我刚才所说的完全一致
and it's the exact same story you're gonna hear from Private Downey.

1025
01:06:27,010 --> 01:06:29,760
此外，我将向各位证实…
Furthermore, the government will also demonstrate...

1026
01:06:29,760 --> 01:06:32,260
被告在抹布上下过毒…
that the accused soaked the rag in poison...

1027
01:06:32,260 --> 01:06:36,520
而且是怀着杀人动机潜入圣地亚哥的房间
and entered Santiago's room with motive and intent to kill.

1028
01:06:37,770 --> 01:06:39,850
现在，凯菲中尉…
Now, Lieutenant Kaffee...

1029
01:06:39,900 --> 01:06:43,070
会努力玩弄一些小魔术来混淆视听
is gonna try and pull off a little magic act here.

1030
01:06:43,070 --> 01:06:45,610
他会用令人震惊的所谓“军规”…
He's gonna try a little misdirection.

1031
01:06:45,610 --> 01:06:49,410
某些听起来很正式的术语…
He's gonna astonish you with stories of rituals...

1032
01:06:49,410 --> 01:06:52,410
试着误导在场的各位…
and dazzle you with official-sounding terms...

1033
01:06:52,410 --> 01:06:54,370
例如“红色条规”
like "Code Red."

1034
01:06:55,500 --> 01:06:58,790
甚至还有可能牵扯上几位军官
He might even try to cut into a few officers for you.

1035
01:06:58,790 --> 01:07:03,750
他没有证据，一点证据都没有 不过会很有娱乐性
He'll have no evidence, mind you, none, but it's gonna be entertaining.

1036
01:07:03,750 --> 01:07:07,300
但是最终，世上所有的魔术…
And when we get to the end, all the magic in the world...

1037
01:07:07,300 --> 01:07:10,090
都无法让人忽视一个事实…
will not have been able to divert your attention from the fact...

1038
01:07:10,090 --> 01:07:15,770
威廉・圣地亚哥死了 是道森和多尼杀死了他
that Willie Santiago is dead and Dawson and Downey killed him.

1039
01:07:17,100 --> 01:07:20,730
这是本案的事实，是无法否认的
These are the facts of the case, and they are undisputed.

1040
01:07:22,440 --> 01:07:24,070
凯菲中尉
Lieutenant Kaffee.

1041
01:07:24,110 --> 01:07:27,070
抹布没下过毒，而且没有杀人动机
There was no poison on the rag, and there was no intent to kill.

1042
01:07:27,070 --> 01:07:31,860
不管用什么方式去证明都是徒劳的 因为这不是事实
Any attempt to prove otherwise is futile'cause it just aingt true.

1043
01:07:31,860 --> 01:07:35,160
那天夜里道森和多尼 进入圣地亚哥的房间…
When Dawson and Downey went into Santiago's room that night...

1044
01:07:35,160 --> 01:07:37,830
不是因为报复或敌意
it wasn't because of vengeance or hatred.

1045
01:07:37,830 --> 01:07:41,620
不是为了杀人或伤人，也不是为了寻开心
It wasn't to kill or harm, and it wasn't because they were looking for kicks.

1046
01:07:41,620 --> 01:07:44,420
因为他们是奉命行事
It's because it was what they were ordered to do.

1047
01:07:45,750 --> 01:07:47,210
让我重复一次
Let me say that again.

1048
01:07:47,260 --> 01:07:50,430
因为他们是奉命行事
It's because it was what theywere ordered to do.

1049
01:07:51,300 --> 01:07:53,010
在其他地方这无足轻重…
Out in the real world that means nothing...

1050
01:07:53,050 --> 01:07:57,310
哪怕在这…海军学院也没什么大不了
and here at the Washington Navy Yard it doesn't mean a whole lot more.

1051
01:07:57,310 --> 01:08:01,350
但如果一名 古巴关达那摩湾Ｗ步兵警卫连的…
But if you're a Marine assigned to Rifle Security Company Windward...

1052
01:08:01,350 --> 01:08:04,360
海军陆战队员接到一个命令…
Guantanamo Bay, Cuba, and you're given an order...

1053
01:08:04,360 --> 01:08:06,980
不执行就得卷铺盖走人
you follow it or you packyour bags.

1054
01:08:06,980 --> 01:08:09,070
这一点不要弄错
Make no mistake about it.

1055
01:08:09,070 --> 01:08:12,410
哈・道森和劳・多尼今天坐在各位面前…
Harold Dawson and Louden Downey are sitting before you today...

1056
01:08:12,410 --> 01:08:15,870
是因为他们履行了自己的职责
because they did their job.

1057
01:08:19,290 --> 01:08:21,660
控方要传讯第一个证人吗？
Is the government ready to call its first witness?

1058
01:08:22,710 --> 01:08:26,420
庭上，控方请求传召Ｒ・Ｃ・米盖尔先生
If it please the court, the government calls Mr. R.C. McGuire.

1059
01:08:30,760 --> 01:08:33,010
米盖尔先生，请举起你的右手
Mr. McGuire, would you raise your right hand, please?

1060
01:08:33,010 --> 01:08:35,850
你愿意发誓你在法庭上…
Do you solemnly swear that the testimony you give this general court-martial...

1061
01:08:35,850 --> 01:08:38,850
所说的一切完全属实，绝无虚假吗？
will be the truth, the whole truth and nothing but the truth?

1062
01:08:38,850 --> 01:08:42,270
我发誓 请坐下，先生
I do. Have a seat, please, sir.

1063
01:08:42,270 --> 01:08:45,690
请说出你的全名以及职业
Would you state your full name and occupation, for the record?

1064
01:08:45,690 --> 01:08:50,190
罗伯特・Ｃ・米盖尔 海军调查处特别官员
Robert C. McGuire, Special Agent, Naval Investigative Service.

1065
01:08:50,190 --> 01:08:54,570
米盖尔先生，今年九月三日 你的办公室是否收到过一等兵…
Mr. McGuire, did your office receive a letter from P.F.C. William Santiago...

1066
01:08:54,570 --> 01:08:56,780
威廉・圣地亚哥的信？
on 3 September of this year?

1067
01:08:56,780 --> 01:08:59,160
是的 信里面说什么？
We did. What did that letter say?

1068
01:08:59,160 --> 01:09:03,870
是说他所在单位的一名队员 用所持武器在边界向境外开枪
That a member of Santiago's unit had fired his weapon over the fenceline.

1069
01:09:03,870 --> 01:09:06,080
有没有具体说明是谁？
Was that Marine identified in the letter?

1070
01:09:06,080 --> 01:09:09,710
没有，我通知指挥官杰赛普上校…
No. I notified the barracks C.O. Colonel Jessup...

1071
01:09:09,710 --> 01:09:11,760
我将会前往调查
that I would be coming down to investigate.

1072
01:09:11,800 --> 01:09:13,550
调查结果呢？
And what did you find?

1073
01:09:13,590 --> 01:09:16,720
记录显示只有一名哨兵归还武器时…
The shift reported only one sentry returned his weapon to the switch...

1074
01:09:16,720 --> 01:09:18,810
少了一发子弹
with a round of ammunition missing.

1075
01:09:18,810 --> 01:09:22,100
是谁？ 哈罗德・道森准下士
Who was that? Lance Corporal Harold Dawson.

1076
01:09:22,100 --> 01:09:23,730
该你问了
Your witness.

1077
01:09:26,400 --> 01:09:29,690
米盖尔先生 你向道森询问过开枪事件吗？
Mr. McGuire, have you questioned Dawson about the fenceline shooting?

1078
01:09:29,690 --> 01:09:33,740
问过，他声称对方有不利于他的行动
Yes. He claims to have been engaged in some manner by the enemy.

1079
01:09:33,740 --> 01:09:35,990
你不相信他吗？ 这不关我的…
You don'believe him? It's not my place...

1080
01:09:35,990 --> 01:09:41,040
为什么道森准下士触犯了军规却没有 因为无故向敌方开枪受到起诉呢？
Lance Corporal Dawson's been charged with a number of crimes. Why wasn't he charged with firing at the enemy without cause?

1081
01:09:42,750 --> 01:09:45,710
没有足够的证据来起诉
There wasn't enough evidence to support such a charge.

1082
01:09:45,710 --> 01:09:47,670
谢谢
Thank you.

1083
01:09:48,710 --> 01:09:50,880
米盖尔先生，我不明白…
Mr. McGuire, I don't understand what you mean when you say...

1084
01:09:50,920 --> 01:09:53,590
“没有足够的证据”是指什么
"There wasn't enough evidence to support such a charge."

1085
01:09:53,590 --> 01:09:55,930
你有威廉・圣地亚哥的信
You had William Santiago's letter.

1086
01:09:57,140 --> 01:09:59,140
圣地亚哥是唯一的目击者
Santiago was the only eyewitness.

1087
01:09:59,140 --> 01:10:02,640
我没来得及询问他 所以不知道他看到了什么
I never had the chance to interview him, so I don't know what he saw.

1088
01:10:02,640 --> 01:10:06,850
我们永远不会知道了，是不是？ 是的
And now we'll never know, will we, Mr. McGuire?

1089
01:10:09,440 --> 01:10:12,440
我问完了 证人请退下
No more questions. The witness is excused.

1090
01:10:16,400 --> 01:10:19,160
海军陆战队Ｗ步兵警卫连二Ｂ排…
Corporal Carl Edward Hammaker, Marine Barracks...

1091
01:10:19,160 --> 01:10:22,490
卡尔・爱德华・汉梅克下士
Rifle Security Company Windward, Second Platoon Bravo.

1092
01:10:22,490 --> 01:10:29,460
下士，九月六日下午肯德瑞克上尉 召集二排开会时你是否在场？
Corporal, were you present at a meeting that Lieutenant Kendrick held... on the afternoon of September 6 with the members of the Second Platoon?

1093
01:10:29,460 --> 01:10:30,750
在场，长官
Yes, sir.

1094
01:10:30,790 --> 01:10:33,460
能说说会议的内容是什么吗？
Would you tell the court the substance of that meeting?

1095
01:10:33,460 --> 01:10:36,720
肯德瑞克上尉说我们排有个告密的…
Lieutenant Kendrick told us we had an informer in our group...

1096
01:10:36,720 --> 01:10:39,470
一等兵圣地亚哥越级…
that Private Santiago had gone outside the chain of command...

1097
01:10:39,470 --> 01:10:42,470
向海军调查处举报排里的一名队员
and reported to the N.I.S. On a member of our platoon.

1098
01:10:42,470 --> 01:10:46,480
这是不是让你很气愤？ 你可以说实话，下士
Did that make you mad? You can tell the truth, Corporal.

1099
01:10:46,480 --> 01:10:48,350
你是不是很生气？ 是的，长官
Did it make you mad? Yes, sir.

1100
01:10:48,350 --> 01:10:49,600
有多生气？
How mad?

1101
01:10:49,650 --> 01:10:53,570
一等兵圣地亚哥违背了 我们深信不疑的一条规矩，长官
Private Santiago betrayed a code we believe in very deeply, sir.

1102
01:10:53,570 --> 01:10:56,650
其他队员有没有生气？ 反对无根据的假设
Were the other squad members angry? Object. Speculation.

1103
01:10:56,650 --> 01:10:58,910
比方说道森和多尼？ 控方律师这是在…
Were Dawson and Downey? Is the government counsel...

1104
01:10:58,910 --> 01:11:03,530
直接要求证人证实我当事人的想法吗？
honestly asking the witness to testify as to how my clients felt?

1105
01:11:03,530 --> 01:11:05,540
反对有效
Sustained.

1106
01:11:07,330 --> 01:11:11,330
下士，肯德瑞克上尉 在会上是否下过什么命令？
Corporal, did Lieutenant Kendrick leave a standing order at that meeting?

1107
01:11:11,330 --> 01:11:13,500
是的，长官 什么命令？
Yes, sir. What was it?

1108
01:11:15,210 --> 01:11:19,340
他明令我们不得擅自处理这件事
Well, it was clear that he didn't want us taking matters into our own hands.

1109
01:11:19,340 --> 01:11:21,390
是什么命令？
What was the order?

1110
01:11:23,180 --> 01:11:26,270
长官，他说不许碰圣地亚哥
Sir, he said Santiago wasn't to be touched.

1111
01:11:27,730 --> 01:11:29,350
该你问了
Your witness.

1112
01:11:30,390 --> 01:11:34,360
汉梅克下士，散会五分钟后 你是否去过道森和多尼的房间？
Corporal Hammaker, were you in Dawson and Downey's barracks... five minutes after this meeting?

1113
01:11:34,360 --> 01:11:35,980
没有，长官
No, sir.

1114
01:11:36,030 --> 01:11:38,740
谢谢，我问完了
Thanks. I have no more questions.

1115
01:11:38,740 --> 01:11:40,860
证人请退下
The witness is excused.

1116
01:11:44,660 --> 01:11:47,040
控方请求传雷蒙德・汤马斯下士
The government calls Corporal Raymond Thomas.

1117
01:11:47,040 --> 01:11:50,330
我知道罗斯上尉是打算传召…
I understand Captain Ross is planning on calling all the other members...

1118
01:11:50,330 --> 01:11:53,040
Ｗ步兵警卫连的所有队员来作证
of Rifle Security Company Windward to testify.

1119
01:11:53,040 --> 01:11:55,290
显然凯菲中尉的辩护重点…
In light of the defense Lieutenant Kaffee is planning to mount...

1120
01:11:55,290 --> 01:11:59,300
和排长的明确指示有相当大的关系
the explicit instructions of a platoon leader seems particularly relevant.

1121
01:11:59,300 --> 01:12:01,880
辩方可以同意全部二十二名证人…
The defense is willing to concede that all 22 witnesses...

1122
01:12:01,880 --> 01:12:04,260
的证词和汉梅克下士基本一致…
will testify substantially as Corporal Hammaker did...

1123
01:12:04,260 --> 01:12:06,720
只要控方同意九月六日下午四点二十分…
if the government is willing to concede that none of them...

1124
01:12:06,720 --> 01:12:10,390
他们谁都不在道森和多尼的房间
were in Dawson and Downey's room at 16:20 on September 6.

1125
01:12:10,390 --> 01:12:12,400
上尉？
Captain?

1126
01:12:12,400 --> 01:12:14,940
控方可以同意
The government will stipulate.

1127
01:12:14,940 --> 01:12:18,990
现在休庭，你可以 明天传讯你的下一位证人
Then we'll adjourn for the day. You can call your next witness tomorrow.

1128
01:12:18,990 --> 01:12:20,990
全体起立
All rise.

1129
01:12:32,420 --> 01:12:34,380
我要再演习一下医生那段
I want to go over the doctor again.

1130
01:12:34,420 --> 01:12:37,340
还是直接了当吧 那我们已经演习过了
We're taking the right approach. We've been over this already.

1131
01:12:37,340 --> 01:12:41,010
听我说，三点钟时斯通医生 还说不知道圣地亚哥的死因
Listen to me. 3:00... Stone says he doesn't know what killed Santiago.

1132
01:12:41,010 --> 01:12:44,760
等见过杰赛普之后 五点钟时他却说是中毒
Then he meets with Jessup, and at 5:00 he says it was poison?

1133
01:12:44,760 --> 01:12:47,600
医生没有说实话 哦，真是个救星
The doctor's not telling the truth. Oh, that's a relief!

1134
01:12:47,600 --> 01:12:50,770
但我作辩时总不能说他是在撒谎吧
I was afraid I wouldn't be able to use the "liar, liar, pants on fire" defense.

1135
01:12:50,770 --> 01:12:55,770
我们无法证明他受过胁迫 还是温习一下手头掌握的材料吧
We can't prove coercion. Let's go over what we have, okay?

1136
01:13:05,950 --> 01:13:09,660
一等兵圣地亚哥 是零点十二分分送到急救室的…
Private Santiago was admitted to the E.R. At 0012...

1137
01:13:09,660 --> 01:13:13,290
在零点三十七分被确认死亡
and he was pronounced dead at 0037.

1138
01:13:13,290 --> 01:13:16,540
斯通医生，什么是乳酸中毒？
Dr. Stone, what is lactic acidosis?

1139
01:13:16,540 --> 01:13:19,750
如果 肌肉及人体的其他细胞燃烧的是糖…
If the muscles and other cells of the body burn sugar...

1140
01:13:19,750 --> 01:13:22,670
而不是氧，体内就会产生乳酸
instead of oxygen, lactic acid is produced.

1141
01:13:22,670 --> 01:13:26,180
正是乳酸导致了圣地亚哥肺出血
That lactic acid is what caused Santiago's lungs to bleed.

1142
01:13:26,180 --> 01:13:29,180
通常肌肉和其他细胞要多长时间…
Normally, how long does it take for the muscles and other cells...

1143
01:13:29,180 --> 01:13:31,680
才开始燃烧糖而不是氧？
to begin burning sugar instead of oxygen?

1144
01:13:31,680 --> 01:13:34,310
二十到三十分钟
Twenty to thirty minutes.

1145
01:13:34,310 --> 01:13:38,150
是什么原因 加速了圣地亚哥肌肉的这种反应？
And what caused this process to be sped up in Santiago's muscles?

1146
01:13:38,150 --> 01:13:40,360
某种摄入性中毒
An ingested poison of some kind.

1147
01:13:40,360 --> 01:13:43,490
法官大人，我反对，证人是在推断
Your Honor, we object at this point. The witness is speculating.

1148
01:13:43,490 --> 01:13:45,610
斯通中校是医学专家
Commander Stone is an expert medical witness.

1149
01:13:45,660 --> 01:13:48,160
他的观点不能认为是推断
In this courtroom, his opinion is not considered speculation.

1150
01:13:48,160 --> 01:13:51,240
斯通中校是内科医生，不是犯罪学专家
Commander Stone is an internist, not a criminologist.

1151
01:13:51,240 --> 01:13:53,870
医学事实在法庭上不是决定性的
The medical facts here are ultimately inconclusive.

1152
01:13:53,870 --> 01:13:57,670
我相信你可以通过交互提问证明这一点
A point I'm confident you'll illustrate to the court under cross-examination.

1153
01:13:57,670 --> 01:14:00,880
所以应该不介意我们暂时认可其观点
So I'm sure you won't mind if his opinion is admitted now.

1154
01:14:00,880 --> 01:14:02,710
当然，大人
Not at all, sir.

1155
01:14:05,170 --> 01:14:09,390
斯通医生 威廉・圣地亚哥是死于中毒吗？
Dr. Stone, did Willie Santiago die of poisoning?

1156
01:14:09,390 --> 01:14:11,140
毫无疑问
Absolutely.

1157
01:14:11,180 --> 01:14:15,350
你知道化验室和验尸官的报告 都显示没有毒药的痕迹吗？
You're aware that the lab and coroner's report show no traces of poison?

1158
01:14:15,350 --> 01:14:17,940
知道 那你怎么证明…
Yes, I am. Then how do you justify...

1159
01:14:17,940 --> 01:14:20,980
严格说来有很多种毒素…
There are literally dozens of toxins which are virtually undetectable...

1160
01:14:20,980 --> 01:14:23,690
在人体组织中是无法检测到的
both in the human body and on a fabric.

1161
01:14:23,690 --> 01:14:27,490
在这一案例中酸中毒症状是显而易见的
The nature of the acidosis is the compelling factor on this issue.

1162
01:14:28,240 --> 01:14:30,200
谢谢，长官
Thank you, sir.

1163
01:14:32,080 --> 01:14:35,500
中校，如果有人患了某种病…
Commander, is it possible for a person to have an affliction...

1164
01:14:35,500 --> 01:14:40,000
在某种情形下… 有没有可能加速酸中毒的过程呢？
some sort of condition... which might speed up the process of acidosis?

1165
01:14:42,590 --> 01:14:44,510
有可能吗，中校？
Commander, is it possible?

1166
01:14:44,550 --> 01:14:46,420
有可能
It's possible.

1167
01:14:46,470 --> 01:14:48,930
在什么情形下呢？
What might some of those conditions be?

1168
01:14:49,930 --> 01:14:52,510
如果患有冠状动脉紊乱…
If a person had a coronary disorder...

1169
01:14:52,510 --> 01:14:55,640
或是大脑紊乱，就会加速该过程
or a cerebral disorder, the process would be more rapid.

1170
01:14:55,640 --> 01:14:59,730
如果我有冠状动脉问题 在嘴里塞上一块干净的抹布…
If I had a coronary condition and a clean rag was placed in my mouth...

1171
01:14:59,730 --> 01:15:03,570
塞得非常深，我的细胞是否有可能…
and the rag was pushed too far down, is it possible that my cells...

1172
01:15:03,570 --> 01:15:06,400
在拿掉抹布后继续燃烧糖分呢？
would continue burning sugar after the rag was taken out?

1173
01:15:06,400 --> 01:15:09,410
那得是病情非常严重的情况下
It would have to be a very serious condition.

1174
01:15:09,410 --> 01:15:11,700
是否有可能病情非常严重…
Is it possible to have a serious coronary condition...

1175
01:15:11,740 --> 01:15:15,240
但症状很轻微，以至于在常规的…
where the warning signals were so mild as to escape a physician...

1176
01:15:15,240 --> 01:15:17,830
体检时被医生忽略呢？
during a routine medical exam?

1177
01:15:17,830 --> 01:15:21,170
有可能，但还是会有迹象
Possibly. There would still be symptoms, though.

1178
01:15:21,170 --> 01:15:23,590
何种迹象？ 有好几百种…
What kind of symptoms? There are hundreds...

1179
01:15:23,590 --> 01:15:25,920
胸口疼？ 是的
Chest pains? Yes.

1180
01:15:25,920 --> 01:15:27,920
气喘？ 是的
Shortness of breath? Yes.

1181
01:15:27,920 --> 01:15:30,430
疲劳？ 当然
Fatigue? Of course.

1182
01:15:35,970 --> 01:15:37,980
医生，这是你的签名吗？
Doctor, is this your signature?

1183
01:15:39,560 --> 01:15:40,690
是的
Yes, it is.

1184
01:15:41,440 --> 01:15:45,150
这上面表明 应限制给圣地亚哥分配任务
This is an order for Private Santiago to be put on restrictive duty.

1185
01:15:45,150 --> 01:15:49,150
请你读一下你写在下面的备注好吗？
Would you read your handwritten remarks at the bottom of the page, please?

1186
01:15:49,150 --> 01:15:53,450
初步测试，阴性，患者胸口疼痛…
"Initial testing, negative. Patient complains of chest pains...

1187
01:15:53,450 --> 01:15:55,660
气喘且易疲劳
shortness of breath and fatigue.

1188
01:15:55,660 --> 01:15:59,540
每周跑步的距离应限制在五英里以内
Restricted from running distances over five miles for one week."

1189
01:16:02,250 --> 01:16:05,840
中校，有没有可能 圣地亚哥患有严重的疾病…
Commander, isn't it possible that Santiago had a serious condition...

1190
01:16:05,840 --> 01:16:12,300
而这种疾病会导致化学反应的加速？ 不会
and it was that condition that caused the accelerated chemical reaction?

1191
01:16:12,470 --> 01:16:14,140
不可能吗？
It's not possible?

1192
01:16:15,560 --> 01:16:19,180
是的，我亲自给每个人 做过彻底的身体检查
I personally give each man a thorough physical examination.

1193
01:16:19,180 --> 01:16:22,350
一等兵圣地亚哥各方面都很健康
Private Santiago was given a clean bill of health.

1194
01:16:22,350 --> 01:16:24,980
所以非得是中毒对吧，中校？
That's why it had to be poison, right, Commander?

1195
01:16:24,980 --> 01:16:29,150
因为如果你让一个 冠状动脉有严重问题的人出任务…
'Cause if you put a man with a serious coronary condition on duty...

1196
01:16:29,150 --> 01:16:31,650
而这人死于与心脏有关的事故…
and that man died from a heart-related incident...

1197
01:16:31,650 --> 01:16:33,740
你就会有大麻烦，是吗？
you'd have a lot to answer for, wouldn't you, Doctor?

1198
01:16:33,740 --> 01:16:36,870
反对，请求驳回 反对有效
Object! Move to strike. Sustained.

1199
01:16:38,040 --> 01:16:40,080
我问完了，法官先生
I have no more questions, Your Honor.

1200
01:16:41,370 --> 01:16:44,830
斯通医生，你获得行医执照已有十七年
Dr. Stone, you've held a medical license for 17 years.

1201
01:16:44,830 --> 01:16:47,090
通过了内科医学委员会的鉴定
You're Board-certified in internal medicine.

1202
01:16:47,090 --> 01:16:52,720
在一家为五千四百二十六人服务的医院 任内科主管
You are chief of internal medicine at a hospital which serves 5,426 people.

1203
01:16:52,720 --> 01:16:57,680
以你的医学专业观点来看 圣地亚哥是死于中毒吗？
In your professional medical opinion, was Willie Santiago poisoned?

1204
01:16:57,680 --> 01:17:00,480
辩方重申反对斯通中校的证词…
We renew our objection to Commander Stone's testimony...

1205
01:17:00,480 --> 01:17:02,640
并要求从笔录中撤回
and ask that it be stricken from the record.

1206
01:17:02,690 --> 01:17:06,690
请求陪审团对该证人的证词不予考虑
We further ask the court members to lend no weight to this witness's testimony.

1207
01:17:06,690 --> 01:17:08,360
反对无效，予以驳回
The objection is overruled.

1208
01:17:08,400 --> 01:17:12,570
辩方强烈反对并要求进行合议…
The defense strenuously objects and requests an 802 conference...

1209
01:17:12,570 --> 01:17:16,780
这样庭上可以有机会在判决前听到辩论
so that His Honor might have a chance to hear discussion before ruling.

1210
01:17:16,780 --> 01:17:20,370
辩方的反对我已经听到，反对无效
The objection of the defense has been heard and overruled.

1211
01:17:20,370 --> 01:17:23,120
请求重新考虑 你的反对已被记录下来
Move to reconsider. Your objection is noted.

1212
01:17:23,120 --> 01:17:27,170
该证人是一位专家，法庭要听听他的观点
The witness is an expert, and the court will hear his opinion!

1213
01:17:31,340 --> 01:17:36,220
斯通医生，以你的专业经验所见…
Dr. Stone, in your expert, professional opinion...

1214
01:17:36,220 --> 01:17:39,060
威廉・圣地亚哥是死于中毒吗？
was Willie Santiago poisoned?

1215
01:17:39,060 --> 01:17:41,060
是的
Yes.

1216
01:17:41,060 --> 01:17:44,890
谢谢，长官，我问完了
Thank you, sir. I have no more questions.

1217
01:17:44,890 --> 01:17:47,020
中校，你可以下去了
Commander, you may step down.

1218
01:17:51,530 --> 01:17:57,620
控方请求休庭 同时请求保留传讯特别证人的权力
Please the court, while we reserve the right to call rebuttal witnesses... the government rests.

1219
01:17:57,660 --> 01:18:01,330
本案押后至十九日星期一上午十点再审…
We'll stand in recess until 1000, Monday the 19th...

1220
01:18:01,330 --> 01:18:04,830
届时请辩方传第一证人出庭
at which time, the defense will call its first witness.

1221
01:18:04,830 --> 01:18:06,830
全体起立
All rise.

1222
01:18:15,880 --> 01:18:18,050
“我强烈反对”？
"I strenuously object"?

1223
01:18:18,090 --> 01:18:22,390
那有什么用？ “反对予以驳回”
Is that how it works? "Objection overruled."

1224
01:18:22,390 --> 01:18:24,600
“不，不…我坚持反对”
"No, no. I strenuously object."

1225
01:18:24,600 --> 01:18:28,150
“哦，既然你坚持反对 那我会予以重新考虑
"Oh, well, if you strenuously object, then I should take time to reconsider."

1226
01:18:28,150 --> 01:18:29,770
至少记入了笔录
I got it on the record.

1227
01:18:29,810 --> 01:18:32,070
可也让陪审团以为我们怕那个医生
You also got the court members thinking we're afraid of the doctor.

1228
01:18:32,110 --> 01:18:34,860
反对一次就能让人知道他不是犯罪学专家
You object once, so they can hear us say he's not a criminologist.

1229
01:18:34,860 --> 01:18:38,570
不断重申就让人感觉 这是律师的古怪花招了
You keep after it, and suddenly it looks like a bunch of fancy lawyer tricks.

1230
01:18:38,570 --> 01:18:41,740
书上的法律和庭上的法律是两回事
It's the difference between paper law and trial law.

1231
01:18:41,740 --> 01:18:44,290
结果法官只好强调斯通是专家
You even had the judge saying Stone was an expert!

1232
01:18:44,290 --> 01:18:47,250
她已经犯了错，我们不要再提了
She made a mistake. Let's not relive it.

1233
01:18:48,880 --> 01:18:52,550
我要给我妻子打电话，晚上见
I'm gonna go call my wife. I'll see you tonight.

1234
01:18:54,590 --> 01:18:57,050
你为什么这样恨他们？
Why do you hate them so much?

1235
01:18:57,050 --> 01:18:59,590
他们以强凌弱，这是事实
They beat up on a weakling. That's all they did.

1236
01:18:59,590 --> 01:19:02,680
其他的全都是废话
The rest of this is just smoke-filled coffee house crap.

1237
01:19:02,680 --> 01:19:05,890
他们折磨过一个虚弱的年轻人
They tortured and tormented a weaker kid!

1238
01:19:05,890 --> 01:19:07,980
因为不喜欢他就杀了他
They didn't like him, so they killed him.

1239
01:19:08,020 --> 01:19:10,980
为什么？因为他跑得不快
And why? Because he couldn't run very fast!

1240
01:19:10,980 --> 01:19:14,690
好了，今晚大家都休息吧
All right. Everybody take the night off.

1241
01:19:14,690 --> 01:19:16,690
对不起 我知道
I'm sorry. I know.

1242
01:19:16,690 --> 01:19:19,530
我们连着三周半每天工作二十个小时
We've been working 20 hours a day for three and halfweeks straight.

1243
01:19:19,530 --> 01:19:22,990
就休息一晚，去看看你太太和女儿
Just take the night off. Go see your wife, your daughter.

1244
01:19:22,990 --> 01:19:25,200
乔，你去…
Jo, go do...

1245
01:19:26,500 --> 01:19:30,080
反正不用来，你想干什么就干什么吧
whatever it is you do when you're not here.

1246
01:19:30,080 --> 01:19:32,840
明天星期几？ 星期六
What day is tomorrow? Saturday.

1247
01:19:32,840 --> 01:19:34,840
我们十点碰头
We start at 10:00.

1248
01:19:38,800 --> 01:19:41,180
你为什么这样维护他们？
Why do you like them so much?

1249
01:19:45,350 --> 01:19:47,640
因为他们在守卫边疆…
'Cause they stand on a wall...

1250
01:19:47,640 --> 01:19:52,020
而且保证 “今晚有我站岗，没什么能伤害你们”
and they say, "Nothing's gonna hurt you tonight, not on my watch."

1251
01:19:56,480 --> 01:19:59,900
别担心那个医生，审判要星期一才开始
Don't worry about the doctor. This trial starts Monday.

1252
01:20:04,830 --> 01:20:09,080
有两人出局，安达将球击向左中场
1 and 2 with two out. Anda line drive to left center.

1253
01:20:09,080 --> 01:20:12,380
克比上垒失败
Kirby racing. He won't get there.

1254
01:20:12,380 --> 01:20:18,840
第三个跑垒员是卡尔・瑞普肯…
And rounding third is Cal Ripken... and the Twins'streak is over.

1255
01:20:18,840 --> 01:20:22,720
第三个跑垒员是卡尔・瑞普肯…
One strike away, and Randy Milligan feels right now like Hulk Hogan.

1256
01:20:28,890 --> 01:20:32,060
很抱歉打扰你，我该先打个电话
I'm sorry to bother you. I should've called first.

1257
01:20:32,060 --> 01:20:36,610
没关系，我只是在看球赛，进来吧
No, I was just watching a ball game. Come on in.

1258
01:20:51,370 --> 01:20:56,920
我是想…你愿意和我一起去吃晚饭吗？
I was wondering if... How you'd feel about my taking you to dinner tonight?

1259
01:20:56,920 --> 01:20:59,960
你是想和我约会吗？ 不是
Are you asking me out on a date? No.

1260
01:20:59,960 --> 01:21:02,050
听上去你是想约我 不是
Sounded like you were asking me on a date.

1261
01:21:02,090 --> 01:21:05,180
以前有人约过我，听起来就是那个意思
I've been asked out on dates before, and that's what it sounded like.

1262
01:21:06,390 --> 01:21:08,600
喜欢海鲜吗？我知道一个好地方
Do you like seafood? I know a good seafood place.

1263
01:21:17,400 --> 01:21:19,530
我第三件案子是一起酗酒闹事案
My third case was a drunk and disorderly.

1264
01:21:19,530 --> 01:21:23,450
花了九个星期 我把那晚在酒吧的三十一个人都找遍了
It lasted nine weeks. I rounded up 31 people from the bar that night.

1265
01:21:23,450 --> 01:21:26,950
酗酒闹事花了九个星期？ 控方想怎么判？
Nine weeks on a D and D? What was the prosecutor offering?

1266
01:21:26,950 --> 01:21:28,950
十五天
Fifteen days.

1267
01:21:31,700 --> 01:21:33,410
当事人真是免遭大难
You sure hustled the shit out of him.

1268
01:21:33,460 --> 01:21:35,880
后来他们把我调到了内政部
Well, after that they moved me to Internal Affairs.

1269
01:21:35,880 --> 01:21:37,920
不能怪他们 我…
Tough to blame them. Where I have earned...

1270
01:21:37,960 --> 01:21:41,710
得过两枚立功奖章和两次奖状
two meritorious service medals and two letters of commendation.

1271
01:21:41,710 --> 01:21:44,840
你干嘛总是和我说你的过去？
Why are you always giving me your resume?

1272
01:21:48,640 --> 01:21:50,600
我想要你承认我是个好律师
Because I want you to think I'm a good lawyer.

1273
01:21:50,640 --> 01:21:52,680
我承认
I do.

1274
01:21:52,730 --> 01:21:54,980
不，你没有
No, you don't.

1275
01:21:58,360 --> 01:22:00,690
我觉得你是个了不起的律师
I think you're an exceptional lawyer.

1276
01:22:01,440 --> 01:22:06,160
我注意过陪审团 你能引起他们的共鸣，他们喜欢你
I watch the court members. They respond to you. They like you.

1277
01:22:06,160 --> 01:22:08,830
你令他们信服，我觉得道森和多尼…
I see you convincing them, and I think Dawson and Downey...

1278
01:22:08,830 --> 01:22:11,580
的下半辈子就得靠你了
are gonna end up owing their lives toyou.

1279
01:22:15,160 --> 01:22:17,130
乔，我觉得…
Jo, I think...

1280
01:22:18,790 --> 01:22:22,510
你应该对我们会输的事实现好心理准备
I think you should prepare yourself for the fact that we're gonna lose.

1281
01:22:22,510 --> 01:22:25,970
罗斯说的那些都是事实
Ross's opening statement... it was all true.

1282
01:22:25,970 --> 01:22:30,930
我们可以暂时假设他们是奉命行事
Let's pretend for a minute that it would actually matter... that the guys were given an order.

1283
01:22:30,970 --> 01:22:33,680
但无法证明确有其事
I can't prove it ever happened.

1284
01:22:33,680 --> 01:22:36,230
我们可以继续设法去证明…
We'll keep doing what we're doing and we'll put on a show...

1285
01:22:36,230 --> 01:22:41,860
但我们掌握的所有证据 都是两个被指控谋杀的人提供的
but all we have is the testimony of two people accused of murder.

1286
01:22:42,860 --> 01:22:44,740
我们会找到马金森
We'll find Markinson.

1287
01:22:44,780 --> 01:22:49,450
乔，我们会输，而且会输得很惨
Jo, we're gonna lose, and we're gonna lose huge.

1288
01:22:52,490 --> 01:22:57,920
古巴关达那摩湾海军陆战队Ｗ连 杰弗瑞・欧文・巴恩斯下士
Corporal Jeffrey Owen Barnes, Marine Barracks Windward... Guantanamo Bay, Cuba.

1289
01:22:57,960 --> 01:23:02,380
巴恩斯下士，请说明一下 队员会因哪些理由被执行“红色条规”
Corporal Barnes, name some reasons why a Marine would receive a Code Red.

1290
01:23:02,380 --> 01:23:05,840
排里或连队开会时迟到
Being late for platoon or company meetings.

1291
01:23:05,840 --> 01:23:09,800
营房总是乱七八糟，跑步时掉队
Keeping his barracks in disorder. Falling back on a run.

1292
01:23:09,800 --> 01:23:12,390
你接受过“红色条规”吗？ 是的，长官
Have you ever received a Code Red? Yes, sir.

1293
01:23:12,390 --> 01:23:16,020
我在进行分组突袭训练时武器滑落了
We were doing seven-man assault drills, and my weapon slipped.

1294
01:23:16,020 --> 01:23:19,400
因为当时气温超过一百度 我的手心全是汗…
It was'cause it was over 100 degrees, and my palms were sweaty...

1295
01:23:19,400 --> 01:23:23,110
而我忘了象学过的那样抹上松香
and I'd forgotten to use the resin like we were taught.

1296
01:23:23,110 --> 01:23:24,690
结果呢？
What happened?

1297
01:23:24,730 --> 01:23:27,860
当天夜里我的队友用毯子蒙住我…
That night, the guys in my squad threw a blanket over me...

1298
01:23:27,860 --> 01:23:30,740
狠狠揍了我五分钟…
took turns punching me in the arm for five minutes...

1299
01:23:30,740 --> 01:23:33,410
然后在我的手上涂上胶水
then they poured glue on my hands.

1300
01:23:33,410 --> 01:23:37,250
这很管用 因为从那以后我的武器再没有脱过手
And it worked too,'cause I aingt never dropped my weapon since.

1301
01:23:38,580 --> 01:23:41,750
一等兵圣地亚哥开会时迟过到吗？
Was Private Santiago ever late for platoon meetings?

1302
01:23:41,750 --> 01:23:42,920
是的，长官
Yes, sir.

1303
01:23:42,960 --> 01:23:45,420
他的营房很乱吗？ 是的，长官
Was his barracks ever in disorder? Yes, sir.

1304
01:23:45,420 --> 01:23:47,800
他跑步时掉过队吗？ 每次都是，长官
Did he ever fall back on a run? All the time, sir.

1305
01:23:47,800 --> 01:23:53,260
九月六日晚上之前 他有没有接受过“红色条规”？
Did he ever, prior to the night of September 6, receive a Code Red?

1306
01:23:53,260 --> 01:23:54,760
没有，长官
No, sir.

1307
01:23:54,810 --> 01:23:56,930
从来没有？ 没有，长官
Never? No, sir.

1308
01:23:58,560 --> 01:24:00,980
你因为手掌出汗受过一次“红色条规”
You got a Code Red'cause your palms were sweaty.

1309
01:24:00,980 --> 01:24:05,190
为什么圣地亚哥 总是拖后腿却没受过一次呢？
Why didn't Santiago, this burden to his unit, ever get one?

1310
01:24:06,530 --> 01:24:08,610
因为道森不允许，长官
Dawson wouldn't allow it, sir.

1311
01:24:09,650 --> 01:24:11,780
道森不允许
Dawson wouldn't allow it.

1312
01:24:11,780 --> 01:24:15,450
大家都对圣地亚哥很凶，但没有碰过他
The guys talked tough about Santiago, but they wouldn't go near him.

1313
01:24:15,450 --> 01:24:17,450
因为都很怕道森
They were too afraid of Dawson.

1314
01:24:17,450 --> 01:24:20,000
反对，证人是在推断
Object. The witness is speculating.

1315
01:24:20,000 --> 01:24:23,750
我换个问法，杰弗瑞你想过 要对圣地亚哥执行“红色条规”吗？
I'll rephrase. Jeffrey, did you ever want to give Santiago a Code Red?

1316
01:24:23,750 --> 01:24:25,750
是的，长官 为什么没有呢？
Yes, sir. Why didn't you?

1317
01:24:25,800 --> 01:24:28,630
因为道森会收拾我，长官
'Cause Dawson would kick my butt, sir.

1318
01:24:28,630 --> 01:24:32,720
很好，现在轮到罗斯上尉问你话了
Good enough. Captain Ross is gonna ask you some questions now.

1319
01:24:33,970 --> 01:24:35,930
巴恩斯下士…
Corporal Barnes...

1320
01:24:37,350 --> 01:24:39,930
这有本新兵训练用的“陆战队纲要”
I hold here the Marine Outline for Recruit Training.

1321
01:24:39,930 --> 01:24:41,730
你熟悉这本书吗？ 是的，长官
Are you familiar with this book? Yes, sir.

1322
01:24:41,770 --> 01:24:43,480
你看过没有？ 看过，长官
Have you read it? Yes, sir.

1323
01:24:43,480 --> 01:24:46,900
好的，请你翻到 关于“红色条规”的章节行吗？
Would you turn to the chapter that deals with Code Reds, please?

1324
01:24:49,360 --> 01:24:53,030
只要翻到描述“红色条规”的那一页
Just flip to the page of the book that discusses Code Reds.

1325
01:24:55,200 --> 01:24:58,750
要知道，长官 “红色条规”是我们用的一个术语
Well, you see, sir, Code Red is a term that we use.

1326
01:24:58,750 --> 01:25:00,500
只限于关达那摩…
Just down in Gitmo...

1327
01:25:00,500 --> 01:25:02,670
好在还有本书
Oh, we're in luck, then.

1328
01:25:05,920 --> 01:25:10,420
古巴关达那摩湾 步兵警卫连行为规范守则
Standard Operating Procedure, Rifle Security Company, Guantanamo Bay, Cuba.

1329
01:25:10,420 --> 01:25:14,510
我猜这本书里 会有“红色条规”的定义条款
I assume we'll find the term Code Red and its definition in that book.

1330
01:25:14,510 --> 01:25:16,390
没有，长官 没有？
No, sir.

1331
01:25:16,430 --> 01:25:18,260
下士，难道陆战队员…
Corporal Barnes, I'm a Marine.

1332
01:25:18,310 --> 01:25:22,520
没有书，没有手册 也没有制订规章制度…
Is there no book, no manual or pamphlet, no set of orders or regulations...

1333
01:25:22,520 --> 01:25:27,110
让大家明白执行“红色条规” 是陆战队员的职责之一吗？
that lets me know that as a Marine one of my duties is to perform Code Reds?

1334
01:25:27,110 --> 01:25:30,610
没有，长官，没这种书，长官
No, sir. No book, sir.

1335
01:25:30,610 --> 01:25:32,610
我问完了
No further questions.

1336
01:25:34,610 --> 01:25:37,240
下士，请你将书翻到…
Corporal, would you turn to the page in this book...

1337
01:25:37,240 --> 01:25:39,700
有餐厅位置说明的那一页
that says where the mess hall is, please?

1338
01:25:39,700 --> 01:25:42,910
凯菲中尉，书里没有这个，长官
Lieutenant Kaffee, that's not in the book, sir.

1339
01:25:44,370 --> 01:25:47,380
你是说 你在关达那摩期间从没吃过饭吗？
You mean to say in all your time at Gitmoyou've never had a meal?

1340
01:25:47,380 --> 01:25:50,630
不，长官，一日三餐都会吃，长官
No, sir. Three squares a day, sir.

1341
01:25:51,340 --> 01:25:52,970
这我就不懂了
I don't understand.

1342
01:25:53,010 --> 01:25:56,180
书里没说，那你怎么知道餐厅在哪？
How did you know where the mess hall was if it's not in this book?

1343
01:25:58,680 --> 01:26:01,930
在吃饭时间跟着大家一起去就能知道
Well, I guess I just followed the crowd at chow time, sir.

1344
01:26:02,810 --> 01:26:05,060
我问完了
No more questions.

1345
01:26:05,060 --> 01:26:08,860
巴恩斯下士，你可以下去了 谢谢，长官
Corporal Barnes, you may step down. Thank you, sir.

1346
01:26:14,360 --> 01:26:16,910
今晚七点，最后演练一下 对肯德瑞克的问话
7:00 tonight we'll do a final Kendrick review.

1347
01:26:16,910 --> 01:26:19,910
我要让他目瞪口呆
I want to slam-dunk this guy.

1348
01:26:31,250 --> 01:26:32,880
嘿，卢瑟
Hey, Luther.

1349
01:26:32,920 --> 01:26:35,470
“海军上将”，案子的进展如何？
Admiral, how's the big case going?

1350
01:26:35,470 --> 01:26:37,510
忙得团团转
Nose to the grindstone.

1351
01:26:37,510 --> 01:26:40,760
苍蝇都没法落在你身上 正是这样
No flies on you. A rolling stone gathers no moss.

1352
01:26:40,760 --> 01:26:43,350
鹿死谁手尚未可知
Well, it aingt over till the fat lady sings.

1353
01:26:43,350 --> 01:26:45,770
你可以再说一次
You can say that again.

1354
01:26:45,770 --> 01:26:49,190
鹿死谁手尚未可知
It aingt over till the fat lady sings. Till the fat lady sings.

1355
01:26:50,190 --> 01:26:52,190
说起来轻松
Walked into that one.

1356
01:27:03,660 --> 01:27:06,460
哦，我的天
Oh, Jesus Christ!

1357
01:27:06,460 --> 01:27:09,210
你没锁车门
You left the door unlocked.

1358
01:27:09,210 --> 01:27:12,340
你吓得我魂都没了 继续往前开
You scared the shit out of me. Just keep driving.

1359
01:27:12,340 --> 01:27:14,340
知道法庭想传讯你吗？
Are you aware you're under subpoena?

1360
01:27:14,340 --> 01:27:18,220
知道，我还知道 有两名陆战队员的命运掌握在你手中
Yes. I'm also aware that the lives of two Marines are in your hands.

1361
01:27:18,220 --> 01:27:22,930
因为我没能阻止事态的发展 所以只好来帮你一把
If there was something I could do about that, I would. But since I can't, all I can do is help you.

1362
01:27:22,930 --> 01:27:25,310
你知道些什么？ 所有细节
What do you know? I know everything.

1363
01:27:25,310 --> 01:27:27,600
是一次“红色条规”吗？ 是的
Was it a Code Red? Yes.

1364
01:27:27,640 --> 01:27:29,810
是肯德瑞克下的命令？ 是的
Did Kendrick give the order? Yes.

1365
01:27:29,810 --> 01:27:32,820
是你亲眼所见吗？ 用不着
Did you witness it? I didn't need to.

1366
01:27:32,820 --> 01:27:35,530
那你怎么知道？你根本不知道
Then how do you know? You know shit.

1367
01:27:35,530 --> 01:27:37,990
他决不会被调离基地
He was never gonna be transferred off that base.

1368
01:27:43,830 --> 01:27:47,210
杰赛普想让他留在基地，说要好好教训他
Jessup was gonna keep him on the base. He said he wanted him trained.

1369
01:27:47,210 --> 01:27:49,870
可调令是你签发的 我知道
The transfer order has your signature. Yeah, I know.

1370
01:27:49,870 --> 01:27:54,000
是圣地亚哥死后第五天 你们到古巴的当天早上签的
I signed it the morning you arrived in Cuba, five days after Santiago died.

1371
01:27:57,510 --> 01:28:00,340
我会为你争取举报人豁免权
I'm gonna get you a deal, some kind of immunity with the prosecutor.

1372
01:28:00,340 --> 01:28:04,930
四天后你要出面作证 把你知道的事情说出来
In about four days, you'll appear as a witness and tell what you know.

1373
01:28:04,930 --> 01:28:08,640
我给你找家旅馆，我们要从头来过
I'm gonna check you into a motel. We are gonna start from the beginning.

1374
01:28:08,640 --> 01:28:12,860
用不着协议，我也不需要豁免权
I don't want a deal, and I don't want immunity.

1375
01:28:12,860 --> 01:28:18,280
我只想让你知道 我为自己曾做过和正在做的事而自豪
I want you to know that I'm proud neither of what I've done or am doing.

1376
01:28:20,450 --> 01:28:22,450
他在哪？ “东北市区旅馆”
Where is he? The Downtown Lodge in Northeast.

1377
01:28:22,490 --> 01:28:24,660
要保证他的安全 是个好提议
I want him guarded. That's a good idea.

1378
01:28:24,700 --> 01:28:27,450
我的安全调查号码是 411527273 安全调查号？
My clearance code is 411527273. Clearance code?

1379
01:28:27,450 --> 01:28:30,210
谢谢 你有安全调查号吗？
Thank you. Do you have a clearance code?

1380
01:28:30,210 --> 01:28:32,380
我是乔・盖洛维，我要保护一个证人
This is Jo Galloway. I need to secure a witness.

1381
01:28:32,380 --> 01:28:35,420
总之他说 杰赛普在调离基地一事上撒了谎
Anyway, he also said that Jessup's lying about the transportation off the base.

1382
01:28:35,420 --> 01:28:38,300
杰赛普说最早的航班是第二天六点
Jessup said that 6:00 the next morning was the first flight leaving.

1383
01:28:38,300 --> 01:28:41,880
马金森说七小时之前就有飞机飞离基地
Markinson says there was a plane that left seven hours earlier.

1384
01:28:41,880 --> 01:28:44,970
我记得很清楚，你听到我说的话吗？
That was impressive. Did you hear what I said about the flight?

1385
01:28:44,970 --> 01:28:48,310
山姆，飞机何时起飞有记录可查对吗？
Sam, when a flight takes off, there's a record kept, right?

1386
01:28:48,310 --> 01:28:50,560
对，得找到基地指挥塔的航行日志
Yeah, you need the tower chiefs log from Gitmo.

1387
01:28:50,560 --> 01:28:53,770
把它找来 我们会赢的
Get it. We're gonna win.

1388
01:28:53,770 --> 01:28:56,230
还不知道马金森是否可靠 航行日志还在不在
We don't know who Markinson is. We don't know what the logbook will say.

1389
01:28:56,230 --> 01:28:59,320
你去做多尼的工作，我去向罗斯透露一下
You just concentrate on Downey. I'm gonna tell Ross where we are.

1390
01:29:06,370 --> 01:29:09,870
今天询问巴恩斯时表现真不错
Nice work today. Redirect on Barnes.

1391
01:29:09,870 --> 01:29:14,080
我找到了马金森 他在哪？
I have Markinson. Where is he?

1392
01:29:14,080 --> 01:29:18,460
“东北”的一个房间 有六个联邦密探守在门口
Motel room in Northeast with six Federal Marshalls outside his door.

1393
01:29:18,460 --> 01:29:20,670
马金森签发的调令是伪造的
The transfer that Markinson signed is phony.

1394
01:29:20,720 --> 01:29:23,590
杰赛普说最早的航班在早上六点是撒谎
Jessup's statement that the 6:00 a.m. Flight was the first available is a lie.

1395
01:29:23,590 --> 01:29:26,100
我们在查航空日志，啤酒
We're checking the tower chiefs log. I'd like a beer, please.

1396
01:29:26,100 --> 01:29:30,600
同时我要让肯德瑞克出庭 到时就有好戏可看了
In the meantime, I'm gonna put Kendrick on the stand and have some fun.

1397
01:29:30,600 --> 01:29:33,440
好吧，我有义务提醒你…
All right, I have an obligation to tell you...

1398
01:29:33,440 --> 01:29:36,610
如果没有适当的证据 想起诉肯德瑞克或杰赛普…
that if you accuse Kendrick or Jessup of any crime without proper evidence...

1399
01:29:36,610 --> 01:29:39,440
你会被军事法庭以渎职罪论处
you'll be subject to a court-martial for professional misconduct.

1400
01:29:39,440 --> 01:29:44,110
会记入你的档案 不管你以后找什么工作都摆脱不了
That's something that'll be stapled to every job application you ever fill out.

1401
01:29:45,620 --> 01:29:49,290
马金森靠不住，丹尼，他是个疯子
Markinson's not gonna hold up, Danny. He's a crazy man.

1402
01:29:49,290 --> 01:29:52,960
我这么说不是想吓你，是为你着想
I'm not saying this to intimidate you. I'm being your lawyer here.

1403
01:29:52,960 --> 01:29:57,130
谢谢，杰克 我觉得你们这帮人都是见鬼的疯子
Thanks, Jack. And I think the fucking bunch of you are certifiably insane.

1404
01:29:57,130 --> 01:29:59,550
你们的礼法让我看不顺眼
Your code of honor makes me want to beat the shit out of somebody.

1405
01:29:59,550 --> 01:30:03,470
别因为我穿同样的制服 就把我和他们混为一谈
Don't lump me in with them just because we wear the same uniform.

1406
01:30:03,470 --> 01:30:06,640
我是你的朋友 也认为你的当事人不该去监狱…
I'm your friend, and I don't think your clients belong in jail...

1407
01:30:06,640 --> 01:30:08,600
但我无权决定
but I don't get to make that decision.

1408
01:30:08,640 --> 01:30:13,100
我代表美国政府，不能带感情色彩或偏见
I represent the United States government without passion or prejudice.

1409
01:30:13,100 --> 01:30:16,520
我的当事人证据充分 你的酒
My client has a case. Here you go.

1410
01:30:20,270 --> 01:30:23,150
你该感谢我作为军事检察官提醒你…
I want you to acknowledge that the judge advocate has made you aware...

1411
01:30:23,150 --> 01:30:28,240
没有充分的证据想指控一名 海军陆战队军官犯有重罪会有什么后果
of the possible consequences involved in accusing a Marine officer... of a felony without proper evidence.

1412
01:30:28,240 --> 01:30:30,990
我听过这样的忠告
I've been so advised.

1413
01:30:35,120 --> 01:30:38,000
你是被逼上法庭的，丹尼
You got bullied into that courtroom, Danny.

1414
01:30:38,000 --> 01:30:41,920
所有人都给你压力，有道森，有盖洛维
By everyone. By Dawson, by Galloway.

1415
01:30:41,920 --> 01:30:44,550
见鬼，实际上我也有挑衅你
Shit, I practically dared you.

1416
01:30:45,680 --> 01:30:49,300
你父亲当年的盛名也在逼迫你步入法庭
You got bullied into that courtroom by the memory of a dead lawyer.

1417
01:30:55,310 --> 01:30:58,520
你是个下流卑鄙没种的对手，杰克
You're a lousy fucking softball player, Jack!

1418
01:31:01,820 --> 01:31:06,110
你的小伙子们完了，丹尼 我再也无能为力了
Your boys are going down, Danny. I can't stop it anymore.

1419
01:31:11,280 --> 01:31:14,700
肯德瑞克上尉，你认为 一等兵圣地亚哥是个好陆战队员吗？
Lieutenant Kendrick, in your opinion, was Private Santiago a good Marine?

1420
01:31:14,700 --> 01:31:16,830
我只能说他很一般
I'd say he was about average.

1421
01:31:16,870 --> 01:31:20,330
你在三份圣地亚哥的考核报告上签过名
You signed three proficiency and conduct reports on Santiago.

1422
01:31:20,330 --> 01:31:24,130
你在所有这些报告上 都是给予中等偏下的评语
On all three reports, you indicate a rating of below average.

1423
01:31:27,380 --> 01:31:31,390
是的，一等兵圣地亚哥的表现 是低于一般水平
Yes, Private Santiago was below average.

1424
01:31:31,390 --> 01:31:35,220
我看不出有必要再践踏一个死者的尊严
I did not see the need to trample on a man's grave.

1425
01:31:35,220 --> 01:31:37,440
我们非常赞同，但你是发过誓的
We appreciate that, but you're under oath now.

1426
01:31:37,440 --> 01:31:40,150
也许会令人不快，但我们是想了解真相
Unpleasant as it may be, we'd all just as soon hear the truth.

1427
01:31:40,150 --> 01:31:42,070
我知道我发过誓
I'm aware of my oath.

1428
01:31:42,070 --> 01:31:47,110
这是道森准下士最近的三份考核报告 上面有你的签名
These are the last three pro-con reports you signed for Lance Corporal Dawson.

1429
01:31:47,110 --> 01:31:49,110
两次被评为优异…
Dawson received two marks of exceptional...

1430
01:31:49,110 --> 01:31:53,580
但最后一份即六月九日 的报告上他得到的评语是中等偏下
but on this most recent report of June 9 he received a rating of below average.

1431
01:31:53,580 --> 01:31:57,620
我想讨论一下这最后一份报告 没问题
I'd like to discuss this last report. That would be fine.

1432
01:31:57,620 --> 01:32:01,380
道森准下士 从步兵学校毕业后的等级评定非常优秀
Lance Corporal Dawson's ranking after the school of infantry was perfect.

1433
01:32:01,380 --> 01:32:04,380
同班超过半数的人晋升为下士时…
Over half that class has since been promoted to full corporal...

1434
01:32:04,380 --> 01:32:06,710
道森还是个准下士
while Dawson has remained a lance corporal.

1435
01:32:06,760 --> 01:32:09,800
道森晋升受阻是因为最后这份报告吗？
Was Dawson's promotion held up because of this last report?

1436
01:32:10,050 --> 01:32:11,940
肯定是
I'm sure it was.

1437
01:32:11,940 --> 01:32:15,030
为什么这份报告 会给道森如此可怜的等级？
Do you recall why Dawson was given such a poor grade on this report?

1438
01:32:15,030 --> 01:32:16,320
我确实忘了
I'm sure I don't.

1439
01:32:16,400 --> 01:32:20,280
我手下有很多人，有很多报告要写
I have many men in my charge. I write many reports.

1440
01:32:20,280 --> 01:32:26,120
上尉，你是否能记起一名 叫柯蒂斯・贝尔的一等兵…
Lieutenant, do you recall an incident involving a P.F.C. Curtis Bell...

1441
01:32:26,120 --> 01:32:28,910
从军官俱乐部偷酒的事？
who'd been found stealing liquor from the Officers'Club?

1442
01:32:28,910 --> 01:32:30,870
是的，有这事
Yes, I do.

1443
01:32:30,920 --> 01:32:33,420
你是否向上级举报过？
Did you report Private Bell to proper authorities?

1444
01:32:35,250 --> 01:32:37,460
我床头有两本书…
I have two books at my bedside...

1445
01:32:37,460 --> 01:32:40,550
“海军陆战队员行为守则”和“圣经”
The Marine Corps Code of Conduct and The King james Bible.

1446
01:32:40,550 --> 01:32:43,220
我唯一知道的上级就是我的指挥官…
The only proper authorities I'm aware of are my commanding officer...

1447
01:32:43,220 --> 01:32:45,970
内森・Ｒ・杰赛普上校和上帝
Colonel Nathan R. Jessup and the Lord our God.

1448
01:32:47,470 --> 01:32:50,100
以你的说法，上尉，我可以理解为…
At your request, Lieutenant Kendrick, I can have the record reflect...

1449
01:32:50,100 --> 01:32:52,850
你不承认军事法庭也是你的上级
your lack of acknowledgement of this court as a proper authority.

1450
01:32:52,850 --> 01:32:55,770
反对，与本案无关 反对有效
Objection. Argumentative. Sustained.

1451
01:32:55,770 --> 01:32:57,900
请注意，律师
Watch yourself, counselor.

1452
01:32:57,940 --> 01:33:00,700
你向上级举报柯蒂斯・贝尔没有？
Did you report Private Bell to your superiors?

1453
01:33:00,700 --> 01:33:03,530
我记忆中一等兵贝尔是很优秀的…
I remember thinking very highly of Private Bell...

1454
01:33:03,530 --> 01:33:06,790
不希望看到他的履历因此而染上污点
not wanting to see his record tarnished by a formal charge.

1455
01:33:07,870 --> 01:33:10,830
你更愿意在单位内部解决是吗？
You preferred it be handled within the unit?

1456
01:33:12,460 --> 01:33:14,460
是的，确实如此
Yes, I most certainly did.

1457
01:33:15,630 --> 01:33:18,960
你知道什么是“红色条规”吗？ 是的，我知道
Do you know what a Code Red is? Yes, I do.

1458
01:33:18,960 --> 01:33:22,220
你曾下令执行过“红色条规”吗？ 不，我没有
Have you ever ordered a Code Red? No, I have not.

1459
01:33:22,220 --> 01:33:25,390
你是否曾命令道森和另两个部下…
Did you order Dawson and two other men to make sure that Private Bell...

1460
01:33:25,390 --> 01:33:30,890
看住贝尔，总共七天 除了水之外不给他任何食物或饮料？
received no food or drink, except water, for a period of seven days?

1461
01:33:30,890 --> 01:33:33,270
这是歪曲事实，中尉
That is a distortion of the truth, Lieutenant.

1462
01:33:33,270 --> 01:33:35,610
一等兵贝尔是被监禁在营房内
Private Bell was placed on barracks restriction.

1463
01:33:35,610 --> 01:33:38,780
有水和维他命作补充 而且我能向你保证…
He was given water and vitamin supplements, and I can assure you...

1464
01:33:38,780 --> 01:33:42,820
他的健康从未受到威胁
at no time was his health in danger.

1465
01:33:42,820 --> 01:33:45,620
我相信这对一等兵贝尔来说很有趣
I'm sure it was lovely for Private Bell.

1466
01:33:45,620 --> 01:33:48,330
但你有没有下令关禁闭呢？
But you did order the barracks restriction, didn't you?

1467
01:33:48,330 --> 01:33:52,580
有没有下令不提供食物呢？ 是的，我下过命令
You did order the denial of food? Yes, I did.

1468
01:33:52,580 --> 01:33:56,500
这种形式的处罚 可以认为是属于“红色条规”吗？
Wouldn't this form of discipline be considered a Code Red?

1469
01:33:58,250 --> 01:33:59,130
不
No

1470
01:33:59,170 --> 01:34:03,130
如果我传关达那摩湾的 其他四百七十八名陆战队员作证…
If I called the other 478 Marines at Guantanamo Bayto testify...

1471
01:34:03,130 --> 01:34:05,260
他们会认为这是“红色条规”吗？
would they consider it a Code Red?

1472
01:34:05,300 --> 01:34:09,350
证人不可能证实 其他四百七十八个人会怎么说
The witness can't possibly testify as to what 478 other men would say.

1473
01:34:09,350 --> 01:34:13,270
控方反对这一系列的提问 这些与本案无关…
We object to this entire line of questioning. It's argumentative...

1474
01:34:13,270 --> 01:34:15,690
是对证人的无端骚扰
and irrelevant badgering of the witness.

1475
01:34:15,690 --> 01:34:18,400
控方反对有效，凯菲中尉…
The government's objection is sustained, Lieutenant Kaffee...

1476
01:34:18,400 --> 01:34:21,610
我要提醒你 你正在询问的是一名海军军官…
and I would remind you that you're now questioning a Marine officer...

1477
01:34:21,610 --> 01:34:23,780
履历记录无可挑剔
with an impeccable service record.

1478
01:34:23,820 --> 01:34:25,410
谢谢，法官大人
Thank you, Your Honor.

1479
01:34:26,450 --> 01:34:30,330
上尉，道森最后那份报告 被给予中等偏下的评定…
Lieutenant, was Dawson given a rating of below average on this last report...

1480
01:34:30,330 --> 01:34:33,250
是因为你发觉他偷偷给贝尔食物吗？
because you learned he'd been sneaking food to Private Bell?

1481
01:34:33,250 --> 01:34:36,630
反对 别着急…上尉？
Object! Not so fast. Lieutenant?

1482
01:34:38,210 --> 01:34:41,960
道森准下士被给予中等偏下的评语…
Lance Corporal Dawson was given a below average rating...

1483
01:34:42,840 --> 01:34:45,380
是因为他违犯了军规
because he had committed a crime.

1484
01:34:45,380 --> 01:34:48,720
军规？他犯了什么军规？
A crime? What crime did he commit?

1485
01:34:50,470 --> 01:34:51,430
肯德瑞克上尉
Lieutenant Kendrick

1486
01:34:52,560 --> 01:34:58,520
道森给一个饥饿的人送食物 犯了哪条军规？
Dawson brought a hungry guy some food. What crime did he commit?

1487
01:35:00,320 --> 01:35:01,900
他违反了命令
He disobeyed an order.

1488
01:35:01,940 --> 01:35:04,530
因为他履行了自己的价值观…
And because he exercised his own set ofvalues...

1489
01:35:04,530 --> 01:35:07,570
作了与一名陆战队员健康有关的决定…
because he made a decision about the welfare of a Marine...

1490
01:35:07,570 --> 01:35:11,290
而这与你的命令有抵触，所以得受罚 是这样吗？
that was in conflict with your order, he was punished, is that right?

1491
01:35:11,290 --> 01:35:14,910
道森准下士违反了命令
Lance Corporal Dawson disobeyed an order.

1492
01:35:14,910 --> 01:35:17,500
可那不是真正的命令不是吗？
Yeah, but it wasn't a real order, was it?

1493
01:35:17,500 --> 01:35:19,750
毕竟现在是和平年代
After all, it's peacetime.

1494
01:35:19,750 --> 01:35:23,090
他没被派去守卫山头或是进攻滩头阵地
He wasn't being asked to secure a hill or advance on a beachhead.

1495
01:35:23,090 --> 01:35:27,590
我是说 一名具备道森这种能力的陆战队员…
I mean, surely a Marine of Dawson's intelligence...

1496
01:35:27,590 --> 01:35:30,760
完全可以自己决定哪些命令重要…
can be trusted to determine on his own which are the important orders...

1497
01:35:30,760 --> 01:35:34,810
哪些命令有可能…在道德上有疑义
and which orders might, say, be morally questionable?

1498
01:35:36,180 --> 01:35:37,440
肯德瑞克上尉？
Lieutenant Kendrick?

1499
01:35:37,940 --> 01:35:39,770
是这样吗？
Can he?

1500
01:35:39,770 --> 01:35:43,530
道森可以自己决定应该服从哪些命令吗？
Can Dawson determine on his own which orders he's going to follow?

1501
01:35:43,530 --> 01:35:45,280
不，他不能
No, he cannot.

1502
01:35:45,280 --> 01:35:48,110
柯蒂斯・贝尔的事让他受了教育，是吧？
A lesson he learned after the Curtis Bell incident, right?

1503
01:35:48,110 --> 01:35:51,030
我想是的 你确信是这样对吧？
I would think so. You know so, don't you?

1504
01:35:51,030 --> 01:35:52,780
反对 反对有效
Object! Sustained.

1505
01:35:54,790 --> 01:35:57,790
肯德瑞克上尉，最后一个问题
Lieutenant Kendrick, one final question.

1506
01:35:59,000 --> 01:36:02,380
如果你命令道森 对圣地亚哥执行“红色条规”…
If you had ordered Dawson to give Santiago a Code Red...

1507
01:36:02,380 --> 01:36:06,670
我特地命令手下… 他会再次违反命令吗？
I specifically ordered those men... Would he disobey you again?

1508
01:36:06,670 --> 01:36:10,800
上尉，不必作答 用不着回答，我问完了
Lieutenant, don't answer that! You don't have to. I'm through.

1509
01:36:10,800 --> 01:36:14,510
肯德瑞克上尉 你是否曾命令道森准下士…
Lieutenant Kendrick, did you order Lance Corporal Dawson...

1510
01:36:14,510 --> 01:36:18,640
和一等兵多尼 对威廉・圣地亚哥执行“红色条规”？
and Private Downey to give Willie Santiago a Code Red?

1511
01:36:20,150 --> 01:36:21,230
肯德瑞克上尉？
Lieutenant Kendrick?

1512
01:36:21,690 --> 01:36:24,780
不，我没有 谢谢
No, I did not. Thank you.

1513
01:36:28,650 --> 01:36:30,860
怎么样？
What's the word?

1514
01:36:30,860 --> 01:36:35,200
我拿到了指挥塔那天晚上的日志 杰赛普说的是事实
I got the tower chiefs log from that night. Jessup's telling the truth.

1515
01:36:35,200 --> 01:36:39,580
最早离开的航班是在早上六点 让我看看
6:00 a.m. Flight was the first plane. Let me see this.

1516
01:36:49,630 --> 01:36:52,590
今晚加班？ 是啊
Working late tonight? Oh, yeah.

1517
01:36:56,850 --> 01:37:00,640
十一点根本没有航班 你到底在搞什么鬼？
There wasn't a flight at 11:00. What the fuck are you trying to pull?

1518
01:37:00,640 --> 01:37:03,940
从关达那摩到美国最早的航班 是在二十三点
The first flight stateside left Guantanamo Bay at 2300.

1519
01:37:03,940 --> 01:37:07,940
凌晨两点过几分抵达安德鲁斯空军基地
It arrived at Andrews Air Force Base at a few minutes past 2:00.

1520
01:37:07,940 --> 01:37:11,240
是吗？那为什么指挥塔的日志没有记录？
Really? Then why isn't it listed in the tower chiefs log?

1521
01:37:13,240 --> 01:37:14,580
杰赛普
Jessup.

1522
01:37:14,620 --> 01:37:17,120
你是说他窜改了日志吗？
What are you telling me? He fixed the logbook?

1523
01:37:19,080 --> 01:37:23,210
也许他能更改起飞记录 但我可以证明曾有飞机降落过
Maybe he can make it so a plane didn't take off, but I can prove one landed.

1524
01:37:23,210 --> 01:37:25,340
我去安德鲁斯找记录
I'll get the logbook from Andrews.

1525
01:37:25,380 --> 01:37:28,380
你在安德鲁斯的日志上也发现不了什么
You're not gonna find anything in the Andrews logbook, either.

1526
01:37:28,380 --> 01:37:30,380
他能让整个航班消失吗？
He can make an entire flight disappear?

1527
01:37:30,380 --> 01:37:34,970
杰赛普就要被任命为安全委员会的主管了
Jessup is about to be appointed director of operations for the Security Council.

1528
01:37:34,970 --> 01:37:39,060
不知道怎么避开地雷 是休想得到那个位置的
You don't get to that position without knowing how to sidestep some land mines.

1529
01:37:39,060 --> 01:37:41,980
可他没法避开你
He's not gonna be able to sidestep you.

1530
01:37:41,980 --> 01:37:44,440
你不会还想让我出庭吧？
You don't still intend to put me on the stand?

1531
01:37:44,440 --> 01:37:47,480
星期四上午十点
Thursday morning, 10:00.

1532
01:37:51,820 --> 01:37:55,740
得找到能证实有那趟航班的人
There's gotta be someone who can testify to the flight.

1533
01:37:55,740 --> 01:37:59,040
这不象航空公司有固定的飞行时刻表
This isn't TWA. There isn't a regular flight schedule.

1534
01:37:59,040 --> 01:38:01,910
你知道每天有多少架飞机起起落落？
Do you have any idea how many planes take off and land every day?

1535
01:38:01,910 --> 01:38:05,420
地勤人员也记不住 那趟航班四周前的降落时间
A ground crew kid won't remember a flight that landed four weeks ago.

1536
01:38:05,420 --> 01:38:08,630
不去查怎么会知道呢？ 忘了那趟航班
How do you know if you don't check? Forget the flight!

1537
01:38:08,630 --> 01:38:12,510
马金森会证明杰赛普拒绝调走圣地亚哥
Markinson will testify that Jessup refused to transfer Santiago.

1538
01:38:12,510 --> 01:38:15,140
他会证明调令是伪造的，这就够了
He'll testify to the forged transfer, and that'll be enough.

1539
01:38:15,140 --> 01:38:17,760
加上多尼的证词应该够了
That and Downey's testimony really ought to be enough.

1540
01:38:23,190 --> 01:38:27,230
六号夜里你们为什么 进入圣地亚哥的房间？
Why did you go into Santiago's room on the night of the 6th?

1541
01:38:27,230 --> 01:38:30,530
对一等兵圣地亚哥 执行“红色条规”，夫人
To give Private Santiago a Code Red, ma'am.

1542
01:38:30,530 --> 01:38:32,780
你们为什么这样做？
Why did you give him a Code Red?

1543
01:38:32,780 --> 01:38:37,180
是Ｗ步兵警卫连 排长乔纳森-詹姆斯-肯德瑞克上尉…
I was ordered to give him a Code Red by the platoon commander...

1544
01:38:37,180 --> 01:38:40,660
下令对他执行“红色条规”
of Rifle Security Company Windward, Lieutenant Jonathan James Kendrick.

1545
01:38:41,750 --> 01:38:44,210
你们会没事的
You're gonna do fine.

1546
01:38:45,750 --> 01:38:48,340
你觉得会让我们很快回连队吗，夫人？
You think they'll let us go back to our platoon soon, ma'am?

1547
01:38:49,670 --> 01:38:51,630
绝对没问题
Absolutely.

1548
01:38:54,800 --> 01:38:57,300
记得提问的顺序吗？能肯定吗？
Do you remember the order of questions? Areyou sure?

1549
01:38:57,300 --> 01:39:00,310
简练一点，不然他听不懂就麻烦了
And we'll use small words,'cause he gets rattled ifhe doesn't understand.

1550
01:39:00,310 --> 01:39:03,270
我是说节奏要慢一点 我会的
I'm just saying go slow. I'm gonna go slow.

1551
01:39:03,270 --> 01:39:06,270
但要尽快把问题问完
And get him off as fast as you can.

1552
01:39:06,270 --> 01:39:09,270
怎么了？不会有问题的
What? It's gonna be fine.

1553
01:39:11,650 --> 01:39:13,650
尊敬的圣地亚哥先生和夫人…
Dear Mr. And Mrs. Santiago...

1554
01:39:14,950 --> 01:39:17,490
我是威廉的行政长官
I was William's executive officer.

1555
01:39:17,490 --> 01:39:21,080
我对令郎不太熟悉，只知道他叫什么名字
I knew your son vaguely, which is to say I knew his name.

1556
01:39:22,040 --> 01:39:26,870
那两个对令郎之死负有责任的人 的审判很快就有结果了
In a matter of time, the trial of the two men... charged with your son's death will be concluded...

1557
01:39:26,870 --> 01:39:29,210
你们素不相识的七男两女…
and seven men and two women whom you've never met...

1558
01:39:29,210 --> 01:39:33,300
将试着为令郎的死给出一个解释
will try to offer you an explanation as to why William is dead.

1559
01:39:33,300 --> 01:39:37,050
而我已经尽我所能来使真相大白于天下
For my part, I've done as much as I can to bring the truth to light.

1560
01:39:37,800 --> 01:39:39,340
事实上…
And the truth is this...

1561
01:39:39,390 --> 01:39:42,010
令郎的死只有一个原因…
Your son is dead for only one reason...

1562
01:39:42,010 --> 01:39:45,020
我阻止事态发展时不够强硬
I wasn't strong enough to stop it.

1563
01:39:45,020 --> 01:39:51,020
美国海军，马修-安德鲁-马金森中校 敬上
Always, Lieutenant Colonel Matthew Andrew Markinson... United States Marine Corps.

1564
01:39:56,150 --> 01:39:59,740
一等兵，我要你再向大家说一次
Private, I want you to tell us one last time.

1565
01:39:59,740 --> 01:40:05,660
你们为什么在九月六日夜里 去一等兵圣地亚哥的房间？
Why did you go to Private Santiago's room on the night of September 6?

1566
01:40:05,660 --> 01:40:10,540
是排长肯德瑞克上尉 命令我们去执行“红色条规”
A Code Red was ordered by my platoon commander... Lieutenant Jonathan James Kendrick.

1567
01:40:11,040 --> 01:40:12,840
谢谢
Thank you.

1568
01:40:12,880 --> 01:40:14,500
该你问了
Your witness.

1569
01:40:19,010 --> 01:40:21,260
一等兵，九月二日那一周的…
Private, the week of 2 September...

1570
01:40:21,260 --> 01:40:24,850
换岗记录显示 十六点以前你一直在三十九号哨岗
the switch log has you down at Post 39 until 1600.

1571
01:40:24,850 --> 01:40:26,060
是这样吗？
Is that correct?

1572
01:40:26,100 --> 01:40:29,100
是的，长官，记录一直做得很准确
I'm sure it is, sir. They keep that log pretty good.

1573
01:40:29,100 --> 01:40:32,770
三十九号哨岗离Ｗ连的营房有多远？
How far is it from Post 39 to the Windward Barracks?

1574
01:40:32,770 --> 01:40:36,320
有点距离，长官，得走一阵子
Well, it's a ways, sir. It's a hike.

1575
01:40:36,320 --> 01:40:39,240
搭乘越野车要多久？
About how far by Jeep?

1576
01:40:39,240 --> 01:40:42,660
他问这个干什么？ 十到十五分钟，长官
About ten or fifteen minutes, sir.

1577
01:40:42,660 --> 01:40:44,620
你曾步行过吗？
You ever had to walk it?

1578
01:40:44,620 --> 01:40:48,540
是的，长官 星期五那天，“临时司机”…
Yes, sir. That day, Friday. The pickup private...

1579
01:40:48,540 --> 01:40:51,670
我们都这么叫负责接送我们的二等兵…
That's what we call the guy who drops us off and picks us up...

1580
01:40:51,670 --> 01:40:54,960
同时也因为他能在“纽约城”泡到女孩子
also'cause he can get girls in New York City.

1581
01:40:55,920 --> 01:40:58,130
他到三十九号哨的时候爆胎了
The pickup private got a flat, sir, right at 39.

1582
01:40:58,130 --> 01:41:01,050
他一停车，胎就爆了，又没有备胎
He pulled up and, bam, blowout with no spare.

1583
01:41:01,050 --> 01:41:03,140
所以我们只好跑步回营房
So we had to double-time it back to the barracks.

1584
01:41:03,180 --> 01:41:06,930
既然越野车要花十到十五分钟，我猜…
And if it's about ten or fifteen minutes by Jeep, I'm guessing...

1585
01:41:06,930 --> 01:41:10,100
跑步至少要一个小时，对不对？
it must be a good hour by foot, am I right?

1586
01:41:10,100 --> 01:41:13,270
他和我刚好用了四十五分钟，长官
Pickup and me did it in 45 flat, sir.

1587
01:41:13,270 --> 01:41:14,730
不错啊
Not bad.

1588
01:41:16,110 --> 01:41:19,610
你说你们去袭击一等兵圣地亚哥…
You've said that your assault on Private Santiago...

1589
01:41:19,610 --> 01:41:22,950
是因为肯德瑞克上尉十六点二十分时…
was a result of an order that Lieutenant Kendrick gave you...

1590
01:41:22,950 --> 01:41:26,660
在你们的房间给你们下了命令，对不对？
in your barracks room at 1620, am I right?

1591
01:41:27,660 --> 01:41:29,290
是的，长官
Yes, sir.

1592
01:41:29,330 --> 01:41:33,250
但你刚才说十六点四十五分之前 你们还没回到营房
But you just said that you didn't make it back to the barracks until 1645.

1593
01:41:35,710 --> 01:41:39,920
既然十六点四十五分之前 你还没回到营房…
Well, if you didn't make it back to the barracks until 1645...

1594
01:41:39,920 --> 01:41:42,180
那十六点二十分你怎么会在房间里？
how could you be in your room at 1620?

1595
01:41:43,140 --> 01:41:46,010
是这样，长官，车胎爆了…
Well, you see, sir, there was a blowout...

1596
01:41:46,010 --> 01:41:49,980
你有没有亲耳听到 肯德瑞克上尉下令执行“红色条规”？
Did you ever actually hear Lieutenant Kendrick order a Code Red?

1597
01:41:49,980 --> 01:41:51,770
哈罗德说…
Well, Hal said that...

1598
01:41:51,810 --> 01:41:54,400
一等兵，你有没有亲耳听到…
Private, did you ever actually hear...

1599
01:41:54,400 --> 01:41:58,780
肯德瑞克上尉下令执行“红色条规”？ 没有，长官
Lieutenant Kendrick order a Code Red?

1600
01:41:58,900 --> 01:42:02,320
请求暂时休庭 我要和我的当事人交换意见
I'd like to request a recess in order to confer with my client.

1601
01:42:02,320 --> 01:42:04,700
你为什么去圣地亚哥的房间？ 证人有他的权利
Why did you go into Santiago's room? The witness has rights!

1602
01:42:04,700 --> 01:42:08,040
证人早就知道他的权利 重复一下刚才的问题
The witness has been read his rights. The question will be repeated.

1603
01:42:08,040 --> 01:42:10,040
你为什么去圣地亚哥的房间？ 哈罗德
Why did you go into Santiago's room?

1604
01:42:10,040 --> 01:42:13,540
是道森要你去执行“红色条规”吗？ 哈罗德
Did Lance Corporal Dawson tell you to give Santiago a Code Red?

1605
01:42:13,540 --> 01:42:15,330
不要看他 哈罗德
Don't look at him! Hal!

1606
01:42:15,380 --> 01:42:17,380
回答上尉的问题
Answer the captaings question!

1607
01:42:20,630 --> 01:42:26,430
长官，是我的班长，美国海军 哈罗德-Ｗ-道森准下士给我的命令…
Yes, Captain, I was given an order by my squad leader... Lance Corporal Harold W. Dawson, United States Marine Corps...

1608
01:42:26,430 --> 01:42:27,720
所以我执行了
and I followed it.

1609
01:42:49,120 --> 01:42:50,830
你说他会去哪？
Where do you think he is?

1610
01:42:53,040 --> 01:42:55,870
对多尼而言，那就是肯德瑞克下的命令
As far as Downey was concerned, it was an order from Kendrick.

1611
01:42:55,870 --> 01:42:57,920
是不是亲耳听到都一样
It doesn't matter that he didn't hear it firsthand.

1612
01:42:57,920 --> 01:43:01,090
他不会关心两者之间的区别
He doesn't distinguish between the two.

1613
01:43:05,180 --> 01:43:07,510
丹尼，我很抱歉
Danny, I'm sorry.

1614
01:43:08,390 --> 01:43:09,970
不用担心
Don't worry about it.

1615
01:43:10,010 --> 01:43:12,640
山姆和我刚才谈到我们应该…
Sam and I were just talking about how all we really have to do...

1616
01:43:12,640 --> 01:43:15,560
找些能指认间接命令的证人
is call some witnesses who will talk about implied orders.

1617
01:43:15,560 --> 01:43:18,230
在盘问道森之前让多尼再次充当证人
Maybe we can put Downey back on the stand before we get to Dawson.

1618
01:43:18,900 --> 01:43:23,690
照这样干下去 我们能让道森为暗杀肯尼迪负责
If we work at it, we can get Dawson charged with the Kennedy assassination.

1619
01:43:26,860 --> 01:43:28,030
你喝了酒？
Are you drunk?

1620
01:43:28,910 --> 01:43:31,740
喝了不少
Pretty much.

1621
01:43:34,120 --> 01:43:37,790
我去多弄点咖啡 我们今天要忙到很晚才行
I'll put on a pot of coffee. We've got a long night's work ahead.

1622
01:43:38,830 --> 01:43:41,300
她要去弄咖啡
She's gonna make coffee.

1623
01:43:42,380 --> 01:43:44,380
真不赖
That's nice.

1624
01:43:48,260 --> 01:43:51,180
多尼当时不在房间里
Downey wasn't in his room.

1625
01:43:51,180 --> 01:43:53,140
根本不在
Wasn't even there.

1626
01:43:54,520 --> 01:43:57,810
那是条非常重要的信息，你认为呢？
That was an important piece of information, don't you think?

1627
01:44:00,190 --> 01:44:04,570
丹尼，这是个打击，对此我很抱歉
Danny, it was a setback, and I'm sorry.

1628
01:44:04,570 --> 01:44:07,320
但还能补救，我们有马金森
But we fix it, and move on to Markinson.

1629
01:44:08,990 --> 01:44:10,780
马金森死了
Markinson's dead.

1630
01:44:16,620 --> 01:44:20,710
你真得感谢那些联邦密探，伙计
You really gotta hand it to those Federal Marshals, boy.

1631
01:44:20,710 --> 01:44:23,460
他不是用自己的鞋带上吊…
It's not like he hanged himself by his shoelaces...

1632
01:44:23,460 --> 01:44:26,130
也不是用偷藏的黄油刀割腕
or slashed his wrists with a concealed butter knife.

1633
01:44:26,130 --> 01:44:27,590
这家伙…
This guy...

1634
01:44:29,510 --> 01:44:33,260
身着全套制服，站在房间的中央…
got into full dress uniform, stood in the middle of that room...

1635
01:44:33,260 --> 01:44:36,480
从他的枪套里拔出一支蹭亮的手枪…
drew a nickel-plated pistol from his holster...

1636
01:44:36,480 --> 01:44:38,980
朝自己的嘴里开了一枪
and fired a bullet into his mouth.

1637
01:44:42,810 --> 01:44:46,740
既然我们已经没有证人了 我想我该喝上一点
Anyway, since we seem to be out of witnesses, I thought I'd drink a little.

1638
01:44:46,740 --> 01:44:48,990
我还是认为我们能赢
I still think we can win.

1639
01:44:50,990 --> 01:44:52,620
或许你也该喝点
Maybe you should drink a little.

1640
01:44:52,660 --> 01:44:57,750
我们明早去找伦道夫法官 要求押后二十四小时再审
We'll go to Randolph in the morning and make a motion for a 24-hour continuance.

1641
01:44:57,750 --> 01:45:01,120
我们这样做是为什么？ 传讯杰赛普上校
Why would we want to do that? To subpoena Colonel Jessup.

1642
01:45:02,170 --> 01:45:05,000
什么？ 别急，听我说完
What? Listen for a second. Hear me out.

1643
01:45:05,000 --> 01:45:07,090
我不想听，更不想听你说完
I won't listen, and I won't hear you out.

1644
01:45:07,130 --> 01:45:09,470
勇气可嘉，但毫无意义
Your passion is compelling, Jo. It's also useless.

1645
01:45:09,510 --> 01:45:12,720
劳登・多尼今天需要一个庭审律师
Louden Downey needed a trial lawyer today.

1646
01:45:15,640 --> 01:45:17,350
胆小鬼
You're chickenshit.

1647
01:45:17,390 --> 01:45:20,230
你想用今天的事作借口认输吗？
You're gonna use what happened today as an excuse to give up.

1648
01:45:21,600 --> 01:45:23,230
结束了
It's over.

1649
01:45:23,270 --> 01:45:25,900
你干嘛要向杰赛普要那份调令？
Why did you ask Jessup for the transfer order?

1650
01:45:25,900 --> 01:45:28,610
为什么？ 这有什么？
In Cuba. Why? What does it matter?

1651
01:45:28,610 --> 01:45:31,360
我想要那份该死的调令 胡说
I wanted the damn transfer order! Bullshit.

1652
01:45:31,360 --> 01:45:34,910
想要的话在五角大楼任何部门都能找到
You could've gotten it by calling any department at the Pentagon.

1653
01:45:34,910 --> 01:45:39,710
你不是想要那份调令 你是想看看杰赛普的反应
You didn't want the transfer order. You wanted to see Jessup's reaction.

1654
01:45:39,710 --> 01:45:42,880
直觉告诉你有内情 而马金森证实了这一点
You had an instinct, and it was confirmed by Markinson.

1655
01:45:42,880 --> 01:45:45,880
我们要让杰赛普出庭了结此事
Let's put Jessup on the stand and end this thing!

1656
01:45:45,880 --> 01:45:50,090
让杰赛普出庭又能有什么好结果呢？
What possible good could come from putting Jessup on the stand?

1657
01:45:50,090 --> 01:45:52,300
是他让肯德瑞克下的“红色条规”令
He told Kendrick to order the Code Red.

1658
01:45:52,300 --> 01:45:56,430
是吗？那太好了，你凭什么这么说？
He did? That's great! Why didn't you say so?

1659
01:45:56,430 --> 01:45:58,770
显然你能证明这一点
And of course you have proof of that!

1660
01:45:58,770 --> 01:46:03,060
对不起，我忘了 你因病缺席了法律学校的法律课
Oh, I'm sorry. I forgot. You were sick the day they taught law at law school.

1661
01:46:03,060 --> 01:46:05,610
让他出庭作证，让他自己说出来
You put him on the stand, and you get it from him.

1662
01:46:05,610 --> 01:46:09,740
让他自己说出来，是啊，没问题
Oh, we get it from him! Yes! No problem!

1663
01:46:09,740 --> 01:46:13,610
杰赛普上校，是不是你 下令对圣地亚哥执行“红色条规”？
Colonel Jessup, isn't it true that you ordered the Code Red on Santiago?

1664
01:46:13,610 --> 01:46:16,830
听着，我们都有点… 对不起，时间到
Listen, we're all a little... I'm sorry. Your time's run out.

1665
01:46:16,830 --> 01:46:20,000
该怎么打发输家呢？让我们的被告…
What do we have for the losers? Well, for our defendants...

1666
01:46:20,000 --> 01:46:22,410
在莱文沃斯堡（监狱）休养一辈子
it's a lifetime at exotic Fort Leavenworth.

1667
01:46:22,410 --> 01:46:25,460
至于辩护律师凯菲中尉…
And for Defense Counsel Kaffee...

1668
01:46:25,460 --> 01:46:27,290
让他上军事法庭
it's a court-martial!

1669
01:46:27,340 --> 01:46:30,590
没错，伙计，因为共谋及作伪证…
Yes, Johnny, after falsely accusing...

1670
01:46:30,590 --> 01:46:34,890
无端指控一名功勋卓著的海军军官…
a highly decorated Marine officer... of conspiracy and perjury...

1671
01:46:34,930 --> 01:46:38,100
凯菲中尉会有一份美好的前途…
Lieutenant Kaffee will have a long and prosperous career...

1672
01:46:38,100 --> 01:46:43,440
去沃克科洛布女子学校 执教打字机维修
teaching typewriter maintenance at the Rocco Clubo School for Women.

1673
01:46:43,440 --> 01:46:49,690
谢谢你参与 “我们该不该听从笨蛋的劝告？”的演出
Thank you for playing "Should we or should we not... follow the advice of the galactically stupid?"

1674
01:47:11,460 --> 01:47:14,630
很抱歉我毁了你的大好前程
I'm sorry I lost your set of steak knives.

1675
01:47:31,530 --> 01:47:33,530
别收拾了
Stop cleaning up.

1676
01:47:38,660 --> 01:47:40,660
山姆，别收拾了
Stop cleaning up.

1677
01:47:49,130 --> 01:47:52,130
想喝点吗？
Want a drink? Yeah.

1678
01:48:10,060 --> 01:48:13,360
你父亲以你为荣吗？ 别给自己太多压力
Is your father proud of you? Don't do this to yourself.

1679
01:48:13,360 --> 01:48:15,150
我敢说一定是
I'll bet he is.

1680
01:48:15,900 --> 01:48:19,320
我打赌他会不厌其烦地对邻居和亲戚说…
I'll bet he bores the shit out of the neighbors and relatives.

1681
01:48:19,320 --> 01:48:23,870
山姆上了'法律评论'栏目 他接了个大案子
"Sam's made LawReview. He's got a big case he's making.

1682
01:48:23,870 --> 01:48:27,080
他上庭了，正在为一个案子作辩护律师
He's arguing. He's making an argument."

1683
01:48:32,500 --> 01:48:36,880
我父亲一定很高兴看到我从法律学校毕业
I think my father would've enjoyed seeing me graduate from law school.

1684
01:48:40,220 --> 01:48:43,010
他一定为此欣喜若狂
I think he would've liked that an awful lot.

1685
01:48:45,520 --> 01:48:51,020
我有没有告诉过你 我在学校时写过一篇关于你父亲的论文？
Did I ever tell you I wrote a paper about your father in college? Yeah?

1686
01:48:51,060 --> 01:48:53,730
他是有史以来最好的律师之一
One of the best trial lawyers ever.

1687
01:48:53,730 --> 01:48:57,110
是的，的确是
Yes, he was.

1688
01:48:57,110 --> 01:48:59,490
如果我是道森和多尼…
If I were Dawson and Downey and I had a choice...

1689
01:48:59,490 --> 01:49:02,530
要从你和你父亲当中选代表律师的话…
between you or your father to represent me in this case...

1690
01:49:02,530 --> 01:49:05,580
不管什么时候我都会选你
I'd choose you any day of the week and twice on Sunday.

1691
01:49:05,580 --> 01:49:09,120
要知道你把肯德瑞克给镇住了
You should've seen yourself thunder away at Kendrick.

1692
01:49:12,080 --> 01:49:14,090
你会让杰赛普出庭吗？
Would you put Jessup on the stand?

1693
01:49:15,210 --> 01:49:16,170
不会
No

1694
01:49:17,760 --> 01:49:22,300
你觉得我父亲会这样做吗？ 以我们掌握的证据而言吗？
Do you think my father would have? With the evidence we got?

1695
01:49:22,300 --> 01:49:25,260
绝对不会
Not in a million years.

1696
01:49:25,260 --> 01:49:28,730
但问题是…现在所有的人都知道…
But here's the thing... and there's really know way of getting around this...

1697
01:49:28,730 --> 01:49:33,110
既不是你父亲也不是我 在担任首席辩护律师来处理…
Neither Lyle Kaffee nor Sam Weinberg are lead counsel for the defense...

1698
01:49:33,110 --> 01:49:36,320
这起政府起诉道森和多尼的案子
in the matter of U... S. V. Dawson and Downey.

1699
01:49:36,320 --> 01:49:40,400
所以唯一的问题就是…你会怎么做？
So there's really only one question... What would you do?

1700
01:49:52,290 --> 01:49:56,460
乔，上车，乔安妮，求你上车吧
Jo, get in the car. Joanne, please get in the car.

1701
01:49:56,460 --> 01:49:57,920
听我说…
Look...

1702
01:50:01,340 --> 01:50:05,760
我很抱歉冲你发火，我为我说的话道歉
I apologize. I was angry. I'm sorry about what I said.

1703
01:50:05,760 --> 01:50:08,430
我会让杰赛普出庭作证
I'm gonna put Jessup on the stand.

1704
01:50:28,620 --> 01:50:30,330
你觉得我们该怎么做？
What do you suggest we do?

1705
01:50:30,330 --> 01:50:32,580
证明杰赛普伪造了调令
I say we hit Jessup with the phony transfer order.

1706
01:50:32,620 --> 01:50:34,580
上哪去找证人？
What's a transfer order without a witness?

1707
01:50:34,630 --> 01:50:36,250
我们有证人 已经死了
We have a witness. A dead witness.

1708
01:50:36,290 --> 01:50:39,250
对一个次席律师来说这确实是个问题
In the hands of a lesser attorney, that would be a problem.

1709
01:50:39,250 --> 01:50:41,800
瞧瞧吧，昨晚他还在借酒消愁…
Look at this. Last night he's swimming in Jack Daniels...

1710
01:50:41,800 --> 01:50:44,590
现在却无所不能了
and now he can leap tall buildings in a single bound.

1711
01:50:44,590 --> 01:50:47,850
我又上好发条了，你们都坐好
I'm getting my second wind. Sit down, both of you.

1712
01:50:47,850 --> 01:50:52,480
很好，杰赛普让肯德瑞克 下“红色条规”令，肯德瑞克照做了
Good. Jessup told Kendrick to order the Code Red. Kendrick did.

1713
01:50:52,480 --> 01:50:54,770
当事人执行了命令，这我们无法证实
Our clients followed the order. The cover-up isn't our case.

1714
01:50:54,770 --> 01:50:59,480
要赢的话，得让杰赛普 告诉陪审团是他下的“红色条规”令
To win, Jessup needs to tell the court members that he ordered the Code Red.

1715
01:50:59,480 --> 01:51:03,280
你觉得你能让他说出来吗？ 我觉得他想说出来
You think you can get him to say it? I think he wants to say it.

1716
01:51:03,280 --> 01:51:05,610
他肯定因为不能说出来而恼火
I think he's pissed off that he's got to hide from us.

1717
01:51:05,610 --> 01:51:09,200
他想说出是他作的决定 这样事情就能解决
I think he wants to say that he made a command decision, and that's the end.

1718
01:51:09,200 --> 01:51:12,200
他吃早餐时三百码外…
He eats breakfast 300 yards away...

1719
01:51:12,200 --> 01:51:15,540
有四千名训练有素的古巴人想干掉他
from 4,000 Cubans that are trained to kill him.

1720
01:51:15,540 --> 01:51:17,670
没人能干涉他带兵的方式
No one's gonna tell him how to run his unit.

1721
01:51:17,710 --> 01:51:20,630
至少穿着娘娘腔制服的“哈佛嘴”不能
Least of all the Harvard mouth in his faggotywhite uniform.

1722
01:51:20,630 --> 01:51:22,800
我得激怒他，让他进行反击…
I need to shake him, put him on the defensive...

1723
01:51:22,840 --> 01:51:25,590
然后领着他自掘坟墓
and lead him right where he's dying to go.

1724
01:51:25,590 --> 01:51:28,640
就这样？这就是计划？ 这就是计划
That's it? That's the plan? That's the plan.

1725
01:51:28,640 --> 01:51:31,890
你打算怎么做？ 还没头绪
How are you gonna do it? I have no idea.

1726
01:51:31,890 --> 01:51:34,100
我需要我的球棒 需要什么？
I need my bat. Your what?

1727
01:51:34,100 --> 01:51:36,440
拿着球棒我的思路更敏捷，它在哪？
I think better with my bat. Where's my bat?

1728
01:51:36,440 --> 01:51:39,980
我把它放在壁橱里了 你把它放在壁橱里了？
I put it in the closet. You put it in the closet?

1729
01:51:39,980 --> 01:51:43,940
我被它绊了一下 永远别把它放到壁橱里
I was tripping on it. Don't ever put that bat in the closet.

1730
01:51:43,940 --> 01:51:47,870
拿着球棒能让他思路更敏捷？ 我能理解
He thinks better with his bat? I can understand that.

1731
01:51:59,210 --> 01:52:02,210
呆在这，我去趟办公室
Stay here. I'm going to the office for a while.

1732
01:52:04,630 --> 01:52:07,340
拿着球棒确实能给他灵感
He does think better with that bat.

1733
01:52:08,800 --> 01:52:12,560
古巴关达那摩湾 打出电话记录

1734
01:52:29,780 --> 01:52:33,200
山姆，我要你替我办件事
Sam, I need you to do something for me.

1735
01:52:36,290 --> 01:52:39,630
怎么了？ 得去趟安德鲁斯
What's going on? Gotta go out to Andrews.

1736
01:53:03,400 --> 01:53:05,400
山姆呢？ 还在路上
Where's Sam? He's on his way.

1737
01:53:05,400 --> 01:53:07,400
他找到人没有？ 找到了
Did he get the guys? Yeah.

1738
01:53:07,400 --> 01:53:10,490
能和你聊几句吗？
Listen, can I talk to you for a second?

1739
01:53:10,490 --> 01:53:12,780
当然，没问题
Oh, yeah, sure.

1740
01:53:23,170 --> 01:53:24,840
你感觉怎么样？
How you feeling?

1741
01:53:26,210 --> 01:53:29,880
我看杰赛普今天要举手投降了
Well, I think Jessup's gonna have his hands full today.

1742
01:53:32,510 --> 01:53:34,510
听我说，丹尼…
Listen, Danny...

1743
01:53:35,640 --> 01:53:38,140
你今天上去的时候…
when you're out there today...

1744
01:53:38,140 --> 01:53:41,350
如果感觉计划不能成功…
if you feel like it's not gonna happen...

1745
01:53:41,350 --> 01:53:44,570
如果你觉得他不会说出来…
if you feel like he's not gonna say it...

1746
01:53:44,570 --> 01:53:46,190
就别勉强行事
don't go for it.

1747
01:53:47,690 --> 01:53:49,990
不然你会惹上麻烦
You could get in trouble.

1748
01:53:49,990 --> 01:53:52,110
我是内政部的特别律师…
I'm special counsel for Internal Affairs...

1749
01:53:52,160 --> 01:53:54,780
我知道那会惹来多少麻烦
and I'm telling you you could get in a lot of trouble.

1750
01:53:54,780 --> 01:53:56,830
等等，盖洛维少校…
Wait, Lieutenant Commander Galloway...

1751
01:53:56,870 --> 01:54:01,160
你不是在奉劝我放弃这个重要证人吧？
you're not suggesting that I back off a material witness?

1752
01:54:01,160 --> 01:54:04,460
如果你觉得不能引他上钩的话，是的
If you think you can't get him, yeah.

1753
01:54:06,590 --> 01:54:08,300
全体起立
All rise.

1754
01:54:13,090 --> 01:54:16,180
山姆呢？ 就快到了
Where's Sam? He's on his way.

1755
01:54:21,730 --> 01:54:24,400
传第一位证人 他在哪？
Call your first witness. Where is he?

1756
01:54:24,400 --> 01:54:26,770
他会来的 中尉
He'll be here. Lieutenant.

1757
01:54:26,770 --> 01:54:28,480
传你的证人
Call your witness.

1758
01:54:35,120 --> 01:54:37,870
辩方传唤内森・杰赛普上校
Defense calls Colonel Nathan Jessup.

1759
01:54:54,590 --> 01:54:57,470
杰赛普上校，请举起你的右手，长官
Colonel Jessup, would you raise your right hand please, sir?

1760
01:54:57,470 --> 01:55:01,020
你能发誓你在法庭上所说的一切…
Do you solemnly swear that the testimony you will give in this court-martial...

1761
01:55:01,020 --> 01:55:04,520
完全属实，绝无虚假吗？
will be the truth, the whole truth and nothing but the truth?

1762
01:55:04,520 --> 01:55:05,940
我发誓
Yes, I do.

1763
01:55:05,980 --> 01:55:07,480
请坐下，长官
Have a seat please, sir.

1764
01:55:09,110 --> 01:55:12,610
请说出你的姓名，军衔和现任职务 以便法庭记录
Would you state your name, rank and current billet for the record, sir?

1765
01:55:12,610 --> 01:55:15,820
内森・Ｒ・杰赛普，上校…
Colonel Nathan R. Jessup, commanding officer...

1766
01:55:15,820 --> 01:55:19,200
古巴关达那摩湾 美国海军陆战队指挥官
Marine Ground Forces, Guantanamo Bay, Cuba.

1767
01:55:19,200 --> 01:55:21,580
谢谢，长官 他还没来
Thank you, sir. He's not here.

1768
01:55:27,330 --> 01:55:30,960
上校，你得知圣地亚哥 写给海军调查处的那封信时…
Colonel, when you learned of Santiago's letter to the N.I. S...

1769
01:55:30,960 --> 01:55:34,170
曾和你手下两位高级军官开过会
you had a meeting with your two senior officers.

1770
01:55:34,170 --> 01:55:36,300
是这样吗？ 是的
Is that right? Yes.

1771
01:55:36,300 --> 01:55:39,970
是排长乔纳森・肯德瑞克上尉…
The platoon commander, Lieutenant Jonathan Kendrick...

1772
01:55:39,970 --> 01:55:43,730
和行政长官马修・马金森中校吗？
and the executive officer, Lieutenant Colonel Matthew Markinson.

1773
01:55:43,730 --> 01:55:45,270
是的
Yes.

1774
01:55:45,310 --> 01:55:49,900
现在马金森中校已经死了，是这样吗？
And at present Colonel Markinson is dead. Is that right?

1775
01:55:49,900 --> 01:55:54,030
反对，不知辩方律师这是什么意思
Objection. I'd like to know just what the defense counsel is implying.

1776
01:55:54,030 --> 01:55:57,530
意思很简单，就是马金森中校已经死了
I'm implying simply that at present Colonel Markinson is not alive.

1777
01:55:57,530 --> 01:56:01,330
杰赛普上校 用不着在法庭上确认这个消息
Colonel Jessup doesn't need to appear in court to confirm that information.

1778
01:56:01,330 --> 01:56:06,710
我是想确认证人是否知道两天前 中校用一支点四五手枪自尽了
I just wasn't sure the witness was aware that two days ago... the colonel took his own life with a.45-caliber pistol.

1779
01:56:06,710 --> 01:56:09,250
证人知道了，法庭知道了…
The witness is aware, the court is aware...

1780
01:56:09,250 --> 01:56:11,250
现在陪审团也知道了
and now the court members are aware.

1781
01:56:11,250 --> 01:56:14,880
谢谢你为我们带来这个消息
We thank you for bringing this to our attention.

1782
01:56:14,880 --> 01:56:16,680
继续吧，中尉
Move on, Lieutenant...

1783
01:56:16,680 --> 01:56:18,510
好的，法官大人
Yes, sir.

1784
01:56:18,510 --> 01:56:22,220
上校，你在会上 给肯德瑞克上尉下过命令是吗？
Colonel, you gave Lieutenant Kendrick an order at this meeting, right?

1785
01:56:22,220 --> 01:56:26,640
我让肯德瑞克告诉他的手下 不许碰圣地亚哥
I told Kendrick to tell his men that Santiago wasn't to be touched.

1786
01:56:26,640 --> 01:56:29,650
你是不是也给马金森中校下过命令？
And did you give an order to Colonel Markinson as well?

1787
01:56:29,650 --> 01:56:35,240
我命令马金森立刻将圣地亚哥调离基地
I ordered Markinson to have Santiago transferred off the base immediately.

1788
01:56:35,240 --> 01:56:37,070
为什么？
Why?

1789
01:56:37,110 --> 01:56:40,950
我担心一旦信的内容泄露出去 他可能会有生命危险
I felt his life might be in danger once word of the letter got out.

1790
01:56:40,950 --> 01:56:42,410
致命的危险？
Grave danger?

1791
01:56:42,450 --> 01:56:44,700
还能是什么？
Is there another kind?

1792
01:56:48,250 --> 01:56:52,250
上校，这是你和马金森联合签名的调令…
Colonel, we have the transfer order that you and Markinson co-signed...

1793
01:56:52,250 --> 01:56:56,970
命令圣地亚哥乘第二天凌晨六点的航班 离开关达那摩
ordering that Santiago be on a flight leaving Guantanamo at 6:00 the next day.

1794
01:56:56,970 --> 01:57:02,260
那是最早的航班吗？ 六点是最早飞离基地的航班
Was that the first flight? The 0600 was the first flight.

1795
01:57:05,930 --> 01:57:09,390
你是今早乘飞机来华盛顿的对吗？
You flew up to Washington this morning. Is that right?

1796
01:57:09,390 --> 01:57:12,860
我注意到你今天是穿着高级制服上的法庭
I notice you'rewearing your class "A" dress uniform in court today.

1797
01:57:12,860 --> 01:57:16,110
彼此彼此，中尉 你在飞机上也是这身穿着吗？
As are you, Lieutenant. Did you wear that on the plane?

1798
01:57:16,110 --> 01:57:18,990
法官大人，这与本案有什么关…
Please the court, is this dialogue relevant to anything...

1799
01:57:18,990 --> 01:57:21,740
辩方难得有机会请这位证人作证
Defense didn't have the opportunity to depose this witness.

1800
01:57:21,740 --> 01:57:25,580
我想多问几个问题 请注意提问范围
I'd ask for a little latitude. A very little latitude.

1801
01:57:26,080 --> 01:57:27,160
上校？
Colonel?

1802
01:57:27,700 --> 01:57:29,790
我在飞机上穿的是便服
I wore utilities on the plane.

1803
01:57:29,790 --> 01:57:32,920
不过你带着军装是吧？ 是的
You brought your dress uniform? Yes.

1804
01:57:32,920 --> 01:57:36,420
那么牙刷，剃须刀，内衣呢？ 法官大人…
Toothbrush, shaving kit, underwear? Your Honor!

1805
01:57:36,420 --> 01:57:38,840
难道上校的内衣也是国家机密吗？
Is the colonel's underwear a matter of national security?

1806
01:57:38,840 --> 01:57:42,300
两位，你最好尽快问完这些，中尉
Gentlemen! You better get somewhere fast with this, Lieutenant.

1807
01:57:42,300 --> 01:57:44,430
是，大人，上校？
Yes, sir. Colonel?

1808
01:57:45,470 --> 01:57:49,270
我带了一套替换衣服和一些私人用品
I brought a change of clothes and some personal items.

1809
01:57:49,270 --> 01:57:51,190
谢谢
Thank you.

1810
01:57:51,230 --> 01:57:54,940
道森和多尼在六号晚上被拘捕后…
After Dawson and Downey's arrest on the night of the sixth...

1811
01:57:54,940 --> 01:57:59,280
圣地亚哥的房间就被封了 这是房内的物品清单
Santiago's barracks were sealed off and its contents inventoried.

1812
01:57:59,280 --> 01:58:02,660
四条迷彩裤，三件卡其衬衣…
"Four pairs camouflage pants, three long-sleeve khaki shirts...

1813
01:58:02,660 --> 01:58:06,620
三双靴子，四双军袜，三件军用Ｔ恤…
three pairs of boots, four pairs green socks, three green T-shirts..."

1814
01:58:06,620 --> 01:58:09,620
法官大人，我们要一直这么问下去吗？
Please the court, is there a question anywhere in our future?

1815
01:58:09,620 --> 01:58:12,830
凯菲中尉，我得要求你提出你的问题
Lieutenant Kaffee, I have to ask you to state your question.

1816
01:58:12,830 --> 01:58:15,710
为什么圣地亚哥没有收拾行李？
I'm wondering why Santiago wasn't packed.

1817
01:58:17,710 --> 01:58:21,090
我稍后会告诉大家，先来看看这个
I'll tell you what. We'll get back to that one in a minute.

1818
01:58:21,880 --> 01:58:25,300
这是过去二十四小时 从你们基地打出的所有电话记录
This is a record of all phone calls made from your base in the past 24 hours.

1819
01:58:25,300 --> 01:58:28,970
在被传唤来华盛顿之后，你打过三个电话
After being subpoenaed to Washington, you made three calls.

1820
01:58:28,970 --> 01:58:31,350
你熟悉这些号码吗？
Do you recognize those number, sir?

1821
01:58:31,350 --> 01:58:34,560
一个打给维州匡迪科基地的菲茨上校
I called Colonel Fitzhughes in Quantico, Virginia.

1822
01:58:34,560 --> 01:58:37,440
让他知道我要来这
I wanted to let him know that I would be in town.

1823
01:58:37,440 --> 01:58:41,070
第二个是打给众议院军事委员会 的里奇蒙德议员…
The second call was to arrange a meeting with Congressman Richmond...

1824
01:58:41,070 --> 01:58:43,410
和他商量见一下面
of the House Armed Services Committee.

1825
01:58:43,410 --> 01:58:46,530
第三个是打给我妹妹伊莉莎白
And the third call was to my sister Elizabeth.

1826
01:58:46,530 --> 01:58:48,700
为什么要打这个电话，长官？
Why did you make that call, sir?

1827
01:58:48,700 --> 01:58:52,160
我想请她今晚一起吃晚饭
I thought she might like to have dinner tonight.

1828
01:58:52,160 --> 01:58:55,630
我会制止的 这些是九月六日从关达那摩…
I'm gonna stop this. These are phone records from Gitmo...

1829
01:58:55,630 --> 01:58:59,920
打出的电话记录，而这是圣地亚哥…
for September 6, and these are 14 letters...

1830
01:58:59,920 --> 01:59:02,720
在九个月内写的十四封信…
that Santiago wrote in nine months...

1831
01:59:02,720 --> 01:59:05,970
请求…事实上是乞求…调离
requesting... in fact, begging... for a transfer.

1832
01:59:05,970 --> 01:59:09,220
在得知终于被允许调离的消息之后…
Upon hearing the news that he was finally getting his transfer...

1833
01:59:09,220 --> 01:59:13,270
圣地亚哥非常兴奋 知道他给多少人打过电话吗？
Santiago was so excited that do you know how many people he called?

1834
01:59:13,270 --> 01:59:15,810
没给任何人打过
Zero. Nobody.

1835
01:59:15,810 --> 01:59:19,730
没有一个电话告知他的父母他要回家了
Not one call to his parents saying he was coming home.

1836
01:59:19,730 --> 01:59:23,030
没有一个电话打给朋友说 “你能来机场接我吗”
Not one call to a friend, saying, "Can you pick me up at the airport?"

1837
01:59:23,030 --> 01:59:26,950
半夜时他在床上睡着了，依你所说…
He was asleep in his bed at midnight, and according to you...

1838
01:59:26,950 --> 01:59:29,540
他六小时后就要上飞机
he was getting on a plane in six hours.

1839
01:59:29,540 --> 01:59:33,210
可他所有的东西 还整整齐齐地放在壁橱里…
Yet everything he owned was hanging neatly in his closet...

1840
01:59:33,210 --> 01:59:35,870
整整齐齐地叠放在扁条箱里
and folded neatly in his footlocker.

1841
01:59:35,870 --> 01:59:39,710
你只离开一天 就收拾了行李并打了三个电话
You were leaving for one day. You packed a bag and made three calls.

1842
01:59:39,710 --> 01:59:44,220
而圣地亚哥离开后这辈子都不会再回来…
Santiago was leaving for the rest of his life...

1843
01:59:45,840 --> 01:59:48,680
但他没打一个电话…
and he hadn't called a soul...

1844
01:59:48,680 --> 01:59:51,430
没收拾一件物品
and he hadn't packed a thing.

1845
01:59:54,560 --> 01:59:56,400
这你能解释吗？
Can you explain that?

1846
01:59:58,860 --> 02:00:01,190
事实是根本没有调令
The fact is, there was no transfer order.

1847
02:00:01,190 --> 02:00:04,030
圣地亚哥哪都不会去，是不是，上校？
Santiago wasn't going anywhere. Isn't that right, Colonel?

1848
02:00:04,030 --> 02:00:07,570
反对，法官大人，显然凯菲中尉意图…
Objection. Your Honor, it's obvious that Lieutenant Kaffee's intention...

1849
02:00:07,570 --> 02:00:09,950
诽谤一位高级海军军官…
is the smear a high-ranking Marine officer...

1850
02:00:09,950 --> 02:00:13,700
希望以这种无礼的举动来达到他的目的
in the hope that the mere appearance of impropriety will win him points.

1851
02:00:13,700 --> 02:00:17,710
大人，我请求对凯菲中尉予以惩戒…
It's my recommendation, sir, that Lieutenant Kaffee be reprimanded...

1852
02:00:17,710 --> 02:00:20,670
以此向证人表示法庭最诚恳的歉意
and the witness be excused with the court's deepest apologies.

1853
02:00:22,420 --> 02:00:25,630
驳回请求… 你的反对已记入笔录
Overruled. Your objection is noted.

1854
02:00:26,590 --> 02:00:27,720
上校？
Colonel?

1855
02:00:31,970 --> 02:00:33,850
很可笑吗，长官？
Is this funny, sir?

1856
02:00:33,890 --> 02:00:37,270
不，不是可笑，是可悲
No, it's not. It's tragic.

1857
02:00:37,270 --> 02:00:40,060
可以回答吗？ 当然
Do you have an answer? Absolutely.

1858
02:00:40,060 --> 02:00:43,940
我得说，我没有这见鬼的第一线索
My answer is, I don't have the first damn clue.

1859
02:00:43,940 --> 02:00:47,780
也许他习惯早起，愿意在早上收拾行李
Maybe he was an early riser and liked to pack in the morning.

1860
02:00:47,780 --> 02:00:50,660
也许他根本没什么朋友
And maybe he didn't have any friends.

1861
02:00:50,660 --> 02:00:54,240
我是受过教育，但我恐怕答不出…
I'm an educated man, but I'm afraid I can't speak intelligently...

1862
02:00:54,240 --> 02:00:57,960
关于威廉・圣地亚哥出行习惯的智力题
about the travel habits of William Santiago.

1863
02:00:57,960 --> 02:01:03,170
我只知道他已经被安排在六点离开基地
What I do know is that he was set to leave the base at 0600.

1864
02:01:03,880 --> 02:01:09,050
现在，难道叫我到这来 就是为了回答这些问题吗？
Now, are these really the questions that I was called here to answer?

1865
02:01:09,050 --> 02:01:11,470
电话以及扁条箱？
Phone calls and footlockers?

1866
02:01:11,470 --> 02:01:15,270
请告诉我你还想知道些什么，中尉
Please tell me that you have something more, Lieutenant.

1867
02:01:15,270 --> 02:01:19,100
这次审判将决定两名陆战队员的命运
These two Marines are on trial for their lives.

1868
02:01:19,100 --> 02:01:23,690
请告诉我他们的律师 不会将希望寄托在电话清单上
Please tell me that their lawyer hasn't pinned their hopes to a phone bill.

1869
02:01:26,030 --> 02:01:29,570
你还有其他问题要问吗，律师？
Do you have any other questions for me, counselor?

1870
02:01:38,040 --> 02:01:39,160
凯菲中尉？
Lieutenant Kaffee?

1871
02:01:48,220 --> 02:01:51,890
中尉，你还有什么问题要问证人吗？
Lieutenant, do you have anything further for this witness?

1872
02:01:59,270 --> 02:02:01,600
谢谢，丹尼，我喜欢华盛顿
Thanks, Danny. I love Washington.

1873
02:02:01,600 --> 02:02:04,270
抱歉，我还没让你走呢
Excuse me. I didn't dismiss you.

1874
02:02:05,270 --> 02:02:07,070
你说什么？
I beg your pardon?

1875
02:02:07,110 --> 02:02:11,780
我的盘问还没有结束，坐下
I'm not through with my examination. Sit down.

1876
02:02:13,370 --> 02:02:16,200
上校 什么意思？
Colonel. What's that?

1877
02:02:16,200 --> 02:02:18,910
你该称呼我 “上校” 或 “长官”
I'd appreciate it if you'd address me as "colonel" or "sir."

1878
02:02:18,910 --> 02:02:20,540
这是我应得的尊重
I believe I've earned it.

1879
02:02:20,580 --> 02:02:24,880
辩方律师应该称呼证人 “上校” 或 “长官”
Defense counsel will address the witness as "colonel" or "sir."

1880
02:02:24,880 --> 02:02:27,920
我不知道你管理的是什么鬼单位
I don't know what the hell kind of unit you're running here.

1881
02:02:27,920 --> 02:02:31,800
证人应该称呼法官 “法官大人” 或者 “庭上”
The witness will address this court as "judge" or "your honor."

1882
02:02:31,800 --> 02:02:36,720
我很肯定这是我应得的尊重 请坐，上校
I'm quite certain I've earned it. Take your seat, Colonel.

1883
02:02:41,520 --> 02:02:45,730
你现在想讨论什么？我最喜欢的颜色吗？
What do you want to discuss now? My favorite color?

1884
02:02:46,900 --> 02:02:49,650
上校，最早离开基地的航班是在六点吗？
Colonel, the 6:00 a.m. Flight was the first one off the base?

1885
02:02:49,650 --> 02:02:50,740
是的
Yes.

1886
02:02:50,780 --> 02:02:52,910
没有航班在七小时前离开…
There wasn't a flight that left seven hours earlier...

1887
02:02:52,910 --> 02:02:55,320
并于凌晨两点降落在安德鲁斯吗？
and landed at Andrews Air Force Base at 2:00 a. M?

1888
02:02:55,320 --> 02:02:58,370
中尉，我们不是问过这个问题了吗？
Lieutenant, I think we've covered this, haven't we?

1889
02:02:59,330 --> 02:03:01,500
法官大人，这些是…
Your Honor, these are the tower chiefs logs...

1890
02:03:01,540 --> 02:03:04,420
关达那摩和安德鲁斯指挥塔的飞行日志
for both Guantanamo Bay and Andrews Air Force Base.

1891
02:03:04,420 --> 02:03:07,880
关达那摩没有航班在二十三点离开的记录
The Guantanamo log lists no flight that left at 11:00 p.m.

1892
02:03:07,880 --> 02:03:10,550
安德鲁斯也没有航班在两点降落的记录
The Andrews log lists no flight that landed at 2:00 a.m.

1893
02:03:10,550 --> 02:03:13,220
辩方希望能从两个基地得到证实
I'd like to admit them as defense exhibits Alpha and Bravo.

1894
02:03:13,930 --> 02:03:17,510
什么意思？ 你想证实一趟从没有过的航班吗？
I don't understand. You're admitting evidence of a flight that never existed.

1895
02:03:17,510 --> 02:03:20,060
我们相信有，大人
We believe it did, sir.

1896
02:03:20,060 --> 02:03:23,440
辩方请求传空军 奥马雷和罗德瑞格作证
Defense will be calling Airmen Cecil O'Malley and Anthony Rodriguez.

1897
02:03:23,440 --> 02:03:26,520
他们是七号两点种时当班的地勤人员
They were working the ground crew at Andrews at 2:00 a.m. On the 7th.

1898
02:03:26,520 --> 02:03:29,440
他们不在证人名单上 第三度答辩证人…
These men weren't on the list. Rebuttal witnesses, Your Honor...

1899
02:03:29,440 --> 02:03:33,820
是特许被传唤 在直接盘问下提供证词的
called specifically to refute testimony offered under direct examination.

1900
02:03:33,820 --> 02:03:36,870
请求通过 真是荒谬
I'll allow the witnesses. This is ridiculous.

1901
02:03:36,870 --> 02:03:41,410
上校，刚才… 看在上帝份上，查查指挥塔的飞行日志吧
Colonel, a moment ago... Check the tower logs, for God's sake!

1902
02:03:42,250 --> 02:03:44,500
现在有空军可以证实，长官
We'll get to the airmen in just a minute, sir.

1903
02:03:45,460 --> 02:03:47,460
你刚才说曾命令肯德瑞克…
A moment ago you said that you ordered Lieutenant Kendrick...

1904
02:03:47,460 --> 02:03:51,590
告诉他的手下不许碰圣地亚哥
to tell his men that Santiago wasn't to be touched.

1905
02:03:51,590 --> 02:03:53,170
没错
That's right.

1906
02:03:53,220 --> 02:03:56,010
但他是不是清楚你的命令？
And Lieutenant Kendrick was clear on what you wanted?

1907
02:03:56,010 --> 02:03:57,840
完全清楚
Crystal.

1908
02:03:57,890 --> 02:04:01,100
他有没有可能忽视这个命令？
Any chance Lieutenant Kendrick ignored the order?

1909
02:04:01,100 --> 02:04:03,140
忽视这个命令？
Ignored the order?

1910
02:04:03,140 --> 02:04:06,310
他有没有可能忘记呢？ 不
Any chance he forgot about it?

1911
02:04:06,310 --> 02:04:10,120
有没有可能他离开你的办公室后说 “老头子错了”呢？
Any chance Lieutenant Kendrick left your office and said, "The old man is wrong"?

1912
02:04:10,940 --> 02:04:11,950
不
No

1913
02:04:12,480 --> 02:04:14,820
当肯德瑞克上尉告诉手下…
When Lieutenant Kendrick spoke to the platoon...

1914
02:04:14,820 --> 02:04:18,200
不许碰圣地亚哥时 他们有没有可能当成耳边风？
and ordered them not to touch Santiago, any chance they ignored him?

1915
02:04:19,530 --> 02:04:22,620
你曾在步兵团服过役吗，小子？
You ever served in an infantry unit, son?

1916
02:04:22,620 --> 02:04:26,000
没有，长官 曾经上过前线吗？
No, sir. Ever served in a forward area?

1917
02:04:26,420 --> 02:04:30,340
没有，长官 有没有把性命交给过别人…
Ever put your life in another man's hands?

1918
02:04:30,340 --> 02:04:33,800
或让别人把性命托付给你？ 没有，长官
Asked him to put his life in yours?

1919
02:04:34,260 --> 02:04:36,260
我们要服从命令，小子
We follow orders, son.

1920
02:04:36,300 --> 02:04:39,340
得服从命令，不然就会出人命
We follow orders, or people die.

1921
02:04:39,340 --> 02:04:42,560
就这么简单，听明白了吗？
It's that simple. Are we clear?

1922
02:04:42,560 --> 02:04:44,430
是的，长官
Yes, sir.

1923
02:04:44,470 --> 02:04:46,230
听明白没有？
Are we clear?

1924
02:04:46,270 --> 02:04:48,270
完全明白
Crystal.

1925
02:04:50,360 --> 02:04:55,070
在我盘问奥马雷和罗德瑞格之前 还有个问题
I have just one more question before I call Airmen O'Malley and Rodriguez.

1926
02:04:56,240 --> 02:05:00,570
既然你下了命令不许碰圣地亚哥…
If you gave an order that Santiago wasn't to be touched...

1927
02:05:00,570 --> 02:05:03,200
而你的命令总是能得到遵从…
and your orders are always followed...

1928
02:05:05,080 --> 02:05:08,290
那圣地亚哥为什么会有危险？
then why would Santiago be in danger?

1929
02:05:10,080 --> 02:05:13,960
为什么他必须被调离基地呢？
Why would it be necessary to transfer him off the base?

1930
02:05:19,430 --> 02:05:22,640
圣地亚哥是一名不合格的陆战队员
Santiago was a substandard Marine.

1931
02:05:22,640 --> 02:05:25,100
他被调走… 你刚才可没这样说
He was being transferred... That's not what you said!

1932
02:05:25,100 --> 02:05:28,810
你说要调走他是因为他有生命危险 是的
You said he was being transferred because he was in grave danger.

1933
02:05:28,810 --> 02:05:31,810
我说 “致命的危险吗？” 你说 “还能是什么？”
I said, "Grave danger?" You said, "Is there any other kind?"

1934
02:05:31,810 --> 02:05:34,400
我记得我说过什么 我可以念给你听
I recall what I said. I can have it read back to you.

1935
02:05:34,400 --> 02:05:37,490
我知道我说过什么，用不着念给我听
I know what I said! I don't have to have it read back to me.

1936
02:05:37,490 --> 02:05:41,200
那为什么有两项命令？上校？
Then why the two orders? Colonel?

1937
02:05:43,030 --> 02:05:45,790
有时候那些手下会自作主张
Sometimes men take matters into their own hands.

1938
02:05:45,790 --> 02:05:48,960
你说得很清楚，你的部下决不会自作主张
You've made it clear that your men never take matters into their own hands.

1939
02:05:48,960 --> 02:05:51,000
他们得服从命令，否则会出人命
Your men follow orders, or people die.

1940
02:05:51,000 --> 02:05:53,710
那圣地亚哥应不应该有危险呢？
So Santiago should have been in danger, should he?

1941
02:05:53,710 --> 02:05:57,630
你这个无礼的小杂种 大人，我请求休庭
You snotty little bastard. I'd like to ask for a recess.

1942
02:05:57,630 --> 02:06:01,390
我要求证人回答这个问题 请证人回答问题
I'd like an answer to the question. The court will wait for an answer.

1943
02:06:02,090 --> 02:06:04,510
既然肯德瑞克曾经下令…
If Lieutenant Kendrick gave an order...

1944
02:06:04,510 --> 02:06:07,560
不许碰圣地亚哥…
that Santiago wasn't to be touched...

1945
02:06:07,560 --> 02:06:09,520
那他为什么非得调走？
then why did he have to be transferred?

1946
02:06:10,890 --> 02:06:11,810
上校？
Colonel?

1947
02:06:12,400 --> 02:06:16,650
肯德瑞克下“红色条规”令 是因为你授意他那样去做
Lieutenant Kendrick ordered the Code Red because that's what you told him to do!

1948
02:06:16,650 --> 02:06:19,740
反对 然后你却让他们做替罪羊
Object! And then you cut these guys loose!

1949
02:06:19,740 --> 02:06:23,370
我要告你藐视法庭 你还窜改了飞行日志
I'll hold you in contempt. You doctored the logbook!

1950
02:06:23,370 --> 02:06:26,290
该死的，凯菲 是你在藐视法庭
Damn it, Kaffee! Consider yourself in contempt.

1951
02:06:26,290 --> 02:06:29,160
杰赛普上校 是你下的“红色条规”令吗？
Colonel Jessup, did you order the Code Red?

1952
02:06:29,160 --> 02:06:32,790
你不必回答这个问题 我要回答
You don't have to answer that. I'll answer the question.

1953
02:06:32,790 --> 02:06:34,880
你想要答案？ 我有这个权利
You want answers? I think I'm entitled!

1954
02:06:34,920 --> 02:06:37,380
你想知道答案？ 我想知道事实
You want answers? I want the truth!

1955
02:06:37,380 --> 02:06:40,550
你受不了这个事实
You can't handle the truth!

1956
02:06:40,550 --> 02:06:45,300
小子，我们生活的世界 需要有人手持武器来守卫边疆
Son, we live in a world that has walls... and those walls have to be guarded by men with guns.

1957
02:06:45,300 --> 02:06:49,770
谁来守卫？是你？ 还是你，温伯格中尉？
Who's gonna do it? You? You, Lieutenant Weinberg?

1958
02:06:49,770 --> 02:06:53,810
我的责任比你们能想象到的要重要得多
I have a greater responsibility than you can possibly fathom.

1959
02:06:53,810 --> 02:06:57,360
你为圣地亚哥抱屈 却来折腾这些海军陆战队员
You weep for Santiago, and you curse the Marines.

1960
02:06:57,360 --> 02:07:01,280
你有幸不必知道我知道的事…
You have the luxury of not knowing what I know...

1961
02:07:01,280 --> 02:07:05,450
圣地亚哥的死固然是个悲剧 但可能拯救了更多的性命
that Santiago's death, while tragic, probably saved lives.

1962
02:07:05,450 --> 02:07:11,410
至于我的存在方式，对你来说是怪异 和不可理解的，但却是在拯救生命
And my existence, while grotesque and incomprehensible to you, saves lives!

1963
02:07:11,410 --> 02:07:15,630
你不想面对这个事实 是因为你未曾提起的潜意识里…
You don't want the truth because deep down you don't talk about...

1964
02:07:15,630 --> 02:07:17,840
你需要我来保家卫国
you want me on that wall.

1965
02:07:17,840 --> 02:07:20,630
你需要我来保家卫国
You need me on that wall!

1966
02:07:20,630 --> 02:07:25,340
我们惯用的词语是尊严，军规，忠诚
We use words like honor, code, loyalty.

1967
02:07:25,340 --> 02:07:29,140
对这些词语我们不惜用生命来捍卫
We use these words as the backbone of a life spent defending something.

1968
02:07:29,140 --> 02:07:31,180
你们却拿来当儿戏
You use them as a punch line.

1969
02:07:31,180 --> 02:07:35,100
我既没有时间也没有兴趣 向你这种人作解释
I have neither the time nor the inclination to explain myself...

1970
02:07:35,100 --> 02:07:39,360
你在我提供的自由被褥下高枕无忧 却反过来质疑…
to a man who rises and sleeps under the blanket of the freedom I provide...

1971
02:07:39,360 --> 02:07:42,280
我提供自由的方式
and then questions the manner in which I provide it!

1972
02:07:42,280 --> 02:07:45,610
我看你最好是说声谢谢然后滚到一边去
I would rather you just said thank you and went on your way.

1973
02:07:45,610 --> 02:07:49,450
否则，我建议你拿上武器去站岗
Otherwise, I suggest you pick up a weapon and stand a post.

1974
02:07:49,450 --> 02:07:54,410
不然休想我给你 你自以为该有的什么鬼权利
Either way, I don't give a damn what you think you are entitled to!

1975
02:07:54,410 --> 02:07:56,120
是你下的“红色条规”令吗？
Did you order the Code Red?

1976
02:07:56,170 --> 02:07:58,130
我身负重任… 是你下的命令吗？
I did the job... Did you order the Code Red?

1977
02:07:58,170 --> 02:08:00,550
该死的，没错，是我
You're goddamned right I did!

1978
02:08:11,560 --> 02:08:14,730
法官大人，我提议让陪审团回避…
Please the court, I suggest the members be dismissed...

1979
02:08:14,730 --> 02:08:18,020
然后直接依据39-Ａ条款开庭
so that we can move to an immediate Article 39-A session.

1980
02:08:18,020 --> 02:08:20,520
这是证人的权利
The witness has rights.

1981
02:08:20,520 --> 02:08:22,820
罗斯上尉？
Captain Ross?

1982
02:08:26,990 --> 02:08:28,030
杰克？
Jack?

1983
02:08:33,620 --> 02:08:37,370
请陪审团到休息室等候进一步指示
The members of the court will retire to an anteroom until further instructed.

1984
02:08:37,370 --> 02:08:39,210
全体起立
All rise.

1985
02:08:40,420 --> 02:08:43,960
到底怎么回事？上校，怎么回事？
What the hell is this? Colonel, what's going on?

1986
02:08:43,960 --> 02:08:46,550
我是履行职责，以后也会这样做
I did my job. I'd do it again.

1987
02:08:46,590 --> 02:08:49,760
我得赶飞机回我的基地了
I'm gonna get on a plane and go on back to my base.

1988
02:08:49,760 --> 02:08:53,560
你哪都不能去，上校 宪兵，保护好上校
You're not going anywhere, Colonel. M.P. S, guard the colonel.

1989
02:08:53,560 --> 02:08:55,020
是，长官
Yes, sir.

1990
02:08:57,020 --> 02:08:59,610
罗斯上尉 这是搞什么鬼？
Captain Ross. What the hell is this?

1991
02:08:59,610 --> 02:09:02,610
杰赛普上校，你有权保持沉默
Colonel Jessup, you have the right to remain silent.

1992
02:09:02,610 --> 02:09:07,280
是指控我有罪吗？我犯了什么罪？
I'm being charged with a crime? Is that what this is?

1993
02:09:07,280 --> 02:09:10,700
我被指控有罪吗？ 你有权找一位律师
I'm being charged with a crime? You have a right to consult a lawyer.

1994
02:09:10,700 --> 02:09:14,620
荒谬，真是荒谬 你可以自已指定一名律师
This is funny. That's what this is. This lawyer may be appointed by you.

1995
02:09:14,620 --> 02:09:18,370
我要挖出你的眼睛，用你的头骨当便壶
I'm gonna rip the eyes out of your head and piss in your dead skull!

1996
02:09:18,370 --> 02:09:20,380
你毁了海军陆战队
You fucked with the wrong Marine!

1997
02:09:20,380 --> 02:09:23,880
杰赛普上校 你明白我刚才宣读的权利了吗？
Colonel Jessup, do you understand these rights as I have just read them?

1998
02:09:30,010 --> 02:09:32,850
你们这些混蛋
You fucking people.

1999
02:09:32,850 --> 02:09:35,680
你们不知道怎样保家卫国
You have no idea how to defend a nation.

2000
02:09:35,680 --> 02:09:39,190
你今天的作为只会危害到国家，凯菲
All you did was weaken a country today, Kaffee.

2001
02:09:39,190 --> 02:09:41,230
这就是你干的好事
That's all you did.

2002
02:09:41,270 --> 02:09:46,440
你将人民的生命置于危险之中 做你的美梦去吧，小子
You put people's lives in danger. Sweet dreams, son.

2003
02:09:46,440 --> 02:09:48,650
别叫我小子
Don't call me son.

2004
02:09:48,650 --> 02:09:53,160
我是美国海军中的一名律师和军官…
I'm a lawyer and an officer in the United States Navy...

2005
02:09:53,160 --> 02:09:56,040
你被逮捕了，狗娘养的
and you're under arrest, you son of a bitch.

2006
02:10:00,250 --> 02:10:02,250
证人可以退下了
The witness is excused.

2007
02:10:24,360 --> 02:10:25,400
全体起立
All rise.

2008
02:10:36,910 --> 02:10:38,580
陪审团有结果了吗？
Have the members reached a verdict?

2009
02:10:38,620 --> 02:10:40,620
是的，大人
We have, sir.

2010
02:10:52,380 --> 02:10:55,970
道森准下士和一等兵多尼
Lance Corporal Dawson and Private First Class Downey.

2011
02:10:59,220 --> 02:11:03,440
谋杀罪名，陪审团认为该项指控…
On the charge of murder, the members find the accused...

2012
02:11:03,440 --> 02:11:05,440
罪名不成立
not guilty.

2013
02:11:06,440 --> 02:11:10,110
共谋谋杀罪名…
On the charge of conspiracy to commit murder...

2014
02:11:10,110 --> 02:11:13,990
陪审团认为该项指控罪名不成立
the members find the accused not guilty.

2015
02:11:16,700 --> 02:11:20,580
对一名海军陆战队员行为不当罪名…
On the charge of conduct unbecoming a United States Marine...

2016
02:11:20,580 --> 02:11:26,630
陪审团认为该项指控罪名成立
the members find the accused guilty as charged.

2017
02:11:28,380 --> 02:11:31,590
据此所判刑期已于关押期间服满…
The accused are hereby sentenced to time already served...

2018
02:11:31,590 --> 02:11:36,640
并勒令从海军陆战队不荣誉解职
and you are ordered to be dishonorably discharged from the Marine Corps.

2019
02:11:37,890 --> 02:11:40,020
现在宣布退庭
This court-martial is adjourned.

2020
02:11:40,060 --> 02:11:41,980
全体起立
All rise.

2021
02:11:57,780 --> 02:11:59,790
那是什么意思？
What does that mean?

2022
02:12:01,790 --> 02:12:02,700
哈罗德
Harold

2023
02:12:04,920 --> 02:12:06,880
那是什么意思？
What did that mean?

2024
02:12:10,130 --> 02:12:14,420
我没明白，杰赛普上校都说了 是他下的“红色条规”令
I don't understand. Colonel Jessup said he ordered the Code Red.

2025
02:12:14,420 --> 02:12:18,430
我知道 他都承认了，我们没做错什么
I know. What did we do wrong?

2026
02:12:18,430 --> 02:12:22,020
这事没那么简单 我们没做错什么
It's not that simple. We did nothing wrong!

2027
02:12:22,020 --> 02:12:23,430
不，我们有错
Yeah, we did.

2028
02:12:26,560 --> 02:12:30,610
我们本该为那些没有自卫能力的人而战斗
We were supposed to fight for people who couldn't fight for themselves.

2029
02:12:31,610 --> 02:12:34,360
我们本该为圣地亚哥而战斗
We were supposed to fight for Willie.

2030
02:12:42,080 --> 02:12:45,210
我要带他们去人事处办些手续
I have to take these men over to personnel for some paperwork.

2031
02:12:55,840 --> 02:12:56,760
哈罗德
Harold

2032
02:13:00,350 --> 02:13:01,260
长官？
Sir?

2033
02:13:03,270 --> 02:13:06,230
你用不着手臂上的臂章来证明你的尊严
You don't need to wear a patch on your arm to have honor.

2034
02:13:09,730 --> 02:13:10,520
立正
attention hand

2035
02:13:12,770 --> 02:13:15,940
向长官致敬
There's an officer on deck.

2036
02:13:39,760 --> 02:13:42,100
空军奥马雷和罗德瑞格…
Airmen Cecil O'Malley and Anthony Rodriguez...

2037
02:13:42,100 --> 02:13:45,020
到底是来作什么证？
What exactly were these guys gonna testify to?

2038
02:13:45,020 --> 02:13:47,270
如果没弄错，他们是来宣誓证明…
Unless I'm mistaken, they were both gonna testify under oath...

2039
02:13:47,270 --> 02:13:50,350
他们确实什么都记不起来了
that they had absolutely no recollection of anything.

2040
02:13:50,350 --> 02:13:53,730
重要的证人 而且很帅，你觉得呢？
Strong witnesses. And handsome too, don't you think?

2041
02:13:55,190 --> 02:13:57,900
回见，我得去逮捕肯德瑞克
I'll see you around campus. I gotta go arrest Kendrick.

2042
02:13:57,900 --> 02:13:59,150
代我向他问好
Tell him I say hi.

2043
02:14:00,610 --> 02:14:02,240
我会的
Will do.
